\c 1
\s1 David in his old age
\rem /s1 King David in His Old Age; Solomon succeeds David; The Struggle for the Succession; David in His Old Age; Adonijah Sets Himself Up as King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* KingВҰ155591 DavidВҰ155592 had become very old, andВҰ155591 \add вүҲhe couldn't keep warm even when coveredВҰ155596 withВҰ155597 blankets\add*,
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* his servantsВҰ155604 \add вүҲsuggested\add*, вҖң\add вүҲAllow us search for a youngВҰ155608 womanВҰ155608 who can wait onВҰ155618 you and take care of your needsВҰ155605. She can sleep beside you and keep our\add* master, the king, warm.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ155623\add* they searchedВҰ155623 \add вүҲthroughout\add* YisraelВҰ155628 and foundВҰ155629 a beautifulВҰ155625 youngВҰ155624 womanВҰ155624 called AvishagВҰ155632 (a ShunammiteВҰ155633) and broughtВҰ155634 her to the kingВҰ155636.
\v 4 \add *She\add* was incredibly beautifulВҰ155639 andВҰ155638 she \add вүҲtook care of\add* the king, butВҰ155638 \add *he\add* didn'tВҰ155648 \add вүҲhave sexualВҰ155649 relations\add* with her.
\s1 Adoniyyah tries to become king
\rem /s1 Adonijah Claims the Throne
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ155651 \add David and\add* Haggit'sВҰ155654 son Adoniyyah \add вүҲpromoted himselfВҰ155655\add* saying, вҖңI, myself, will reign.вҖқ He \add вүҲacquired\add* a chariotВҰ155661 and horsemenВҰ155662 and fiftyВҰ155663 men who ran \add вүҲalong in front\add*.\x + \xo 1:5: \xt 2Sam 3:4.\x*
\v 6 \add @Haggit\add* had given birth to him afterВҰ155686 Avshalom. He was \add вүҲa good-looker\add*, \add butВҰ155668\add* hisВҰ155672 fatherВҰ155671 \add вүҲhad never disciplined\add* him \add or ever\add* asked, вҖңWhy did you do that?вҖқ
\v 7 \add вүҲHe had spoken\add* with Tseruyah's son YoavВҰ155692 and the priestВҰ155698 Evyatar and theyВҰ155689 had \add both\add* \add вүҲagreed to supportВҰ155699\add* \add *him\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ155703\add* the priestВҰ155704 Tsadok and Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ155705, the prophetВҰ155710 NatanВҰ155709, ShimeiВҰ155711 and ReiВҰ155712, and \add вүҲDavid'sВҰ155715 top warriors\add* were \add all\add* \add вүҲagainst\add* Adoniyyah.
\p
\v 9 ThenВҰ155722 Adoniyyah sacrificedВҰ155722 sheepВҰ155724 and cattleВҰ155726 and fattenedВҰ155726 calves near the Zohelet stoneВҰ155728 (whichВҰ155730 is besideВҰ155732 Eyn-RogelВҰ155734), and he \add вүҲinvited\add* all his brothersВҰ155740 (the king's sonsВҰ155741), and all the menВҰ155745 of YehudahВҰ155746 \add including\add* the king's servantsВҰ155747.
\v 10 \add вүҲHowever\add*, he didn'tВҰ155762 inviteВҰ155763 the prophetВҰ155753 NatanВҰ155752, BenayahВҰ155754, the \add вүҲtop warriors\add*, or his brother Shelomoh.
\s1 Shelomoh is made king
\rem /s1 Solomon Is Made King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ155765 NatanВҰ155766 \add вүҲasked\add* Shelomoh's motherВҰ155772 Batsheva, вҖңHaven't youВҰ155777 heardВҰ155777 that Haggit'sВҰ155783 son Adoniyyah \add вүҲhas made himself kingВҰ155779\add*, andВҰ155784 ourВҰ155784 masterВҰ155784 DavidВҰ155785 doesn't \add even\add* \add вүҲrealise\add*?\x + \xo 1:11: \xt 2Sam 12:24.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ155789\add* pleaseВҰ155792 let me advise you now \add вүҲso that you can save your own life andВҰ155789 that of your son Shelomoh\add* \add (SolomonВҰ155802)\add*.
\v 13 Go and \add вүҲask\add* KingВҰ155809 DavidВҰ155810, вҖҳMy masterВҰ155816 the king, didn'tВҰ155813 you promise your femaleВҰ155819 servant, saying, вҖңSurely your son Shelomoh will reignВҰ155825 afterВҰ155826 me, and he will sit on my throneВҰ155831?вҖқ \add вүҲSo why has Adoniyyah becomeВҰ155833 king\add*?вҖҷ
\v 14 ThenВҰ155844 while you're stillВҰ155838 there talkingВҰ155839 to the king, I'llВҰ155845 come in behind you and \add вүҲconfirmВҰ155847 what you said\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ155852\add* Batsheva \add вүҲwentВҰ155852 to the king's bedroom where\add* Avishag (the ShunammiteВҰ155864) was attending \add *him\add* \add вүҲin his old age\add*.
\v 16 BatshevaВҰ155871 bowedВҰ155870 \add вүҲlow to show respect\add* to the king, andВҰ155870 he \add вүҲasked her what she wanted\add*.
\p
\v 17 вҖңMy masterВҰ155884,вҖқ she \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңyou yourself \add вүҲpromised\add* to your female servantВҰ155889 \add вүҲinВҰ155887 front of\add* your godВҰ155888 YahwehВҰ155884 that your son Shelomoh \add вүҲwould be the one to reignВҰ155894 afterВҰ155895 you andВҰ155882 sitВҰ155897 onВҰ155887 your\add* throneВҰ155900.
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ155902\add* now, listen, AdoniyyahВҰ155904 \add вүҲhas becomeВҰ155905 king\add* \add instead\add*, andВҰ155902 you \add вүҲhaven't even been told about it\add*.
\v 19 He's sacrificingВҰ155912 \add вүҲmany\add* oxen and calves and sheepВҰ155916, and he invitedВҰ155931 the priestВҰ155924 Evyatar, and YoavВҰ155925 the commanderВҰ155926 of the army, and all your sonsВҰ155921 \add вүҲexcept for\add* your servantВҰ155929 Shelomoh.
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ155933\add* \add now\add* \add вүҲeveryone's waiting to see what you'll do\add*, my master the king. \add вүҲTheyВҰ155939 want you to make it clearly known who'll be the king on the throneВҰ155947 afterВҰ155951 you\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲOtherwise\add*, as soon as my masterВҰ155955 the kingВҰ155957 \add passes on\add* \add вүҲto join his ancestorsВҰ155960\add*, my son Shelomoh andВҰ155953 I will be \add вүҲconsidered to be вҖҳin the wayвҖҷ\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲJust\add* thenВҰ155967, while she was stillВҰ155968 talkingВҰ155969 with the king, the prophetВҰ155974 NatanВҰ155973 \add вүҲappeared\add*
\v 23 and \add вүҲhis arrival\add* was announced to the king. HeВҰ155981 wentВҰ155983 \add вүҲinto the room and knelt in frontВҰ155984 of the king and bowedВҰ155986 his face\add* to the floor.
\v 24 ThenВҰ155993 \add *he\add* \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңMy masterВҰ155995 the kingВҰ155996, \add вүҲdid you announce that Adoniyyah will reignВҰ156000 afterВҰ156001 you andВҰ155993 sitВҰ156003 on your\add* throneВҰ156006?
\v 25 \add I ask\add* because today he sacrificedВҰ156012 plenty of oxen and calves and sheepВҰ156016. He'd \add вүҲinvited\add* all your sonsВҰ156021 and army commandersВҰ156023, and Evyatar the priestВҰ156026. They're \add all\add* eatingВҰ156028 and drinkingВҰ156029 with him and saying, вҖҳ\add вүҲLong liveВҰ156032\add* KingВҰ156022 Adoniyyah!вҖҷ
\v 26 ButВҰ156036 as for me, I'm \em your\em* servant, andВҰ156036 \add вүҲnor did he inviteВҰ156049\add* TsadokВҰ156040 the priestВҰ156041 or Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ156042, or Shelomoh your servant.
\v 27 DidВҰ156060 my master the king \add вүҲorganise that without telling\add* your servantsВҰ156062 who will sit on the throneВҰ156068 of my master the king afterВҰ156072 him?вҖқ
\rem /s1 David Makes Solomon King; The Accession of Solomon
\p
\v 28 Then KingВҰ156076 DavidВҰ156077 saidВҰ156078, вҖңCall Batsheva \add back in\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* she cameВҰ156085 \add back\add* into the king's \add room\add* and stoodВҰ156088 in front of \add *him\add*.
\v 29 ThenВҰ156092 the kingВҰ156093 \add вүҲpromised\add*, вҖңAsВҰ156101 YahwehВҰ156097 lives \add вүҲandВҰ156094 has rescued me from every danger\add*,
\v 30 I promise you \add in front of\add* Yisrael'sВҰ156114 godВҰ156113 Yahweh that yourВҰ156119 son Shelomoh will reignВҰ156120 afterВҰ156121 me andВҰ156122 will sitВҰ156123 onВҰ156112 my throneВҰ156126 in my placeВҰ156127. \add вүҲI'llВҰ156130 put it in action today\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 Batsheva \add вүҲknelt down and bowedВҰ156134 her faceВҰ156138 to the floor\add* and said, вҖңMay my masterВҰ156144, the king DavidВҰ156146 live \add вүҲforever\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 Then KingВҰ156152 DavidВҰ156153 \add вүҲcalled out\add*, вҖң\add вүҲSummon\add* TsadokВҰ156157 the priestВҰ156158 for me, and NatanВҰ156159 the prophetВҰ156160, and Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ156161.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* theyВҰ156165 cameВҰ156165 \add вүҲinto the king's room\add*.
\v 33 вҖңTake some of \add *my\add* servantsВҰ156176,вҖқ the kingВҰ156170 \add вүҲinstructed\add* them. вҖңand put my son Shelomoh on my mule and lead him to the GihonВҰ156193 \add Spring\add*.
\v 34 Then \add you two,\add* TsadokВҰ156198 and NatanВҰ156200, must anointВҰ156195 him thereВҰ156197 as king over YisraelВҰ156205. Then blow the horn and \add вүҲshout\add*, вҖҳLet KingВҰ156202 Shelomoh live!вҖҷ
\v 35 Then \add вүҲfollow him back here where he must\add* comeВҰ156215 and sitВҰ156216 on my throneВҰ156219. Then he'll reignВҰ156221 in my placeВҰ156222 as rulerВҰ156226 of YisraelВҰ156229 and YehudahВҰ156232.вҖқ
\p
\v 36 вҖң\add вүҲCertainly\add*,вҖқ BenayahВҰ156235 replied. вҖңJust as YahwehВҰ156249, the godВҰ156248 of my masterВҰ156249 the king has instructed.
\v 37 Just as YahwehВҰ156257 has been with my master the king, so may he be with Shelomoh. And may \add вүҲhis rule be\add* \add even\add* greaterВҰ156265 than \add *that\add* of my master, the king DavidВҰ156272.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 \add вүҲSoВҰ156274\add* TsadokВҰ156275 the priestВҰ156276 and NatanВҰ156277 the prophetВҰ156278 and Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ156279 and the \add вүҲkings bodyguards\add* went and put Shelomoh on the king's mule, and took him to GihonВҰ156298.
\v 39 TsadokВҰ156301 the priestВҰ156302 tookВҰ156300 the horn of oilВҰ156306 from the sacred tent and anointedВҰ156310 Shelomoh \add withВҰ156315 it\add*, and theyВҰ156316 blew the horn and all the peopleВҰ156319 \add вүҲshouted\add*, вҖңLet KingВҰ156321 Shelomoh liveВҰ156320!вҖқ
\v 40 ThenВҰ156324 all the people \add вүҲfollowed\add* him \add back\add* uphill \add to the city\add*, and the people were playingВҰ156330 flutesВҰ156330 and were \add вүҲso exuberant inВҰ156331 theirВҰ156337 celebrations that the ground shookВҰ156335 withВҰ156331 the noiseВҰ156337\add*.
\p
\v 41 \add вүҲWhenВҰ156339\add* Adoniyyah and all \add вүҲhis invited guestsВҰ156343\add* had finishedВҰ156347 eatingВҰ156348, they heard the noise, and YoavВҰ156350 heard the sound of the horn and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWhat's all that commotion in\add* the cityВҰ156359?вҖқ
\v 42 He was still speakingВҰ156363 when Yonatan the son of Evyatar the priestВҰ156369 \add suddenly turned up\add*, and Adoniyyah \add вүҲcalled\add* \add >him\add*, вҖңCome \add over here\add* because you're a \add вүҲgood fellow\add* and you'll bring good newsВҰ156379.вҖқ
\p
\v 43 вҖң\add Actually, no,\add*вҖқ Yonatan answeredВҰ156381. вҖңOur masterВҰ156386 the king DavidВҰ156389 has \add just\add* made Shelomoh \add вүҲking\add*.
\v 44 The king sentВҰ156395 TsadokВҰ156401 the priestВҰ156402 and NatanВҰ156405 the prophetВҰ156406 and Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ156407 and the \add вүҲking's bodyguards\add*, and they placed \add @Shelomoh\add* on the king's mule.
\v 45 ThenВҰ156419 TsadokВҰ156421 and NatanВҰ156423 anointedВҰ156419 him as kingВҰ156425 atВҰ156426 GihonВҰ156426. \add Now\add* they've \add вүҲgone back\add* from thereВҰ156428 \add вүҲcheering\add* \add all the way\add*, and the \add whole\add* cityВҰ156431 is \add happily\add* \add вүҲcelebrating\add*. That's the noiseВҰ156433 thatВҰ156434 you're all hearing.
\v 46 \add вүҲWhat's more\add*, Shelomoh's sitting on the royalВҰ156442 throneВҰ156441 \add right now\add*.
\v 47 \add вүҲAs well as that\add*, the king's servantsВҰ156447 \add вүҲwent in\add* to bless our masterВҰ156452 the king DavidВҰ156454, saying, вҖҳMay God make Shelomoh's \add вүҲreputation\add* \add even\add* better than yours, andВҰ156444 may he make his \add вүҲreign\add* \add even\add* greaterВҰ156464 than yours.вҖҷ ThenВҰ156444 the king in his bed, bowedВҰ156469 down
\v 48 and saidВҰ156478, вҖҳBlessed be Yisrael'sВҰ156483 godВҰ156482 YahwehВҰ156481 who has \add вүҲprovided\add* \add a son\add* to sit on my throneВҰ156490 today, and \add вүҲI've been able to see it\add* \add before my death\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 49 ThenВҰ156494 all Adoniyyah'sВҰ156500 invited guestsВҰ156498 started tremblingВҰ156494, and they all got up and \add вүҲquietly slipped back to their homes\add*.
\v 50 Adoniyyah \add himself\add* was now afraidВҰ156506 of what Shelomoh would do, \add вүҲso\add* he wentВҰ156510 \add to the sacred tent\add* andВҰ156505 held onВҰ156512 to the hornsВҰ156512 of the altarВҰ156513.
\v 51 Shelomoh was told, вҖңListen, Adoniyyah \add вүҲis afraid of the new king because\add* he's grabbed the hornsВҰ156527 of the altarВҰ156528 andВҰ156515 said, вҖҳLet Shelomoh the king promise me as soon as \add вүҲpossible\add*, that he won't \add вүҲexecute\add* his servantВҰ156541 withВҰ156527 the swordВҰ156542.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 52 вҖңIf he \add вүҲshows himself as a loyal subject\add*,вҖқ Shelomoh \add вүҲrespondedВҰ156544\add*, вҖң\add вүҲthen he'll be able to keep his head\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ156544\add* if \add вүҲhe's foundВҰ156559 to be a traitor\add*, then he'll dieВҰ156562.вҖқ
\v 53 \add вүҲSoВҰ156564\add* KingВҰ156565 Shelomoh sent \add for Adoniyyah\add*, and they broughtВҰ156567 him down from beside the altarВҰ156569. He came and bowed down to Shelomoh the king and Shelomoh told him, вҖңGo \add вүҲhomeВҰ156579\add*.вҖқ
\c 2
\s1 David's final words to Shelomoh
\rem /s1 David's Charge to Solomon; David's Instruction to Solomon; David's Last Instructions to Solomon; David's Final Instructions to Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲWhen DavidВҰ156585 knew that his death was close, he instructedВҰ156587\add* his son Shelomoh,
\v 2 вҖңI'll soon be \add вүҲcoming to my end, butВҰ156600\add* \add you must be\add* strongВҰ156600 and \add вүҲsensible\add*.
\v 3 You \add вүҲmust maintain\add* your godВҰ156610 Yahweh's chargeВҰ156607 to walk in his waysВҰ156612, to keepВҰ156604 his statutesВҰ156614, his commandsВҰ156615, his judgements, and his testimoniesВҰ156617, according to what is writtenВҰ156618 in Mosheh'sВҰ156620 instructions, so that you'll \add вүҲbe wise\add* in everything you do and everywhere that you turnВҰ156632,
\v 4 so that Yahweh's promiseВҰ156640 to me that he'd keep one of my descendants onВҰ156654 Yisrael'sВҰ156669 throneВҰ156668, will stand because he gave the condition, вҖҳIf your descendants will \add вүҲobey me and worship me\add* inВҰ156654 truth with all their \add #hearts\add* and with all their \add #souls\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 5 вҖңAlso you're \add вүҲaware of\add* what Tseruyah's son YoavВҰ156679 did to meвҖ”what he did to twoВҰ156685 of the commandersВҰ156687 of Yisrael'sВҰ156689 armiesВҰ156688вҖ”to Ner'sВҰ156693 son AbnerВҰ156690 and to Yeter'sВҰ156697 son AmasaВҰ156694. He murderedВҰ156698 them, \add вүҲshedding blood\add* in peace\add -time\add* \add вүҲas if it was in a war\add*, and \add вүҲthe blood guilt is onВҰ156703 him from head to toe\add*.\x + \xo 2:5: a \xt 2Sam 3:27; \xo b \xt 2Sam 20:10.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ156721 use\add* yourВҰ156715 \add own\add* wisdomВҰ156715, butВҰ156714 don'tВҰ156716 let \add @Yoav\add* \add вүҲget old andВҰ156716 die peacefullyВҰ156720\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever,\add* return loyalВҰ156729 kindness to the sonsВҰ156724 of BarzillaiВҰ156725 the GileaditeВҰ156726, and \add вүҲinvite them to join youВҰ156727\add* atВҰ156731 your tableВҰ156732 because they \add вүҲhelped\add* me when I was fleeing from your brotherВҰ156741 AbshalomВҰ156740.\x + \xo 2:7: \xt 2Sam 17:27-29.\x*
\p
\v 8 Then there's Gera'sВҰ156748 son ShimeiВҰ156745, the Benyamite from BahurimВҰ156752. He cursedВҰ156754 me \add вүҲhorribly when I was\add* going to MahanaimВҰ156759. Then he wentВҰ156758 down to meet me atВҰ156767 the YordanВҰ156764, andВҰ156743 I promised him by Yahweh that I wouldn't \add вүҲexecute\add* him,\x + \xo 2:8: \xt 2Sam 16:5-13; 19:16-23.\x*
\v 9 \add вүҲso\add* don'tВҰ156775 leave him unpunishedВҰ156777 now. You're a wise manВҰ156779 andВҰ156774 you'll knowВҰ156782 \add вүҲhow to handle\add* him. \add вүҲAlthough he's old, make sure he has a bloodyВҰ156792 death\add*.
\s1 David's death
\rem /s1 The Death of David; Death of David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ156795 David \add вүҲbreathed his last\add* andВҰ156800 was buriedВҰ156800 inВҰ156801 the City of David.
\v 11 \add *He\add* had reigned over YisraelВҰ156811 for fortyВҰ156812 yearsвҖ”sevenВҰ156816 years from HebronВҰ156814 and thirty-three years from YerushalemВҰ156818.\x + \xo 2:11: \xt 2Sam 5:4-5; 1Ch 3:4.\x*
\v 12 Shelomoh \add вүҲreplaced\add* his fatherВҰ156830 DavidВҰ156829 on the throneВҰ156828, andВҰ156831 his \add вүҲauthority\add* was establishedВҰ156831 \add вүҲwith firmness\add*.\x + \xo 2:12: \xt 1Ch 29:23.\x*
\s1 Adoniyyah's provocation and death
\rem /s1 The Death of Adonijah; Solomon Consolidates His Reign; Solomon Establishes His Rule; Solomon's Throne Established
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ156835 Haggit'sВҰ156839 son Adoniyyah cameВҰ156835 to Shelomoh's motherВҰ156846 Batsheva andВҰ156835 she \add вүҲasked\add* \add >him\add*, вҖңIs your coming peacefulВҰ156850?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲIt is\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲCan I ask youВҰ156858 something?\add*вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲGo ahead\add*,вҖқ she answered.
\p
\v 15 вҖңYou yourself knowВҰ156864 that the kingship was for me \add as the oldest son\add*,вҖқ he saidВҰ156862, вҖңand all YisraelВҰ156874 \add вүҲwanted\add* me to reign. \add вүҲButВҰ156862 then Yahweh decided that it was for my brotherВҰ156880, and then everything got\add* turnedВҰ156877 around.
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ156886\add* now, I \add вүҲhave only one thing to request from youВҰ156891вҖ”please don'tВҰ156892 refuse me\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңGo on,вҖқ she saidВҰ156898.
\p
\v 17 He saidВҰ156902, вҖңPlease speakВҰ156903 to Shelomoh the kingВҰ156907 because he wouldn't \add вүҲrefuse you\add*. \add Ask him\add* to giveВҰ156915 me Avishag the ShunammiteВҰ156921 as my wife.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:17: \xt 1Ki 1:3-4.\x*
\p
\v 18 вҖң\add вүҲOkay\add*,вҖқ Batsheva \add вүҲagreed\add*, вҖңI'llВҰ156930 \add вүҲpersonally\add* speakВҰ156930 to the kingВҰ156934 for youВҰ156931.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ156936\add* Batsheva went to KingВҰ156942 Shelomoh to speakВҰ156944 to him \add вүҲon Adoniyyah's behalf\add*. The king rose to meet her and bowedВҰ156953 down to her. ThenВҰ156936 he sat on his throne and he had a throne placed on his rightВҰ156964 for his motherВҰ156961 to sit on.
\v 20 ThenВҰ156966 she said, вҖңI have one smallВҰ156969 request for you. \add Please\add* \add вүҲdon'tВҰ156973 say you won'tВҰ156973 do it\add*вҖқ
\p вҖң\add What's yourВҰ156991\add* request, myВҰ156978 motherВҰ156984,вҖқ the king \add вүҲrespondedВҰ156966\add*, вҖңbecause I \add вүҲcouldn't refuse you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖңLet Avishag the ShunammiteВҰ156998,вҖқ she saidВҰ156993, вҖңbe givenВҰ156994 to your brotherВҰ157000 Adoniyyah as a wife.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 KingВҰ157004 Shelomoh answeredВҰ157003 his motherВҰ157007, вҖңYou're requesting Avishag the ShunammiteВҰ157014 for Adoniyyah! \add вүҲYou might as well\add* request the \add вүҲthrone\add* for him, because he's my brotherВҰ157024 and he's olderВҰ157025 than I am! And thenВҰ157003 \add he'll want\add* Evyatar the priestВҰ157029 and Tseruyah's son YoavВҰ157030!вҖқ
\v 23 Then Shelomoh promised by Yahweh, вҖңMay GodВҰ157045 do to me \add вүҲwhatever he wants\add*, unless Adoniyyah \add вүҲpays withВҰ157039 his lifeВҰ157049 for saying that\add*.
\v 24 And now as YahwehВҰ157060 \add вүҲlives\add*, the one who establishedВҰ157062 me and caused me to sit on the throneВҰ157067 of my fatherВҰ157069 David, and who \add вүҲpromised David'sВҰ157068 descendants to continue reigning\add*, Adoniyyah will certainly be put to deathВҰ157079 today.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ157082\add* KingВҰ157083 Shelomoh \add вүҲinstructed\add* Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ157086 and he \add went and\add* struckВҰ157090 \add @Adoniyyah\add* down and he diedВҰ157093.
\s1 Evyatar's banishment and Yoav's death
\rem /s1 Abiathar's Banishment and Joab's Death
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 26 Then concerning Evyatar the priestВҰ157097, the king told \add >him\add*, вҖңGo to your fieldsВҰ157104 atВҰ157109 AnatotВҰ157100 because you're \add вүҲmarked for\add* deathВҰ157107, butВҰ157096 I won'tВҰ157111 \add вүҲdo it today\add* because you carriedВҰ157115 my masterВҰ157119 Yahweh's \add sacred\add* boxВҰ157118 \add вүҲahead of\add* my father DavidВҰ157122, and because you \add вүҲsuffered through\add* all that my father \add вүҲsuffered\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:26: a \xt 2Sam 15:24; \xo b \xt 1Sam 22:20-23.\x*
\v 27 \add That was how\add* Shelomoh \add banished\add* Evyatar from beingВҰ157137 a priestВҰ157138 to Yahweh. \add It was done\add* to fulfillВҰ157140 what Yahweh had said at ShilohВҰ157151 said about \add removing\add* \add вүҲEli'sВҰ157150 descendants\add*.\x + \xo 2:27: \xt 1Sam 2:27-36.\x*
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲWhen\add* the \add вүҲnewsВҰ157154 of that reached\add* YoavВҰ157160, he fled to Yahweh's tent and held onto the hornsВҰ157175 of the altarВҰ157176, because \add *he\add* had \add вүҲsupported\add* Adoniyyah (even though he hadn't \add вүҲsupported\add* Avshalom).
\v 29 \add Someone\add* told KingВҰ157179 Shelomoh that YoavВҰ157183 had fled to Yahweh's tent and was \add there\add* besideВҰ157189 the altarВҰ157190, \add вүҲso\add* Shelomoh \add вүҲinstructed\add* Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ157195, вҖңGo \add вүҲand strike him down\add*.вҖқ
\v 30 \add вүҲSo\add* BenayahВҰ157206 entered Yahweh's tent and he told \add @Yoav\add*, вҖңThe king said for you to come out.вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, I'llВҰ157223 die here,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p \add вүҲSo\add* Benayah \add вүҲwentВҰ157205 back to the king and reported both sides of the conversation\add*
\v 31 and the kingВҰ157240 told him, вҖңJust do \add вүҲwhat he saidВҰ157238\add*. \add вүҲKill\add* him and buryВҰ157247 him, and \add in that way\add* you'll removeВҰ157248 \add вүҲthe blood guilt from me and my descendants\add* for the blood that YoavВҰ157254 shed withoutВҰ157251 causeВҰ157251.
\v 32 YahwehВҰ157261 will return his bloodВҰ157264 onto his \add own\add* head, because he attacked twoВҰ157270 menВҰ157272 more righteousВҰ157273 and betterВҰ157274 than himself: Ner'sВҰ157287 son AbnerВҰ157284, the commander of Yisrael'sВҰ157291 army, and Yeter'sВҰ157297 son AmasaВҰ157294, the commander of Yehudah'sВҰ157301 army. He killedВҰ157276 them with the swordВҰ157277 and my fatherВҰ157278 DavidВҰ157279 didn'tВҰ157280 \add вүҲhave anything to do with it\add*.
\v 33 Their shed bloodВҰ157304 will return onto Joav's head and onВҰ157305 the \add #heads\add* of his \add вүҲdescendants forever\add*. ButВҰ157303 for DavidВҰ157310 and his \add вүҲfamily\add* and his \add вүҲdescendants\add* and his throneВҰ157313, \add вүҲYahwehВҰ157320 will give\add* peaceВҰ157315 \add вүҲforever\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲSoВҰ157322\add* Yehoyada'sВҰ157326 son BenayahВҰ157323 went and \add вүҲstruckВҰ157327\add* \add @Yoav\add* \add atВҰ157332 the altar\add* and \add вүҲkilledВҰ157330\add* himВҰ157330. ThenВҰ157322 he was buriedВҰ157331 onВҰ157332 his \add property\add* inВҰ157332 the wildernessВҰ157333.
\v 35 The king \add вүҲappointed\add* BenayahВҰ157339 \add вүҲas army commander to replace\add* \add @Yoav\add*, andВҰ157335 \add вүҲappointed\add* TsadokВҰ157349 as priestВҰ157350 in place of Evyatar.
\s1 Shimei's execution
\rem /s1 The Death of Shimei
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ157356 the kingВҰ157357 \add вүҲsummoned\add* ShimeiВҰ157359 and told him, вҖңBuild yourselfВҰ157364 a houseВҰ157365 \add here\add* inВҰ157366 YerushalemВҰ157366 and liveВҰ157367 there. \add вүҲButВҰ157356\add* don'tВҰ157369 goВҰ157371 \add вүҲanywhere else\add*
\v 37 \add вүҲbecause\add* the dayВҰ157378 that you \add вүҲleave andВҰ157376 crossВҰ157380\add* the KidronВҰ157384 valley, you can be certain that you'll die. YourВҰ157381 bloodВҰ157390 will be onВҰ157392 your \add own\add* head.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖңMy masterВҰ157401 the king,вҖқ ShimeiВҰ157395 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ157394\add*, вҖң\add вүҲyour decision is good andВҰ157394 your servantВҰ157405 will do just what you said\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 39 \add вүҲHowever,\add* threeВҰ157415 yearsВҰ157416 \add later\add*, twoВҰ157418 of Shimei'sВҰ157421 slaves fled to Maacah'sВҰ157427 son, KingВҰ157428 Akish of GatВҰ157429, and Shimei was told \add вүҲwhere they'd gone\add*.
\v 40 \add вүҲSoВҰ157437\add* ShimeiВҰ157438 saddledВҰ157439 his donkeyВҰ157442 and \add вүҲrode it\add* to Akish at GatВҰ157444 to \add вүҲtry to find\add* his slaves and \add *he\add* \add вүҲwas able to recover them\add*
\v 41 \add вүҲButВҰ157460\add* ShelomohВҰ157461 was told that ShimeiВҰ157465 \add left\add* YerushalemВҰ157466 and gone to GathВҰ157467 and thenВҰ157460 returnedВҰ157468.
\v 42 \add вүҲSoВҰ157470\add* the kingВҰ157471 \add вүҲsummoned\add* ShimeiВҰ157473 andВҰ157470 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңDidn't I \add вүҲget you to promise\add* by Yahweh \add вүҲthat you heardВҰ157496 me say that whenever\add* you leave here, you'll certainly die? And didn'tВҰ157476 you tell me that it \add вүҲwas a good decision\add*?
\v 43 \add вүҲSoВҰ157498\add* why didn'tВҰ157499 you keep the \add вүҲpromise by\add* YahwehВҰ157503 andВҰ157498 \add obey\add* \add вүҲwhat IВҰ157509 instructedВҰ157509\add* you?
\v 44 YouВҰ157516 yourself knowВҰ157518 \add вүҲall the evil things thatВҰ157523 you did\add* to my fatherВҰ157529 DavidВҰ157528, \add вүҲso now\add* YahwehВҰ157531 will returnВҰ157530 your evil onВҰ157535 your head.
\v 45 \add вүҲButВҰ157537\add* \add despite what you yelled out,\add*\x + \xo 2:45 \xt 2Sa 16:5-8.\x* \add Yahweh\add* \add вүҲwill blessВҰ157539 me as kingВҰ157537, andВҰ157540 David'sВҰ157541 throneВҰ157540 will be establishedВҰ157543 forever in frontВҰ157544\add* of Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 46 ThenВҰ157550 the kingВҰ157551 commandedВҰ157550 Yehoyada's son BenayahВҰ157554, and he wentВҰ157558 out and put \add @Shimei\add* \add вүҲto death\add*.
\p \add In those ways,\add* \add вүҲShelomoh establishedВҰ157564 his control of the kingdomВҰ157563\add*.
\c 3
\s1 Shelomoh requests wisdom
\rem /s1 Solomon's Prayer for Wisdom; Solomon Asks for Wisdom; Solomon Prays for Wisdom
\s4 Full kingdom
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 1.3-12)
\p
\v 1 Shelomoh made himself the son-in-law of Egypt'sВҰ157575 kingВҰ157574 Far-oh \add вүҲby taking Far-oh's daughterВҰ157579 as a wife\add* and bringing herВҰ157582 into the cityВҰ157585 of DavidВҰ157586 (\add where she stayed\add* untilВҰ157587 \add вүҲthe completion of the construction of his palace and of Yahweh's temple\add*, and the wall aroundВҰ157601 YerushalemВҰ157600).
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the peopleВҰ157604 were sacrificingВҰ157605 \add вүҲonВҰ157606 various hills\add* because \add вүҲatВҰ157606 that time\add*, a \add вүҲtemple\add* hadn't \add yet\add* been builtВҰ157610 for YahwehВҰ157613.
\v 3 Shelomoh \add demonstrated his\add* \add вүҲlove for\add* YahwehВҰ157623 by \add вүҲobeying the instructions\add* of his fatherВҰ157627 DavidВҰ157626. \add вүҲHowever,\add* heВҰ157630 would \add offer\add* sacrificesВҰ157631 and burn incenseВҰ157632 \add вүҲonВҰ157625 various hills\add*.
\p
\v 4 \add One time,\add* the kingВҰ157635 wentВҰ157634 to GibeonВҰ157636 to sacrifice thereВҰ157638, because it was the \add вүҲmost popular\add* highВҰ157641 placeВҰ157641. Shelomoh offeredВҰ157644 up a thousandВҰ157643 burntВҰ157644 up \add вүҲsacrifices\add* on that altarВҰ157648,
\v 5 and that nightВҰ157658 in Gibeon, YahwehВҰ157653 appearedВҰ157652 to Shelomoh in a dreamВҰ157657 and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhat would you like me to giveВҰ157663 you?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 Shelomoh \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңYou yourself \add вүҲshowed incredible loyalty to\add* your servantВҰ157673 DavidВҰ157674, my fatherВҰ157675, because he walkedВҰ157679 in faithfulnessВҰ157681 and obedience \add вүҲin front of you\add*, and \add вүҲdid what he believed youВҰ157682 wanted\add*. And you'veВҰ157670 \add вүҲmaintained this loyalty towardsВҰ157685\add* him and you \add вүҲallowed him to have\add* a son sitting onВҰ157681 his throneВҰ157701 as \add вүҲI am today\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ157705\add* now, YahwehВҰ157706 my godВҰ157707, you yourself have caused your servantВҰ157712 to reign in placeВҰ157713 of my fatherВҰ157715 DavidВҰ157714, butВҰ157705 I'm \add вүҲstill youngВҰ157718вҖ”I don'tВҰ157719 really knowВҰ157720 much about anything\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲYet\add* your servantВҰ157724 is among your chosenВҰ157728 peopleвҖ”a numerousВҰ157731 people who can'tВҰ157733 be countedВҰ157737 because \add вүҲthere's so many\add* \add of us\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ157740 please\add* give your servantВҰ157741 \add вүҲthe ability to listenВҰ157743 to your people and to judge them well\add*вҖ”discerningВҰ157748 betweenВҰ157749 good and evil, because who's able to judge your peopleвҖ”\add вүҲthat's a heavy task\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲYahwehВҰ157766 was very pleased that ShelomohВҰ157769 had requested that\add*
\v 11 and told him, вҖңBecauseВҰ157781 you requested that and didn'tВҰ157785 request a long lifeВҰ157798 or riches for yourself, or requested the \add #lives\add* of your enemiesВҰ157799, butВҰ157775 you requested discernmentВҰ157803 for yourself \add вүҲwhen listening and dispensing\add* justice,
\v 12 then I've done \add вүҲwhat you requested\add*. Listen, I've given you a wise and discerningВҰ157815 \add вүҲmindВҰ157813 unlike anyone who's lived before you or who will live in the future\add* afterВҰ157822 you.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ157828\add* I'veВҰ157833 also given you what you didn'tВҰ157830 request: both riches andВҰ157828 honourВҰ157840вҖ”there'll be \add вүҲno other king like you for as long as you live\add*,
\v 14 and if you'll \add вүҲobey\add* my statutesВҰ157857 and commandsВҰ157858 like your father DavidВҰ157861 did, thenВҰ157852 I'llВҰ157862 \add also\add* lengthenВҰ157863 your \add вүҲlife\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Then Shelomoh \add вүҲwoke up\add*, and wow, it had been a dreamВҰ157872, and he wentВҰ157873 \add into\add* YerushalemВҰ157874 and stoodВҰ157875 \add вүҲin frontВҰ157877 of the sacred chestВҰ157879\add*. Then he offered up burntВҰ157884 offerings and made peaceВҰ157886 offerings, and he \add вүҲheld\add* a feastВҰ157888 for all his servantsВҰ157891.
\s1 Shelomoh judges a difficult case
\rem /s1 Solomon Judges a Difficult Case; Solomon's Wisdom in Judgment; Solomon Judges Wisely; A Wise Ruling
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲOne day\add* twoВҰ157896 prostitutesВҰ157898 cameВҰ157895 to the kingВҰ157901 andВҰ157902 stoodВҰ157902 \add вүҲin front of\add* himВҰ157903,
\v 17 and one of them said, вҖңPlease, my masterВҰ157909, \add вүҲus two women live in the same\add* house, and \add вүҲwhile she was there\add* in the house, I gave birthВҰ157916 \add to a baby\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲThree days later\add*, this womanВҰ157927 also gave birth \add to her baby\add*. \add вүҲOnly the two of us were thereВҰ157931\add* inВҰ157935 the houseвҖ”no \add вүҲone else was around\add*.
\v 19 \add ButВҰ157942\add* thenВҰ157942 in the nightВҰ157947, \add *her\add* son diedВҰ157942 because sheВҰ157949 \add вүҲrolled over onto\add* him.
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ157952\add* she \add вүҲgot up\add* inВҰ157963 the middleВҰ157953 of the nightВҰ157954 and took my son from besideВҰ157959 me, as your female servantВҰ157960 was asleep. She \add вүҲleft her dead son withВҰ157963 me, and took my son to her bed\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ157971\add* I woke up in the morning \add ready\add* to breastfeed my son, \add вүҲto my horror\add* heВҰ157979 was dead. \add However\add* when I examined him closelyВҰ157980 in the light, more shock, it wasn't \add actually\add* my son!вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңNo, my son is the living one,вҖқ the otherВҰ157993 woman said, вҖңand your son is the dead one.вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, \em your\em* son is the dead one,вҖқ the firstВҰ158000 woman \add вүҲcountered\add*, вҖңand \em my\em* son is the living one!вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ157991 they \add continuedВҰ157991 to\add* \add вүҲargueВҰ158008 in frontВҰ158009 of\add* the kingВҰ158010.
\p
\v 23 The kingВҰ158013 spoke, вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ158012 both of you are claiming that your baby is the one that's aliveВҰ158019 andВҰ158012 that the dead one belongs to the otherВҰ158022\add*.вҖқ
\v 24 Then \add *he\add* \add вүҲordered\add*, вҖңGet me a sword.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* they broughtВҰ158038 a sword to the king.
\v 25 ThenВҰ158043 the kingВҰ158044 \add вүҲcommanded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲCut\add* the livingВҰ158049 childВҰ158048 into twoВҰ158050 pieces andВҰ158043 giveВҰ158051 \add вүҲthem half each\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲButВҰ158061\add* the \add вүҲmother of the surviving baby\add* felt compassionВҰ158073 for her son andВҰ158061 \add вүҲyelled\add*, вҖңPlease, my masterВҰ158080, giveВҰ158081 the baby to herвҖ”you certainly mustn't \add вүҲkill\add* him!вҖқ
\p \add вүҲMeanwhile the otherВҰ158092 womanВҰ158062\add* was sayingВҰ158093, вҖң\add вүҲWell thenВҰ158061, neitherВҰ158094 of us will have him. Cut him in half\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 27 The kingВҰ158105 \add вүҲspoke up\add*, вҖңDon't harm the baby. Give the livingВҰ158113 childВҰ158112 to the \add first\add* womanвҖ”she's his motherВҰ158118.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 All YisraelВҰ158123 \add eventually\add* heardВҰ158120 \add вүҲabout this case\add* that the king had judgedВҰ158126, andВҰ158120 they \add вүҲfelt an awesome respect for\add* \add *him\add* because they saw that he had God's wisdomВҰ158137 to do justiceВҰ158141 within him.
\c 4
\s1 Shelomoh's officials
