\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* Shelomoh was king over all YisraelВҰ158152,
\v 2 andВҰ158155 theseВҰ158155 were his officialsВҰ158156:
\q1 Tsadok'sВҰ158163 son AzaryahuВҰ158160 was the priestВҰ158164.
\q1
\v 3 Shisha'sВҰ158170 sonsВҰ158169 ElihorefВҰ158167 andВҰ158168 AhiyyahВҰ158168 were secretaries.
\q1 Ahilud'sВҰ158175 son YehoshafatВҰ158172 was the recorderВҰ158176.
\q1
\v 4 Yehoyada's son Benayah was the army commander.
\q1 TsadokВҰ158185 andВҰ158178 Evyatar were priestsВҰ158187.
\q1
\v 5 Natan'sВҰ158193 son Azaryahu was supervisor of the governors,
\q1 and his son Zavud was a priestВҰ158201 and adviser to the kingВҰ158203.
\q1
\v 6 Ahishar was in charge of the palaceВҰ158208,
\q1 andВҰ158209 Avda's son AdoniramВҰ158209 \add вүҲsupervised\add* the forcedВҰ158215 labourersВҰ158215.
\p
\v 7 ShelomohВҰ158218 \add вүҲappointed twelve governors\add* over all YisraelВҰ158227, and they \add sent inВҰ158236\add* food for the palaceвҖ”each \add governor\add* was responsible for one monthВҰ158235 of the yearВҰ158236.
\v 8 Their namesВҰ158246 were:
\q1 Ben-HurВҰ158249 inВҰ158250 the hill countryВҰ158250 of EfrayimВҰ158251,
\q1
\v 9 Ben-DekerВҰ158256 inВҰ158257 Makats, Shaalvim, Beyt-Shemesh, and Eylon-Beyt-Hanan,
\q1
\v 10 Ben-HesedВҰ158268 inВҰ158269 ArubotВҰ158269, Sokoh, and all the land of HeferВҰ158275,
\q1
\v 11 Ben-Avindav (who was married to Shelomoh's daughterВҰ158286 Tafat) in Nafat-DorВҰ158284,
\q1
\v 12 Ahilud'sВҰ158297 son BaanaВҰ158294 in Taanak and MegiddoВҰ158299 and all Beyt-Shan next to Tsaretan below YezreelВҰ158308, from Beyt-Shan to Avel-MeholahВҰ158313, as far as the otherВҰ158315 side of YokmeamВҰ158316,
\q1
\v 13 Ben-GeberВҰ158321 in Ramot-Gilead, including the villagesВҰ158325 of Menashsheh'sВҰ158329 son YairВҰ158326 thatВҰ158330 were in Gilead, as well as the Argov area in the BashanВҰ158336 regionВҰ158333, and including sixtyВҰ158337 largeВҰ158339 citiesВҰ158338 withВҰ158322 walls and bronzeВҰ158342 \add gate\add* bars.
\q1
\v 14 Iddo'sВҰ158348 son Ahinadav in Mahanayim.
\q1
\v 15 Ahimaats (who had married Shelomoh's daughterВҰ158360 BasematВҰ158359) inВҰ158352 NaftaliВҰ158352,
\q1
\v 16 Hushai'sВҰ158368 son Baana inВҰ158369 AsherВҰ158369 andВҰ158370 BealotВҰ158370,
\q1
\v 17 Paruah'sВҰ158376 son YehoshafatВҰ158373 inВҰ158377 YissakarВҰ158377,
\q1
\v 18 Ela'sВҰ158383 son ShimeiВҰ158380 inВҰ158384 BenyaminВҰ158384,
\q1
\v 19 Uri'sВҰ158390 son GeberВҰ158387 in the GileadВҰ158392 regionВҰ158391, \add including\add* the lands of the AmoriteВҰ158397 King SihonВҰ158394 and King OgВҰ158398 of the BashanВҰ158400.
\p \add вүҲThere was also one district governorВҰ158401 over Yehudah\add*.
\s1 Shelomoh's prosperity
\rem /s1 Magnificence of Solomon's Rule; Solomon's Daily Provisions; Solomon's Prosperity and Wisdom; Solomon's Prosperous Reign
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 20 \add Now\add* Yehudah and YisraelВҰ158407 had become as numerousВҰ158408 as the sand on the seashore. They \add had plenty\add* to eat and drinkВҰ158417 and theyВҰ158416 were contented.
\v 21 Shelomoh \add вүҲcontrolled\add* all the kingdoms from the \add Euphrates\add* River to the land of the Philistines and as far as the Egyptian border, \add so they\add* brought tribute to \add *him\add* and \add вүҲfollowed his orders\add* \add вүҲduring his lifetime\add*.\x + \xo 4:21: \xt Gen 15:18; 2Ch 9:26.\x*
\p
\v 22 The \add вүҲdaily requirements for the palace included\add* five tonnes of fine flour and eleven tonnes of coarse flour,
\v 23 ten fattened cattle, twenty pasture cattle, one hundred sheep, \add wild game including\add* deer, gazelle, and roebuck, and fattened fowls.
\p
\v 24 He \add вүҲcontrolled all the kingdoms west of the Euphrates\add* from Tifsah \add in the north-east\add* to Gaza \add in the south-west\add*, and there was peace with all \add вүҲhis neighbours\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲSo\add* all Yehudah and Yisrael lived peacefully, from Dan \add in the north\add* to Be'er-Sheva \add in the south\add*вҖ”\add вүҲeveryone focusing on their own property\add*.
\p
\v 26 Shelomoh had forty thousand stalls for his chariot horses, and twelve thousand horsemen.\x + \xo 4:26: \xt 1Ki 10:26; 2Ch 1:14; 9:25.\x*
\v 27 \add вүҲThe district governors provided supplies for the palaceвҖ”one governor for each\add* month. They ensured that nothing was lacking for the king and \add вүҲhis visitors\add*.
\v 28 They also provided the barley and straw for the \add вүҲchariot horses and the other horses\add*, \add вүҲdelivered to the designated locations\add*.
\s1 Shelomoh's wisdom
\rem /s1 Solomon's Wisdom; Fame of Solomon's Wisdom
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 29 God gave Shelomoh wisdom and incredible understanding, and the breadth \add вүҲof his interests seemed without limit\add*.
\v 30 \add *He\add* \add вүҲwas wiser than anyone in the countries east of Yisrael or in\add* Egypt.
\v 31 He was wiser than \add вүҲanyone else\add*, including Eytan the Ezrahite and Mahol's son Heman and Kalkol and Darda, and his \add вүҲreputation spread to\add* all the surrounding countries.\x + \xo 4:31: \xt Psa 89 header.\x*
\v 32 He \add вүҲcould tell\add* three thousand proverbs and he \add composed\add* over a thousand songs.\x + \xo 4:32: \xt Prv 1:1; 10:1; 25:1; Song 1:1.\x*
\v 33 He \add вүҲcould lecture on plant life\add* from the cedars in Lebanon to the hyssop that grows on walls. He \add вүҲtaught\add* about animals, birds, reptiles, and fish.
\v 34 People \add вүҲfrom all around\add* came to listen to Shelomoh's wisdomвҖ”\add вүҲmany having been sent by other kings who'd heard about him\add*.
\c 5
\s1 The preparation of Shelomoh of making the temple
\rem /s1 Solomon Prepares to Build the Temple; Preparations for Building the Temple; Building of the temple; Preparations and Materials for the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 2:1-18)
\p
\v 1 Then King Hiram of Tsor \add (Tyre)\add* sent his servants to Shelomoh when he heard that he'd been anointed as king to replace his father, because Hiram \add вүҲhad always been a friend of\add* David.
\v 2 Shelomoh \add вүҲreplied\add* to Hiram,
\v 3 вҖңYou yourself knew David my father, \add вүЎand you knew\add* that he wasn't able to build a temple for his god Yahweh his god because of the \add вүҲconstant state\add* of warfare until Yahweh \add вүҲwould allow us to defeat all our enemies\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲButВҰ158488\add* now, my god Yahweh has \add вүҲenabled us to have peaceВҰ158496\add* from all aroundВҰ158502. \add вүҲWe have no enemy, and there's no threat of danger\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲSo\add* listen, I'm \add вүҲplanning\add* to build a residence for my god Yahweh, just as Yahweh spoke to my father David, вҖҳYour son who I'll put in your place on your throne, he'll \add be the one to\add* build the house \add вүҲto honour me\add*.вҖҷ\x + \xo 5:5: \xt 2Sam 7:12-13; 1Ch 17:11-12.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* now, \add please give the\add* command to fell cedars for me from the Lebanon \add forest\add*. Let my servants \add вүҲaccompany\add* your servants and I'll \add вүҲpay\add* your servants' wages \add вүҲwhatever amount you set\add*, because you yourself know that there are no \add вүҲother workers who know\add* how to fell trees like the Tsidonians.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲWhen Hiram got Shelomoh's message, he was very happy\add* and said, вҖңBlessed be Yahweh today, who has given David a wise son \add to rule\add* over that great \add вүҲnation\add*.вҖқ
\v 8 \add *He\add* sent \add this message back\add* to Shelomoh, вҖңI've \add вүҲreceived the message\add* that you sent me and I myself will \add вүҲsupervise everything you want including\add* cedar and cypress \add вүҲlogs\add*.
\v 9 My servants will \add вүҲtransport them down from the forest\add* to the ocean, and I'll \add вүҲget them tied into\add* rafts \add вүҲand float them to the place you specify and disassemble the rafts\add*. \add вүҲThen it'll be up to you to get them where you need them\add*. \add вүҲAll I ask for, is food for my family and workers\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSo\add* Hiram \add вүҲsupplied\add* all the cedar and cypress \add вүҲlogs\add* that Shelomoh \add вүҲordered\add*
\v 11 and each year Shelomoh \add вүҲsupplied\add* Hiram withВҰ158625 \add вүҲthree thousand tonnes\add* of wheat and \add вүҲfour hundred thousand litres of pure\add* \add olive\add* oil.
\v 12 Yahweh gave Shelomoh wisdom just like \add вүҲhe'd said he would\add*, and there was peace between Hiram and Shelomoh and the two of them \add вүҲmade a treaty with each other\add*.
\p
\v 13 King Shelomoh \add вүҲforced thirty thousand men from all over Yisrael to become his workers\add*,
\v 14 and each month he sent \add вүҲa group of\add* ten thousand of them to \add work in\add* Lebanon. \add @Each group\add* \add вүҲwould spend\add* a month in Lebanon and then two months \add вүҲat home\add* \add again\add*. Adoniram was \add вүҲput in charge of all that\add*.\x + \xo 5:14: \xt 1Ki 12:18.\x*
\v 15 Shelomoh \add also\add* \add вүҲforced eighty thousand men to cut stones in the hill country andВҰ158691 seventy thousand men to haul loads\add*.
\v 16 Then besides Shelomoh's chief officers who were \add вүҲin charge of\add* the work, there were \add another\add* three thousand three hundred supervisors of the workers.
\v 17 The king commanded \add вүҲthem to quarry large, valuable blocks of dressed stone for the temple foundations\add*.
\v 18 Shelomoh's and Hiram's workers and the Gebalites shaped the stones and prepared the timber for building the temple.
\c 6
\s1 Shelomoh begins temple construction
\rem /s1 Solomon Builds the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add So it was that\add* four hundredВҰ159066 and eightyВҰ159063 years afterВҰ159068 the IsraelisВҰ159071 leftВҰ159068 EgyptВҰ159074, inВҰ159063 the secondВҰ159081 month of the fourthВҰ159076 year of Shelomoh's reignВҰ159082 over YisraelВҰ159071, he began the construction of Yahweh's residence.
\v 2 \add вүҲIt would be\add* twenty-seven metres longВҰ159100, nine metres wideВҰ159102, and fourteen metres highВҰ159105.\f + \fr 6:2 \ft About the height of a modern five-storey building (and the same height as Noah's barge).\f*
\v 3 \add вүҲThe five-metre wide porch onВҰ159122 the front was the same lengthВҰ159115 as the templeВҰ159111 width, so nine metresВҰ159122 long\add*.
\v 4 The windowВҰ159131 \add openings\add* narrowed \add towards the outer edge of the wall\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲAgainstВҰ159143 the outside of the back wall andВҰ159135 the two sides\add*, he builtВҰ159135 \add three-storey (butВҰ159135 lower than the wall)\add* side rooms.
\v 6 \add вүҲThe lowestВҰ159156 level was just over two metresВҰ159158 wide, the middleВҰ159160 level was half a metre wider, and the top level the same again\add* \add (because the temple wall got thinner as it went up)\add*. \add вүҲThe temple walls had ledgesВҰ159169 built into them for the beams to sit onВҰ159158, so they wouldn't have to go through\add* the walls.
\p
\v 7 While the templeВҰ159196 was being built, all of the \add huge\add* stonesВҰ159182 were dressed at the quarryВҰ159185 \add site\add*, so there was no noise from any hammerВҰ159187 or axe or iron tool \add вүҲat the construction site\add*.
\p
\v 8 The \add вүҲentranceВҰ159199 to the bottom level of siderooms was onВҰ159207 the southВҰ159206 side of the templeВҰ159205, then from there, stairs wentВҰ159208 up to the middle level, and more stairs to the top level\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ159219\add* he builtВҰ159219 the temple \add walls\add*, thenВҰ159219 \add вүҲit was roofed withВҰ159230 cedarВҰ159230 beamsВҰ159228 andВҰ159219 planksВҰ159229\add*,
\v 10 and he builtВҰ159232 the \add вүҲsideroomsвҖ”each level just over two metresВҰ159243 highВҰ159244 and attached\add* to the temple withВҰ159249 cedarВҰ159250 \add beamsВҰ159249\add*.
\p
\v 11 Then YahwehВҰ159256 \add вүҲhad this messageВҰ159254 sent\add* to Shelomoh,
\v 12 вҖңThis residence that you'reВҰ159266 buildingВҰ159267, if you \add вүҲcomply withВҰ159271 my regulationsВҰ159271 and follow my judgements and obey\add* all my commandsВҰ159281, then I'llВҰ159294 \add вүҲensure that everything I promisedВҰ159287 your father DavidВҰ159293 will come to pass\add*.
\v 13 I will live among \add you\add* IsraelisВҰ159299 andВҰ159296 I'llВҰ159301 never abandonВҰ159301 my people YisraelВҰ159299.вҖқ
\s1 The temple furnishings
\rem /s1 The Temple's Interior; The Interior Furnishings of the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 3:8-14)
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSo\add* Shelomoh finishedВҰ159313 the construction of the templeВҰ159312,
\v 15 and onВҰ159321 the inside he made walls of cedarВҰ159322 boards. The floor was made withВҰ159321 cypressВҰ159338 boards, and the walls were panelled from the floor to the ceilingВҰ159328.
\v 16 Inside the temple, nine metres atВҰ159348 the rear \add were closed off\add* to make an innerВҰ159359 room called вҖҳthe very holy placeВҰ159361вҖҷ. That too had walls made of cedarВҰ159349 boardsВҰ159348.\x + \xo 6:16: \xt Exo 26:33-34.\x*
\v 17 That left the main temple room as eighteen metresВҰ159364 long,
\v 18 and it had cedar boards on the walls \add decorated with\add* carvingsВҰ159376 of buds and flowers \add вүҲin blossomВҰ159379\add*. \add вүҲAll the internal walls were covered with cedar so none of the large stonesВҰ159383 were visibleВҰ159384\add*.
\p
\v 19 The innerВҰ159386 room at the back was to houseВҰ159389 the boxВҰ159396 containing Yahweh's agreement,
\v 20 and the room (nine metres long and wide and high) was overlaid with pure gold and equipped with an \add incense\add* altarВҰ159415 overlaid with cedarВҰ159416.
\v 21 ThenВҰ159418 ShelomohВҰ159419 overlaid the \add вүҲmain room\add* with pure gold, andВҰ159418 he \add hung\add* gold chainsВҰ159427 crossing acrossВҰ159426 the entrance to the innerВҰ159431 room that was overlaid with gold.
\v 22 He overlaid \add the interior of\add* the entireВҰ159437 temple with gold untilВҰ159442 it was all finishedВҰ159444, including overlaying the altarВҰ159450 belongingВҰ159453 to the innerВҰ159453 room with gold.\x + \xo 6:22: \xt Exo 30:1-3.\x*
\rem /s1 The Furnishings of the Temple
\p
\v 23 In the innerВҰ159458 room, he made twoВҰ159459 winged creatures that were five metresВҰ159465 highВҰ159466 andВҰ159457 made of oliveВҰ159463 wood.\x + \xo 6:23-28: \xt Exo 25:18-20.\x*
\v 24 Each wing was over two metres long, \add вүҲgiving each one a total wingspan\add* of four andВҰ159468 a half metres.
\v 25 \add вүҲBoth creatures were the same size andВҰ159493 shapeВҰ159493\add*,
\v 26 \add andВҰ159503\add* \add вүҲthey were both five metresВҰ159502 high\add*.
\v 27 The \add two\add* winged creatures \add вүҲwere placed across the innerВҰ159514 room where their wingtips touched each other inВҰ159524 the centre andВҰ159507 their outer wings touched the walls\add*.
\v 28 \add BothВҰ159543 of\add* the \add вүҲwooden carvings\add* were overlaidВҰ159542 with goldВҰ159546.
\p
\v 29 He \add had\add* all the \add interior\add* wallsВҰ159551 of the temple engravedВҰ159556 with winged creatures and palm treesВҰ159559 and flowers \add вүҲin bloom\add*,
\v 30 andВҰ159565 he overlaidВҰ159569 the floorВҰ159567 \add вүҲof both rooms\add* with goldВҰ159570.
\p
\v 31 He made doorsВҰ159578 andВҰ159574 doorpostsВҰ159583 for the innerВҰ159576 room with oliveВҰ159581 wood,
\v 32 and \add вүҲboth\add* doorsВҰ159587 were \add вүҲdecorated\add* with carvings of winged creatures and palm trees and flowers \add вүҲin bloom\add*, thenВҰ159586 they were overlaidВҰ159598 with gold that was hammered over the carvings.
\v 33 He made the doorpostsВҰ159615 for the main temple entranceВҰ159613 with oliveВҰ159618 wood,
\v 34 andВҰ159622 the two folding doorsВҰ159623 themselves each had two folding sections made of cypressВҰ159625.
\v 35 \add These doors were also decorated with\add* carvings of winged creatures and palm treesВҰ159639 and flowers \add вүҲin bloom\add*, and thenВҰ159637 overlaidВҰ159642 with goldВҰ159643 smoothedВҰ159644 down over the carvings.
\p
\v 36 HeВҰ159650 builtВҰ159649 the innerВҰ159653 courtyardВҰ159652 with threeВҰ159654 rows of dressed stones andВҰ159657 a row of cedarВҰ159659 beamsВҰ159658.
\p
\v 37 The foundationВҰ159663 for Yahweh's residence was laid inВҰ159666 the second monthВҰ159666 of the fourthВҰ159662 yearВҰ159661 of Shelomoh's reign,
\v 38 and it was completedВҰ159677 inВҰ159669 the eighthВҰ159676 month of his eleventh yearВҰ159669вҖ”meeting all his specificationsВҰ159684 and requirements. SoВҰ159673 it took \add over\add* sevenВҰ159687 yearsВҰ159688 to buildВҰ159686 it.
\c 7
\s1 Shelomoh's palace
\rem /s1 Solomon's Palace; Solomon's Palace and Other Buildings; Solomon Builds His Palace
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 ShelomohВҰ159694 \add also\add* spent thirteen years getting his own palace finished.
\v 2 He builtВҰ159705 the вҖҳLebanonВҰ159711 Forest HallвҖҷ that was forty-six metres longВҰ159714, twenty-three metres wideВҰ159717, and fourteen metres highВҰ159720, with fourВҰ159722 rows of cedar pillars and cedar beamsВҰ159726 sitting across the pillars.
\v 3 It was roofedВҰ159732 withВҰ159733 cedarВҰ159733 boards onВҰ159733 forty-five supports set out into three rows of fifteen.
\v 4 There were three rows of window gaps arranged in sets of three.
\v 5 All the entrances and doorpostsВҰ159761 were made \add with wood\add* \add вүҲplaned with squareВҰ159762 sides\add*, and they were arranged in sets of threeВҰ159769.
\p
\v 6 He made \add &his\add* covered porch with pillars. It was twenty-three metres longВҰ159778 andВҰ159772 fourteen metres wideВҰ159781.
\p
\v 7 He made a \add вүҲhall\add* for \add &his\add* throne whereВҰ159794 he would judgeВҰ159795 \add >cases\add*вҖ”\add called\add* вҖҳThe Judgement HallвҖҷ. It was coveredВҰ159801 withВҰ159802 cedarВҰ159802 from floorВҰ159803 to ceiling.
\p
\v 8 His actual residence \add вүҲbehind\add* the hall was constructedВҰ159817 in a similarВҰ159817 way. Shelomoh also built a houseВҰ159820 for his wife who was Far-oh's daughterВҰ159822.\x + \xo 7:8: \xt 1Ki 3:1.\x*
\p
\v 9 All theseВҰ159833 buildings were constructed with expensive stonesВҰ159834 that had been cut to size and trimmed with saws inside and out. They went from the foundationВҰ159842 up to the eaves, and from the outsideВҰ159846 across to the greatВҰ159850 courtyardВҰ159849.
\v 10 These large, costlyВҰ159854 stones in the foundationsВҰ159852 \add were cut\add* \add вүҲin two sizes, with the largest almost five metresВҰ159859\add* \add long\add*.
\v 11 On top of those were other costlyВҰ159866 stonesВҰ159865 \add вүҲof various sizes\add*, andВҰ159869 thenВҰ159864 cedarВҰ159869 \add beams\add*.
\v 12 TheВҰ159883 largest courtyard had threeВҰ159874 rows of dressed stones and one row of cedarВҰ159879 beamsВҰ159878, as did the innerВҰ159884 temple courtyard and the \add вүҲpalace hall\add*.
\s1 Huram comes to work
\rem /s1 Products of Hiram the Bronzeworker; Furnishings for the Temple; Huram's Task; The Temple's Furnishings
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 13 King Shelomoh sentВҰ159889 for \add a craftsman \add* in Tsor \add (Tyre) called\add* Huram.\f + \fr 7:13 \ft Sometimes (including this passage) his named is spelt вҖҳHiramвҖҷ, but we've opted to consistently name him вҖҳHuramвҖҷ (as per 2 Chr. 4:11) to conveniently avoid confusion with King Hiram (also from Tsor/Tyre).\f*
\v 14 His mother was a widowВҰ159901 with NaftaliВҰ159904 ancestry, and his fatherВҰ159905 had been a bronze engraver in Tsor. He was \add вүҲvery knowledgeableВҰ159920 and skilled in everything to do\add* with bronze, and \add so\add* he cameВҰ159926 to workВҰ159924 for KingВҰ159929 Shelomoh.
\s1 The two bronze pillars
\rem /s1 The Two Bronze Columns
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 3:15-17)
\p
\v 15 He cast two \add hollow\add* bronzeВҰ159943 pillarsВҰ159942вҖ”each being just over eightВҰ159944 metres tall andВҰ159938 measuring over five metres around.
\v 16 ThenВҰ159961 he made two decorative bronzeВҰ159970 caps for those pillarsВҰ159968вҖ”each over two metresВҰ159972 high.
\v 17 To hang over them, he made ornamental chainsВҰ159987 and wreathsВҰ159985вҖ”seven sets over the cap on each pillarВҰ159993.
\v 18 ThenВҰ160001 he made two rows of \add decorative bronze\add* pomegranatesВҰ160020 to go aroundВҰ160007 each of the two caps.
\v 19 The two caps were each shaped like lilies thatВҰ160027 were nearly two metresВҰ160036 high
\v 20 andВҰ160038 there were two hundredВҰ160053 \add bronze\add* pomegranatesВҰ160052 in rows aroundВҰ160055 each cap. NEED A DIAGRAM
\p
\v 21 \add @Huram\add* \add вүҲstood\add* the \add two\add* pillars at the templeВҰ160065 entrance porch. (The left pillar got \add вүҲnicknamed\add* вҖҳYakinВҰ160075вҖҷ andВҰ160060 the one on the rightВҰ160070, вҖҳBoazВҰ160085вҖҷ.)
\v 22 The two bronze caps shaped like lilies \add were placed on\add* top of the pillars andВҰ160092 so the pillar construction was completed.
\s1 The bronze water tank
\rem /s1 The Bronze Tank
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 4:2-5)
\p
\v 23 \add @Huram\add* also cast a very large round basin \add nicknamed\add* вҖҳThe seaВҰ160099вҖҷ that was fiveВҰ160110 metres across (so a circumference of fourteen metres) andВҰ160096 over two metres highВҰ160112.
\v 24 \add вүҲPart of the same casting was twoВҰ160135 rows of decorative buds that went around it underВҰ160122 the lip of the basin. There were about eighteen buds for each metre of circumference\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲTwelve bronze cattle had also been cast and the large basin was sitting on theirВҰ160167 backs. The cattle were facing outwards with three facing towardsВҰ160168 each of the four compass points\add*.
\v 26 \add вүҲThe basin was about 8cm thickВҰ160170 andВҰ160170 itВҰ160181 had a lipВҰ160174 around the outside like a lily blossomВҰ160177. It could containВҰ160181 around forty-four thousandВҰ160179 litres\add* \add of water\add*.
\s1 The bronze basin holders
\rem /s1 The Bronze Carts
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ160185 \add @Huram\add* cast tenВҰ160188 bronzeВҰ160189 carts \add for individual water basins\add*. Each one was nearly two metres long and two metres wideВҰ160197 and just over a metre tall,
\v 28 andВҰ160207 they had frames on the sides with panels betweenВҰ160208 them.
\v 29 There were bronze lions, oxen, and winged creatures \add in relief\add* on the panels, and aboveВҰ160226 and belowВҰ160227 those, wreathsВҰ160230 were inset into the bronze.
\v 30 Each cart had two bronze axlesВҰ160239 with four bronze wheelsВҰ160235 attached to them. At each of the top four cornersВҰ160242, there were bronze supports to hold a \add wash\add* basinВҰ160246, andВҰ160234 these were also cast with \add decorative\add* wreathsВҰ160251.
\v 31 Inside \add вүҲthose supports there was a round frame that protruded half a metre upwards andВҰ160253 was inset by a quarter of a metre. It also had engravings onВҰ160257 it insideВҰ160254 squareВҰ160273 frames\add*.
\v 32 The axlesВҰ160281 were part of the main casting, andВҰ160277 the fourВҰ160277 70cm \add bronze\add* wheelsВҰ160285 were below the panels.
\v 33 The design of the wheels was similar to chariotВҰ160295 wheels, \add вүҲbutВҰ160291\add* with their axlesВҰ160296, rims, spokesВҰ160298, andВҰ160291 hubs all cast \add from bronze\add*.
\v 34 Each cart had four handles as part of the castingвҖ”one projecting from each cornerВҰ160307.
\v 35 There was a 25cm \add bronze\add* band aroundВҰ160322 the top of each cart as well as supports andВҰ160315 framesВҰ160327вҖ”all part of the main casting.
\v 36 He engraved winged creatures, lionsВҰ160339, and palm treesВҰ160340 on the flat areas of the carts wherever there was spaceВҰ160341, and \add вүЎengraved\add* wreathsВҰ160344 aroundВҰ160345 them.
\v 37 SoВҰ160349 that's how he made the tenВҰ160350 cartsвҖ”all the same shapeВҰ160356 and size using the same mold.
\p
\v 38 \add @Huram\add* also cast ten bronzeВҰ160364 \add wash\add* basins for the ten cartsвҖ”each one was almost two metresВҰ160372 across and could hold 900 litres \add of water\add*.\x + \xo 7:38: \xt Exo 30:17-21.\x*
\v 39 He put five \add basins on\add* carts on each side of the temple (northВҰ160399 and south \add of the east-facing temple\add*), and he put the huge basin \add on its bronze cattle\add* near the south-east cornerВҰ160408.
\rem /s1 Summary List of Temple Furnishings
\rem /r (2 Chronicles 4.11вҖ”5.1)
\v 40 Huram \add also\add* made the basins and the \add ash\add* shovelsВҰ160419 and the bowls.
\s1 The list of temple objects
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 4:11вҖ“5:1)
\p \add вүҲSo\add* Huram finished everything thatВҰ160431 KingВҰ160433 Shelomoh had requested him to make for Yahweh's residence:
\v 41 two \add massive\add* pillars with \add large\add* decorated caps and then networks of chain over the caps,
\v 42 the four hundred pomegranates with each pillarВҰ160486 having two strings of one hundred of them placed over them,
\v 43 the ten carts andВҰ160488 the ten basinsВҰ160494 on them,
\v 44 the \add huge\add* water tank andВҰ160504 the twelve cattle supporting it,
\v 45 and the pots and shovelsВҰ160518 and bowls and all the other containers.
\p All the above was made from polishedВҰ160537 bronzeВҰ160536 by Huram for KingВҰ160532 Shelomoh for Yahweh's residence.
\v 46 The kingВҰ160542 \add had them\add* cast in the clay in the YordanВҰ160540 valley between Sukkot andВҰ160547 Tsaretan.
\v 47 \add вүҲNoneВҰ160551 of the above was weighedВҰ160562, becauseВҰ160557 bronzeВҰ160563 was so plentiful that itВҰ160561 didn'tВҰ160560 matter\add*.
\p
\v 48 Shelomoh also had the gold items made for Yahweh's residence, including the gold \add incense\add* altarВҰ160575 andВҰ160565 the gold tableВҰ160579 for the \add вүҲsacred\add* breadВҰ160582,\x + \xo 7:48: a \xt Exo 30:1-3; \xo b \xt Exo 25:23-30.\x*
\v 49 the ten pure gold lampstands that were placed five on each side of the entrance to the innerВҰ160594 room, along with the gold flowersВҰ160597, lamps, andВҰ160586 tongsВҰ160599,\x + \xo 7:49: \xt Exo 25:31-40.\x*
\v 50 the pureВҰ160613 gold cups, trimmers, bowls, dishesВҰ160605, and firepansВҰ160606, and \add also\add* the gold door socketsВҰ160609 for the innerВҰ160612 holiest room and the main room of the templeВҰ160616.
\p
\v 51 \add вүҲFinally\add* all the workВҰ160624 thatВҰ160625 KingВҰ160627 Shelomoh did for Yahweh's residence was completed, and \add *he\add* \add had\add* all the holy thingsВҰ160635 from his fatherВҰ160638 DavidВҰ160637, including the silverВҰ160641 and the goldВҰ160644 and the containers, taken into the storerooms of the \add вүҲtemple\add*.\x + \xo 7:51: \xt 2Sam 8:11; 1Ch 18:11.\x*
\c 8
\s1 The sacred box is taken to the temple
\rem /s1 Temple worship; Dedication of the Temple; The Covenant Box Is Brought to the Temple; The Ark Brought to the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 5:2вҖ“6:2)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* Shelomoh assembledВҰ160655 the IsraeliВҰ160659 leadersВҰ160667, and the tribal and \add вүҲclan\add* heads, in YerushalemВҰ160675 \add to celebrate\add* the arrival of the boxВҰ160679 containing Yahweh's agreement coming from David'sВҰ160684 cityВҰ160683, i.e., TsiyyonВҰ160686/ZionВҰ160686.\x + \xo 8:1: \xt 2Sam 6:12-16; 1Ch 15:25-29.\x*
\v 2 \add *This all happened\add* during the Celebration \add in Shelters\add* in the seventhВҰ160702 month of Etanin.\x + \xo 8:2: \xt Lev 23:34.\x*
\v 3 TheВҰ160707 IsraeliВҰ160706 eldersВҰ160706 andВҰ160708 the priestsВҰ160709 lifted the \add sacred\add* boxВҰ160712
\v 4 and \add вүҲcarried\add* it \add to the temple\add*. \add OtherВҰ160718\add* priestsВҰ160733 and LevitesВҰ160734 brought all the \add вүҲsacred objects\add* from the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 5 KingВҰ160736 ShelomohВҰ160737 and all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ160741\add* who were there, \add вүҲwalked\add* ahead of the boxВҰ160746, sacrificingВҰ160747 \add more\add* sheepВҰ160748 and cattle than could be countedВҰ160753, becauseВҰ160756 there were so many.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ160758 the priestsВҰ160759 broughtВҰ160758 the boxВҰ160762 containing the agreement into the innerВҰ160771 roomВҰ160768 in the temple (the very holy place), andВҰ160758 \add placed it\add* beneath the wingsВҰ160780 of the \add two wooden\add* winged creatures,
\v 7 The two creatures had their wings stretched out \add and touching in the middle of the roomВҰ160789\add* where the sacred box was placedВҰ160789, so their wings coveredВҰ160791 over the top of the box and itsВҰ160798 \add carrying\add* polesВҰ160798.
\v 8 The poles were \add very\add* long and the ends of \add *them\add* could be seen from the entrance to that innerВҰ160812 roomВҰ160808, \add вүҲbutВҰ160801\add* \add otherwise\add* they couldn't be seen from the outsideВҰ160815, and they're still thereВҰ160817 to this dayВҰ160819.
\v 9 ThereВҰ160822 was nothing inВҰ160823 the boxВҰ160823 except for the twoВҰ160825 stoneВҰ160827 slabs thatВҰ160828 MoshehВҰ160831 \add (Moses)\add* had put inside atВҰ160823 \add вүҲMt. Sinai (also called Horev) \add* whereВҰ160833 YahwehВҰ160835 made the agreement withВҰ160823 the IsraelisВҰ160839 after \add вүҲhe'd brought them out\add* of EgyptВҰ160842.\x + \xo 8:9: \xt Deu 10:5.\x*
\p
\v 10 WhenВҰ160844 the priestsВҰ160846 cameВҰ160845 back out of the holy placeВҰ160849, a cloudВҰ160850 filledВҰ160851 Yahweh'sВҰ160855 residence\x + \xo 8:10-11: \xt Exo 40:34-35.\x*
\v 11 andВҰ160857 the priestsВҰ160860 were unable to standВҰ160861 to ministerВҰ160862 because of the cloudВҰ160864, because Yahweh's \add вүҲpresence\add* had filledВҰ160867 his temple.
\rem /s1 Solomon Blesses the People
\v 12 Then Shelomoh said, вҖңYahwehВҰ160880 stated that he would dwellВҰ160882 inВҰ160883 the cloudy darknessВҰ160883.\x + \xo 8:12: \xt Psa 18:11; 97:2.\x*
\v 13 Actually, I'veВҰ160886 builtВҰ160886 a raised houseВҰ160887 for youвҖ”where you can live foreverВҰ160892.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh's address to the people
\rem /s1 Solomon's Address to the People; Solomon's Speech
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 6:3-11)
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ160894 while all the people stood there, the kingВҰ160895 turnedВҰ160894 aroundВҰ160894 andВҰ160894 \add вүҲpronounced a blessingВҰ160899\add* on all YisraelВҰ160904,
\v 15 saying, вҖңBlessed is YahwehВҰ160913, the godВҰ160914 of YisraelВҰ160915, who spokeВҰ160917 \add вүҲaudibly to\add* my fatherВҰ160921 DavidВҰ160920, andВҰ160911 thenВҰ160911 put into action the promise he'd given,
\v 16 вҖҳFrom the dayВҰ160928 when I broughtВҰ160930 my people Yisrael out of EgyptВҰ160937, I didn'tВҰ160938 choose a cityВҰ160941 from \add among\add* all the tribesВҰ160943 of Yisrael to buildВҰ160945 a houseВҰ160946 \add inВҰ160941\add* so that my nameВҰ160948 would be \add established\add* thereВҰ160949. \add вүҲInstead\add* I choseВҰ160940 DavidВҰ160951 to \add вүҲlead\add* my people Yisrael.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 8:16: \xt 2Sam 7:4-11; 1Ch 17:3-10.\x*
\p
\v 17 \add Shelomoh continued,\add* вҖңMy fatherВҰ160963 DavidВҰ160962 wanted to buildВҰ160964 a temple to confirm Yahweh's \add вүҲpower andВҰ160958 authority here\add*.\x + \xo 8:17-18: \xt 2Sam 7:1-3; 1Ch 17:1-2.\x*
\v 18 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ160975, YahwehВҰ160972 told him that it was good that he wanted to buildВҰ160983 a temple for him\add*,
\v 19 however he wouldn't be the one to build it, because it would be his \add вүҲbiological\add* son who would do it.\x + \xo 8:19: \xt 2Sam 7:12-13; 1Ch 17:11-12.\x*
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲNow\add* Yahweh has \add вүҲput his promiseВҰ161014 into action\add*, and I'm here now having succeeded my fatherВҰ161020 DavidВҰ161019вҖ”sitting on Yisrael's throneВҰ161024 just as Yahweh said, and I've been the one to build the residence for Yisrael's godВҰ161033 Yahweh.
\v 21 I'veВҰ161051 included a placeВҰ161038 for the boxВҰ161039 containing \add the two stone tablets with\add* the agreement thatВҰ161045 YahwehВҰ161044 made with our ancestorsВҰ161049 when he broughtВҰ161050 them out of EgyptВҰ161053.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh's prayer of dedication
\rem /s1 Solomon's Prayer; Solomon's Prayer of Dedication
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 6:12-42)
\p
\v 22 Then Shelomoh stoodВҰ161056 \add вүҲbetween\add* Yahweh's altarВҰ161059 and all the \add вүҲgathered IsraelisВҰ161065\add*, and \add вүҲheld his arms up towards the sky\add*
\v 23 and \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ161071, the god of YisraelВҰ161073, there'sВҰ161074 no godВҰ161072 like you inВҰ161078 the heavensВҰ161078 aboveВҰ161079 or \add here\add* onВҰ161078 the earthВҰ161082 belowВҰ161083, keeping the agreement and \add showing\add* loyal affection to your servantsВҰ161087, the ones who \add вүҲserve you withВҰ161078 honest devotion\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲYouВҰ161099 have done what you told your servantВҰ161096 DavidВҰ161097, my fatherВҰ161098, thatВҰ161100 you said you'd do\add*вҖ”you said it with your mouthВҰ161105 and then put it into action with your hands as \add we can see\add* today.
\v 25 Now, YahwehВҰ161112, the godВҰ161114 of Yisrael, \add вүҲdo the other things\add* for your servantВҰ161117 DavidВҰ161119 myВҰ161131 fatherВҰ161120, \add вүҲwhen you told him thatВҰ161122 there'll always be one of his descendants on Yisrael'sВҰ161115 throneВҰ161135, provided they follow you like he did\add*.\x + \xo 8:25: \xt 1Ki 2:4.\x*
\v 26 \add вүҲSoВҰ161151\add* now, GodВҰ161152 of YisraelВҰ161153, \add вүҲshow thatВҰ161158 you're faithful to do what you say, by doing what you told\add* your servantВҰ161160 DavidВҰ161161, my fatherВҰ161162.
\p
\v 27 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ161173\add* would GodВҰ161167 really reside on the earthВҰ161170? The sky and the heavensВҰ161173 \add вүҲaren'tВҰ161175 big enough for you\add* so how could this building I'veВҰ161183 constructed \add вүЎcontain you\add*?\x + \xo 8:27: \xt 2Ch 2:6.\x*
\v 28 \add вүҲButВҰ161185 still,\add* please give attention to your servant's prayer andВҰ161185 my request for favour, YahwehВҰ161193 my godВҰ161194. \add Please\add* listenВҰ161195 to my \add вүҲhumble\add* prayer thatВҰ161202 your servant is prayingВҰ161204 \add вүҲto you today\add*
\v 29 that your eyesВҰ161209 be on this houseВҰ161213 nightВҰ161215 and dayВҰ161216вҖ”the place that you'veВҰ161221 said \add вүҲwill be associated with your nameВҰ161223\add*. \add вүҲMay you answer\add* the \add #prayers\add* that your servantВҰ161231 will pray \add вүҲtowards\add* this place.\x + \xo 8:29: \xt Deu 12:11.\x*
\v 30 Listen to your servant'sВҰ161241 plea for favour, and \add the prayers thatВҰ161244\add* your peopleВҰ161242 YisraelВҰ161243 will pray toward this place. \add вүҲKeep listening from where you live in\add* the heavensВҰ161258, and hear and forgiveВҰ161260.
\p
\v 31 вҖңWhen someone \add is accused of\add* sinning againstВҰ161266 his neighbourВҰ161266 and says onВҰ161276 oath \add that the accusation is false\add*, and makes that oath in frontВҰ161274 of yourВҰ161275 altarВҰ161275 here in this temple,
\v 32 thenВҰ161279 youВҰ161281 should listenВҰ161281 from the heavensВҰ161282 and judgeВҰ161284 yourВҰ161287 people YisraelВҰ161285, so that wicked people will be condemnedВҰ161288 \add вүҲand bear the appropriate punishment\add*, and innocent people should be \add вүҲdeclared not guiltyВҰ161289 and dealt withВҰ161292 appropriately\add*.
\p
\v 33 WhenВҰ161312 your peopleВҰ161301 YisraelВҰ161302 are defeatedВҰ161300 by an enemyВҰ161304 because they've sinned against you, and they turnВҰ161309 back to you and confessВҰ161311 your nameВҰ161314 and pray, and pleadВҰ161316 for favour toward you inВҰ161300 this temple,
\v 34 thenВҰ161321 you should listenВҰ161322 from the heavensВҰ161323 and forgiveВҰ161324 the sinВҰ161325 of your peopleВҰ161326 YisraelВҰ161327, and bringВҰ161328 them back to this land thatВҰ161332 you gaveВҰ161333 to our ancestorsВҰ161334.
\p
\v 35 вҖң\add OrВҰ161353 when\add* the rain \add вүҲis held back inВҰ161337\add* the sky because \add @your people\add* have sinned against you, and then theyВҰ161344 pray towards this placeВҰ161350 and \add вүҲacknowledge you\add* and turnВҰ161357 away from the \add вүҲdisobedience that caused the problem\add*,
\v 36 thenВҰ161361 \add вүҲlistenВҰ161363 to them from\add* the heavensВҰ161364 and forgiveВҰ161365 the sin of your servantsВҰ161367 and your people YisraelВҰ161369, because you'll direct \add вүҲthem towards the right way to conduct themselves\add*. ThenВҰ161361 you'll \add вүҲsend\add* rain onto your land thatВҰ161376 you gave to your people as an inheritanceВҰ161389.
\p
\v 37 вҖңSuppose that there was a drought in the land, or \add вүҲdiseases like\add* blightВҰ161401 or mildewВҰ161402, or \add вүҲswarms of\add* locusts or grasshoppers, or if an enemyВҰ161411 \add вүҲbesieges them in a gated city\add*, or some other trouble or calamity,
\v 38 \add вүҲthen if anyone from\add* yourВҰ161433 peopleВҰ161433 YisraelВҰ161434 who knows \add вүҲabout their own disobedience\add* would spread out their palms toward this temple,
\v 39 thenВҰ161447 \add вүҲlistenВҰ161448 to them from yourВҰ161468 heavenlyВҰ161449 abode\add* and forgiveВҰ161452 their sin, and give them \add вүҲwhat they need\add*. You and you alone are the only one who knows \add вүҲwhat's inside a humanВҰ161475 heart\add*.
\v 40 \add вүҲThen\add* \add @the people\add* will \add вүҲwant to obey\add* you \add вүҲas long as they're aliveВҰ161485\add* \add here\add* in the land thatВҰ161482 you gaveВҰ161491 to our ancestorsВҰ161492.
\p
\v 41 вҖңAlso the foreignersВҰ161497 who are not \add вүҲdescendants of\add* YisraelВҰ161502 andВҰ161494 who came from distantВҰ161506 countries because of your \add вүҲreputation\add*
\v 42 (when they heard about your \add вүҲnature\add* and \add вүҲsaw your power in action\add*), and they come and pray toward this temple,
\v 43 \add then\add* listenВҰ161530 \add to them\add* from your abode in the heavensВҰ161531 and \add вүҲdo what that foreignerВҰ161540 begged of you\add*, so that all the countries will know your \add вүҲreputation and respect\add* you like your peopleВҰ161552 YisraelВҰ161553 do. Then they'll know that your \add вүҲauthority is connected with\add* this residence that I'veВҰ161564 builtВҰ161564.
\p
\v 44 вҖң\add вүҲWhen\add* your peopleВҰ161569 goВҰ161568 out to battleВҰ161570 against the enemyВҰ161573, and onВҰ161574 the road where you sent them they pray to \add you\add* YahwehВҰ161580, inВҰ161574 this cityВҰ161582 that you'veВҰ161584 chosenВҰ161584, withВҰ161574 this houseВҰ161586 that I'veВҰ161589 builtВҰ161589 for your \add вүҲhonour\add*,
\v 45 ThenВҰ161592 listenВҰ161592 from the heavensВҰ161593 to their prayerВҰ161596 and their request, and \add вүҲhelp their situation\add*.
\p
\v 46 вҖңIf they disobey you (because everyone sinsВҰ161613) and you're angryВҰ161614 withВҰ161615 them and \add вүҲcause them to be defeated by theirВҰ161620 enemies\add*, and then they get taken prisoner and led away to the enemy's country (even a far away country),
\v 47 and thenВҰ161629 they \add вүҲhave a change of mindВҰ161632\add* in the land whereВҰ161634 they were takenВҰ161635 to as captivesВҰ161635, and while they're still living in that land, they turn back and beg for your favour and confess, вҖҳWe've disobeyed and done wrongВҰ161646вҖ”we've behaved wickedlyВҰ161647,вҖҷ
\v 48 and they returnВҰ161649 to you with all their \add #hearts\add* and all their \add #souls\add* in the land of their enemiesВҰ161658 where they were taken captiveВҰ161661, and they pray to you toward the directionВҰ161665 of their country which you gaveВҰ161668 to their fathers, the cityВҰ161670 that you choseВҰ161672, and the residence that I'veВҰ161676 builtВҰ161676 for your \add вүҲhonour\add*,
\v 49 thenВҰ161680 \add вүҲlistenВҰ161680 to\add* their \add #prayers\add* and \add #requests\add* from yourВҰ161683 abode in the heavensВҰ161681, and \add вүҲhelp their situation\add*.
\v 50 Forgive yourВҰ161694 peopleВҰ161694 who've \add вүҲdisobeyed\add* youВҰ161705 andВҰ161693 \add вүЎforgive\add* the \add вүҲwicked things\add* thatВҰ161702 they've \add вүҲdone\add*. \add вүҲHelp their captorsВҰ161709 to be compassionate to\add* them,
\v 51 because \add they're\add* your peopleВҰ161714 and your \add вүҲspecial possession\add* who youВҰ161718 broughtВҰ161718 out from EgyptВҰ161719вҖ”from the middle of the iron-smelting furnaceВҰ161721.
\p
\v 52 вҖңMay \add вүҲyou notice\add* the plea for favour from your servantВҰ161730 and from your peopleВҰ161734 YisraelВҰ161735вҖ”to listenВҰ161736 to them inВҰ161738 all their crying out to you.
\v 53 BecauseВҰ161763 you yourself separatedВҰ161745 them for yourself as a \add вүҲspecial possession\add* out of all the peopleВҰ161749 groups inВҰ161753 the world, just as you said through your servantВҰ161756 MoshehВҰ161755 when you broughtВҰ161757 our ancestorsВҰ161760 out from EgyptВҰ161761, my masterВҰ161762 YahwehВҰ161762.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh blesses the people
\rem /s1 The Final Prayer; Solomon Blesses the Assembly; The Dedication of the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 54 Once Shelomoh was finishedВҰ161768 praying this prayerВҰ161777 and request for favour to Yahweh, he stoodВҰ161780 up from bowing on his kneesВҰ161787 with his palms spreadВҰ161789 out toward the heavensВҰ161790 in front of Yahweh's altarВҰ161782,
\v 55 thenВҰ161792 stoodВҰ161792 \add there\add* andВҰ161793 blessedВҰ161793 all the IsraeliВҰ161798 \add вүҲpeople\add*, saying,
\v 56 вҖңBlessed be YahwehВҰ161804, who has givenВҰ161806 \add вүҲpeace to\add* his peopleВҰ161808 YisraelВҰ161809 \add вүҲlike he said he would\add*. \add вүҲHe didn'tВҰ161813 fail to do even one part out of all the goodВҰ161820 things that he told his servantВҰ161825 MoshehВҰ161824 that he'd do\add*.\x + \xo 8:56: \xt Deu 12:10; Josh 21:44-45.\x*
\v 57 May our godВҰ161829 YahwehВҰ161828 be with us, just as he was with our ancestorsВҰ161835. May he not leaveВҰ161838 us \add вүҲor\add* abandonВҰ161841 us,
\v 58 \add вүҲhelp us to want to follow him and\add* walk on all his paths and \add вүҲobey\add* his commandsВҰ161851 and statutesВҰ161852 and judgements \add вүҲthatВҰ161854 heВҰ161855 gave\add* our ancestorsВҰ161858.
\v 59 May \add вүҲthis prayer\add* of mine pleading for Yahweh's favourВҰ161864, be \add вүҲremembered by\add* our godВҰ161871 Yahweh day and nightВҰ161873вҖ”to \add вүҲprotect\add* \add both\add* his servantВҰ161877 and his peopleВҰ161879 YisraelВҰ161880 \add вүҲas each day requires\add*,
\v 60 so that all the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ161890 groups in the worlds\add* would knowВҰ161887 that YahwehВҰ161893 is the godВҰ161895вҖ”there'sВҰ161896 no \add other\add* besides \add >him\add*.
\v 61 And \add you people\add*, may yourВҰ161900 \add вүҲpurpose be to completelyВҰ161901 follow\add* ourВҰ161904 godВҰ161904 YahwehВҰ161903, by \add вүҲobeying\add* his statutesВҰ161906, andВҰ161907 by keepingВҰ161907 his commandsВҰ161908 \add вүҲlike you're doing today\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The temple dedication
\rem /s1 Solomon Offers Sacrifices; The Dedication of the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 7:4-10)
\p
\v 62 ThenВҰ161912 the kingВҰ161912 andВҰ161913 all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ161915 offered\add* sacrificesВҰ161917 to YahwehВҰ161920,
\v 63 and KingВҰ161943 Shelomoh sacrificedВҰ161925 peace offeringsВҰ161926 to Yahweh (twenty-two thousand cattleВҰ161930 and one hundredВҰ161935 and twenty thousand sheepВҰ161934) and the kingВҰ161943 and the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ161947\add* dedicatedВҰ161938 Yahweh's residence.
\v 64 On that dayВҰ161949 the king \add вүҲreserved\add* the middleВҰ161955 of the courtyardВҰ161956 that was \add вүҲin front of the temple\add*, because \add вүҲthat was where\add* he made the burnt up offerings and the grain offerings and the fat pieces of the peace offerings. \add This was\add* because the bronzeВҰ161978 altarВҰ161977 was too smallВҰ161982 to \add вүҲhandle all those offerings\add*.
\p
\v 65 ThenВҰ161994 Shelomoh andВҰ161994 \add вүҲIsraelis from all over the country\add* celebrated in frontВҰ162016 of YahwehВҰ162017 atВҰ161996 that timeвҖ”\add people\add* from Lebo-HamatВҰ162010 \add in the far north\add* \add вүҲdown to the Egyptian border\add* \add in the far south\add*вҖ”one week, thenВҰ161994 a second weekвҖ”\add a totalВҰ162003 of\add* fourteen days.
\v 66 The \add вүҲnext\add* dayВҰ162027, he \add вүҲinstructed\add* the people \add вүҲto go home\add*, and they blessedВҰ162033 the kingВҰ162036, then \add вүҲwent home feeling happy and encouraged\add* because of all the \add вүҲgood things\add* thatВҰ162046 YahwehВҰ162048 had done for his servantВҰ162050 David\add 's family\add* and for his people YisraelВҰ162051.
\c 9
\s1 Yahweh speaks to Shelomoh again
\rem /s1 God Appears Again to Solomon; The Lord's Response to Solomon; The reign of Solomon; God Appears to Solomon Again; The Lord Appears to Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 7:11-22)
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOnce\add* Shelomoh had finishedВҰ162055 the construction of the \add вүҲtemple and his palace, and various other projects of his\add*,
\v 2 YahwehВҰ162078 appeared a secondВҰ162082 time to \add *him\add*, \add вүҲsimilar to his appearance\add* atВҰ162086 GibeonВҰ162086\x + \xo 9:2: \xt 1Ki 3:5; 2Ch 1:7.\x*
\v 3 and saidВҰ162088, вҖңI've heardВҰ162091 your prayerВҰ162094 and your plea for favourВҰ162099 \add вүҲrequested from me\add*. I've \add вүҲdeclared that\add* this residence that you builtВҰ162107 \add вүҲis holy\add* by \add вүҲassociating my nameВҰ162110 with it forever\add*, and my eyes and my heart will \add вүҲconstantly\add* be there.\f + \fr 9:3 \ft вҖҳmy eyes and my heartвҖҷ: many translations have something like вҖҳmy presenceвҖҷ, but we've left it literal here for the reader to interpret rather than oversimplifying what we don't necessarily understand.\f*
\v 4 And as for you, if you'll \add вүҲbehave with godliness\add* just like your father DavidВҰ162130 \add вүҲlived with totalВҰ162137 dedication and honesty\add*, by \add вүҲfollowing everything\add* that I've commandedВҰ162139 you including keeping my statutesВҰ162140 and my judgements,
\v 5 thenВҰ162144 I'llВҰ162158 \add вүҲcontinue your dynasty over Yisrael forever\add*, just like I told your father DavidВҰ162157 when I said, вҖҳ\add вүҲyour descendants will never be removed\add* from Yisrael'sВҰ162151 throne.вҖҷ\x + \xo 9:5: \xt 1Ki 2:4.\x*
\v 6 IfВҰ162181 you or your descendants ever turn back from \add вүҲfollowingВҰ162175\add* me and don'tВҰ162176 keepВҰ162177 my commandsВҰ162178 and statutesВҰ162179, and you goВҰ162183 and serveВҰ162184 otherВҰ162186 godsВҰ162185 and bow down to them,
\v 7 thenВҰ162190 I'll cut Yisrael off from \add вүҲthe land\add* that I'veВҰ162198 givenВҰ162198 them and from the \add вүҲtemple that's dedicated to \add* my nameВҰ162205вҖ”I'll sendВҰ162206 \add >them\add* \add вүҲfar\add* away, and Yisrael will \add вүҲbecome an example and a laughing stock\add* among all the \add other\add* \add вүҲcountries\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲAs this temple is on a hill and very visible\add*, everyoneВҰ162221 who passesВҰ162223 \add anywhere\add* nearby \add will see it and\add* will be appalledВҰ162225 and will hiss and they'll sayВҰ162227, вҖҳ\add What did the people do\add* \add вүҲthat was so bad that\add* YahwehВҰ162232 did that to this country and to this temple?вҖҷ\x + \xo 9:8: \xt 2Ki 25:9; 2Ch 36:19.\x*
\v 9 ThenВҰ162239 they'll \add вүҲanswer\add*, вҖҳ\add It's\add* because they abandonedВҰ162242 their godВҰ162246 Yahweh who brought their ancestorsВҰ162251 out of EgyptВҰ162253, \add вүҲbutВҰ162239\add* they held onВҰ162255 to otherВҰ162256 godsВҰ162255 and bowed down to them and servedВҰ162261 them. Therefore Yahweh brought all this \add вүҲcalamity\add* onto them.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 King Hiram gains some poor cities
\rem /s1 Solomon's Agreement with Hiram; Solomon's Other Activities
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 8:1-2)
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲIt took\add* twentyВҰ162277 years for Shelomoh to construct \add вүҲthe temple for YahwehВҰ162290 and the palace for himself\add*.
\v 11 King HiramВҰ162316 from Tsor \add (TyreВҰ162299)\add*, had supportedВҰ162300 Shelomoh with cedarВҰ162305 and cypressВҰ162307 \add вүҲlogs\add*, and with goldВҰ162308вҖ”\add вүҲas much as he'd needed. So\add* King Shelomoh gaveВҰ162313 \add *him\add* twentyВҰ162317 cities inВҰ162304 the GalileeВҰ162320 \add вүҲregionВҰ162319\add*,
\v 12 \add вүҲbutВҰ162322 when\add* HiramВҰ162323 came \add вүҲdown\add* from Tsor to seeВҰ162325 the citiesВҰ162328 thatВҰ162329 Shelomoh had givenВҰ162330 him, \add вүҲhe wasn't very happy about them\add*
\v 13 and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңMy friend, what \add sort of\add* citiesВҰ162340 are theseВҰ162341 thatВҰ162342 you'veВҰ162344 givenВҰ162344 me?вҖқ and he called the area вҖҳKabulвҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳWorthlessвҖҷ), whichВҰ162342 it's still called\add* to this dayВҰ162352.
\v 14 HiramВҰ162357 \add had\add* sentВҰ162356 four tonnes of goldВҰ162362 to Shelomoh.
\s1 Shelomoh's other achievements
\rem /s1 Further Achievements of Solomon; Other Acts of Solomon; Solomon's Many Achievements
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 8:3-18)
\p
\v 15 Now this is the matter of the forcedВҰ162367 labourВҰ162367 thatВҰ162368 KingВҰ162372 Shelomoh brought up to buildВҰ162374 Yahweh's residence and his \add вүҲpalace\add*, the \add вүҲraisedВҰ162370 terraces\add* and the YerushalemВҰ162387 \add city\add* wall, and \add the cities of\add* Hatsor, MegiddoВҰ162393 and GezerВҰ162396.
\v 16 (Egypt'sВҰ162401 KingВҰ162399 Far-oh had seized GezerВҰ162406 and set fireВҰ162408 to it and killedВҰ162414 the CanaanitesВҰ162411 who had livedВҰ162412 inВҰ162408 the cityВҰ162413. Then he'd givenВҰ162415 it as a \add вүҲwedding present\add* to his daughterВҰ162417 \add вүҲwhen Shelomoh had married her\add*.)
\v 17 Shelomoh \add вүҲrebuilt\add* GezerВҰ162425 andВҰ162426 lowerВҰ162430 Beyt-HoronВҰ162429,
\v 18 Baalat, TadmorВҰ162437 inВҰ162439 the Yehudah wildernessВҰ162439,
\v 19 all of Shelomoh's storehouse cities, and the cities for his chariotsВҰ162452 and horses. They \add also\add* built whatever else Shelomoh wantedвҖ”in YerushalemВҰ162463, in LebanonВҰ162464, and in \add вүҲthe entireВҰ162443 area\add* of his dominionВҰ162467.
\v 20 All the \add вүҲremaining\add* AmoriteВҰ162475, HittiteВҰ162476, PerizziteВҰ162477, HiviteВҰ162478, andВҰ162479 Yebusite peopleВҰ162471 (theyВҰ162485 weren't descendants of YisraelВҰ162484),
\v 21 had descendants who continued living in YisraelВҰ162497. These were peopleВҰ162496 groups that the IsraelisВҰ162497 hadn't been able to annihilate so Shelomoh used them for forcedВҰ162501 labourВҰ162501 (\add where they remainВҰ162489\add* to this dayВҰ162505).
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ162508\add* \add *he\add* didn'tВҰ162510 \add вүҲconsign any IsraelisВҰ162509 to slavehoodВҰ162514\add*, because theyВҰ162517 were \add вүҲhis warriorsВҰ162518\add* and servantsВҰ162520, and his officers and captainsВҰ162522, and the commanders of his chariotsВҰ162524 and horsemen.
\v 23 \add вүҲSomeВҰ162536\add* were commanders of the fiveВҰ162538 hundredВҰ162539 andВҰ162538 fiftyВҰ162537 \add вүҲwork supervisors\add*.
\p
\v 24 Once Far-oh's daughterВҰ162546 moved out of the City of DavidВҰ162551 to \add вүҲthe palace\add* thatВҰ162555 he'd built for herВҰ162554, then he built the raised terraces.
\p
\v 25 Shelomoh offered burntВҰ162570 offerings and peace offerings threeВҰ162567 timesВҰ162568 that yearВҰ162569 onВҰ162569 the altarВҰ162574 that he'd builtВҰ162576 for Yahweh, and he burnt incenseВҰ162578 to Yahweh withВҰ162569 it, and he completedВҰ162584 the \add вүҲtemple\add*.\x + \xo 9:25: \xt Exo 23:17; 34:23; Deu 16:16.\x*
\rem /s1 Solomon's Commercial Activity
\p
\v 26 KingВҰ162591 Shelomoh constructed a fleetВҰ162589 \add of shipsВҰ162589\add* in EzionВҰ162593-Geber, whichВҰ162596 is near Eylot onВҰ162593 the shoreВҰ162602 of the Red Sea in the EdomВҰ162607 \add вүҲregionВҰ162606\add*.
\v 27 \add King\add* HiramВҰ162610 sent \add some of\add* his servants \add вүҲwho were experienced sailors to serve withВҰ162611 Shelomoh's menВҰ162615\add*.
\v 28 They \add вүҲsailed\add* to OfirВҰ162624 andВҰ162623 brought back fourteen tonnes of goldВҰ162627 that they tookВҰ162625 to Shelomoh.
\c 10
\s1 The queen from Sheva visits Shelomoh
\rem /s1 The Queen of Sheba Visits Solomon; The Queen of Sheba's Visit; The Visit of the Queen of Sheba; Visit of the Queen of Sheba
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 9:1-12)
\p
\v 1 Now the queenВҰ162640 from Sheva had heard a reportВҰ162646 \add вүҲabout how YahwehВҰ162649 had blessed\add* Shelomoh, and she cameВҰ162650 to test himВҰ162651 withВҰ162652 difficult questionsВҰ162652.\x + \xo 10:1-10: \xt Mat 12:42; Luk 11:31.\x*
\v 2 She came to YerushalemВҰ162655 withВҰ162656 \add вүҲlots of her top people\add*, camelsВҰ162659 carryingВҰ162660 spicesВҰ162661 and gemstones and a lot of goldВҰ162662. ThenВҰ162654 she wentВҰ162654 to Shelomoh and \add вүҲstarted asking him everything thatВҰ162660 had been onВҰ162656 her mind\add*.
\v 3 \add *He\add* \add вүҲansweredВҰ162683 all herВҰ162691 questionsВҰ162691вҖ”there wasn't any topic thatВҰ162700 he wasn't able to shed light on\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲWhenВҰ162705\add* the queenВҰ162706 from Sheva sawВҰ162705 \add вүҲthe extent\add* of Shelomoh's wisdomВҰ162712, the \add вүҲpalace\add* thatВҰ162715 he'd builtВҰ162716,
\v 5 the food onВҰ162735 his tableВҰ162719, the seatingВҰ162720 of his servantsВҰ162723, the uniforms and the service of his waiters, and the burntВҰ162727 offeringsВҰ162727 thatВҰ162728 he \add вүҲsacrificed\add* atВҰ162735 Yahweh'sВҰ162731 \add вүҲtemple\add*, \add вүҲshe was totally lost for words\add*.
\p
\v 6 She told the kingВҰ162742, вҖң\add Wow,\add* everything thatВҰ162746 I heardВҰ162747 about you \add back\add* inВҰ162748 my own country, andВҰ162739 about how wise you are, is true.
\v 7 I hadn't believedВҰ162758 it untilВҰ162760 I \add вүҲgot here\add* and saw it \add вүҲwith my own eyesВҰ162765, butВҰ162756 thenВҰ162756 I find thatВҰ162779 what I heard is only \em half\em* of how incredible it is\add*. Your wisdomВҰ162774 and your goodness is \add way\add* more than what I'd heard \add вүҲdescribed\add*.
\v 8 YourВҰ162791 menВҰ162783 \add вүҲare so fortunate\add* and \add especially\add* your servantsВҰ162785 who are always standingВҰ162787 in front of you and able to hearВҰ162790 \add вүҲthe wise things that you say\add*.
\v 9 May your godВҰ162797 Yahweh be blessedВҰ162798, who \add вүҲwas pleased withВҰ162801\add* you \add and\add* placed you onВҰ162801 Yisrael'sВҰ162806 throneВҰ162805. He \add вүҲappointed\add* you as kingВҰ162814 to \add вүҲrule them fairly and honestly\add* because Yahweh loves Yisrael forever.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ162819 \add @the queen\add* gave to king four tonnes of goldВҰ162825 and very many spices and preciousВҰ162830 \add #gemstones\add*. \add вүҲNever againВҰ162836 did KingВҰ162820 Shelomoh receive more spices than what the queen gave him\add* \add thatВҰ162838 day\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add KingВҰ162856\add* Hiram'sВҰ162849 fleet also \add вүҲbroughtВҰ162855\add* goldВҰ162853 from OfirВҰ162854 \add as well as\add* a lot of almugВҰ162858 wood andВҰ162861 preciousВҰ162862 \add #gemstones\add*.
\v 12 The king used the almug timber to make \add вүҲrailings\add*\f + \fr 10:12 \ft The exact meaning of this Hebrew word is unknown, especially as it's only used once. (Other possibilities for the use of this obviously high-quality timber includes вҖҳstepsвҖҷ or вҖҳpillarsвҖҷ.)\f* for \add вүҲthe temple\add* and \add вүҲthe palace\add*, and lyresВҰ162876 and harpsВҰ162877 for the \add вүҲmusicians\add*. Such \add вүҲa quantity and quality of almug wood has never again\add* been brought in or seen \add in Israel\add* to this dayВҰ162888.
\p
\v 13 Then KingВҰ162891 SolomonВҰ162892 gaveВҰ162893 the queenВҰ162894 from Sheva \add вүҲeverything she wanted\add*вҖ”whatever she requested \add вүҲon top of\add* what he \add вүҲhad already givenВҰ162906\add* to her. Then she departed with her servantsВҰ162916 andВҰ162891 returned to her country.
\s1 Shelomoh's wealth
\rem /s1 Solomon's Wealth and Splendour; King Solomon's Wealth; Solomon's Splendour
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 9:13-29)
\p
\v 14 The \add вүҲamount\add* of gold thatВҰ162922 came to Shelomoh inВҰ162926 one year was \add around\add* twenty-two tonnes,
\v 15 \add вүҲnot counting what came from explorers and tradersВҰ162937\add*, and all the Arab kingsВҰ162942, and the governorsВҰ162944 of the land.
\p
\v 16 KingВҰ162948 ShelomohВҰ162949 had two hundredВҰ162950 bodyВҰ162951 shields made from beatenВҰ162953 gold \add overlaid over wood\add*вҖ”each shield took six kilograms of gold.
\v 17 \add He also had\add* three hundredВҰ162966 \add smaller\add* shieldsВҰ162967 madeвҖ”each of them \add covered\add* with two kilograms of goldвҖ”andВҰ162964 placed in \add &his\add* вҖҳLebanonВҰ162982 Forest HallвҖҷ.
\p
\v 18 The kingВҰ162986 had a large ivoryВҰ162989 throneВҰ162987 made and overlaidВҰ162991 with pure goldВҰ162992.
\v 19 \add *It\add* had six stepsВҰ162996 \add вүҲgoing up to\add* \add *it\add* and \add вүҲthe seat-back was roundedВҰ163000 at the top\add*. \add вүҲIt had armrests on both sides, then a lion on each side next to the armrests\add*,
\v 20 plus twelve lionsВҰ163018 standingВҰ163019 one on each side of the sixВҰ163023 stepsВҰ163024. \add вүҲThere was nothing like itВҰ163029 in any other kingdomВҰ163033.\add*
\p
\v 21 All of Shelomoh's cups were gold, andВҰ163035 the \add вүҲvarious dishes\add* inВҰ163053 the вҖҳLebanonВҰ163046 Forest HallвҖҷ were \add also\add* pure gold. \add вүҲNothing was made out of silverВҰ163050 because it was considered to be of little value during Shelomoh's time\add*
\v 22 because the kingВҰ163060 had a fleet of ships that joined \add KingВҰ163060\add* Hiram'sВҰ163064 fleet. Every threeВҰ163066 yearsВҰ163067 the fleet would return bringing goldВҰ163073 and silverВҰ163074, ivory, monkeys and baboons.\f + \fr 10:22 \ft baboons: We're not certain of the meaning of this last word (some suggest вҖҳpeacocksвҖҷ), nor are we sure of the type of the ships named вҖҳTarshish shipsвҖҷ.\f*
\p
\v 23 KingВҰ163080 ShelomohВҰ163081 became \add вүҲricherВҰ163085 andВҰ163079 wiser\add* than \add вүҲany other kingВҰ163080 in the world\add*,
\v 24 andВҰ163088 \add even\add* \add вүҲpeople from distant countries would come to see\add* ShelomohВҰ163095 to listenВҰ163096 to the wisdomВҰ163099 thatВҰ163100 GodВҰ163103 had given \add вүҲhim\add*.
\v 25 Every \add вүҲvisitor\add* would bringВҰ163107 a gift: goldВҰ163113 containers, clothes, weaponsВҰ163115, spicesВҰ163116, horsesВҰ163117 andВҰ163106 mulesВҰ163118. \add вүҲThis continued year after year\add*.
\p
\v 26 Shelomoh \add вүҲacquired\add* 1,400 chariots and twelve thousand horsemenВҰ163128. He \add вүҲstationedВҰ163142\add* \add most of them\add* in his chariotВҰ163144 citiesВҰ163143 and \add some\add* withВҰ163143 \add *him\add* \add there\add* in YerushalemВҰ163148.\x + \xo 10:26: \xt 1Ki 4:26.\x*
\v 27 \add While he was\add* kingВҰ163151, silverВҰ163154 in YerushalemВҰ163155 \add вүҲwas given a value similar to\add* stonesВҰ163156, andВҰ163150 cedarВҰ163158 timber \add вүҲwas given a value like that of\add* the sycamoresВҰ163160 that \add вүҲgrow in plenty\add* in the lowlands.\x + \xo 10:27: \xt Deu 17:17.\x*
\v 28 Shelomoh \add вүҲacquired\add* horsesВҰ163167 from EgyptВҰ163170 andВҰ163171 from KueвҖ”\add вүҲhis tradersВҰ163172 would acquire them\add* from Kue for the kingВҰ163173 for a priceВҰ163176.\x + \xo 10:28: \xt Deu 17:16.\x*
\v 29 An Egyptian chariotВҰ163180 went for six hundred silverВҰ163184 coins and a horseВҰ163185 for one hundred and fiftyВҰ163186. ThenВҰ163178 \add вүҲthey'd export them again to the HittiteВҰ163192 and Aramean\add* kings.
\c 11
\s1 Shelomoh turns from God
\rem /s1 Solomon's Many Wives; Solomon's Errors; Solomon Turns Away from God; Solomon's Wives
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Now KingВҰ163199 Shelomoh lovedВҰ163201 many foreignВҰ163203 womenвҖ”besides Far-oh's daughterВҰ163207 \add there were\add* Moabite women, AmmoniteВҰ163211 women, Edomite women, SidonianВҰ163213 women, and HittiteВҰ163214 women.\x + \xo 11:1: \xt Neh 13:26; Deu 17:17.\x*
\v 2 \add They were\add* from the nations thatВҰ163219 YahwehВҰ163222 had told YisraelВҰ163226 about, вҖңYou must not \add вүҲmix with peopleВҰ163225 from\add* \add @those nations\add*, and they must not \add вүҲjoin together with\add* you. They will \add вүҲcertainly entice you to worship \add* theirВҰ163242 godsВҰ163242.вҖқ \add However,\add* Shelomoh clung to them for love.\x + \xo 11:2: \xt Exo 34:16; Deu 7:3-4.\x*
\v 3 \add вүҲHe had sevenВҰ163253 hundred wives who were kings' daughters, as well as\add* threeВҰ163256 hundred slave-wives, andВҰ163248 his wives \add вүҲwere instrumental in his turning away\add* \add from Yahweh\add*.
\v 4 By the time of his old age, Shelomoh's wivesВҰ163268 had \add вүҲpersuaded him to worship the godsВҰ163274 from their countries\add*вҖ”his heart wasn't \add вүҲtotally dedicated\add* to YahwehВҰ163283 like his fatherВҰ163287 DavidВҰ163286 had been.
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ163289\add* Shelomoh \add вүҲstarted to worship\add* the Tsidonians' God Ashtoret andВҰ163295 the Ammonites' detestableВҰ163297 God Milkom,
\v 6 \add вүҲso\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲdid many things that Yahweh had said were\add* evilВҰ163302вҖ”he didn'tВҰ163305 remain fully \add вүҲcommitted to\add* Yahweh like his fatherВҰ163310 DavidВҰ163309 had been.
\v 7 Then Shelomoh builtВҰ163314 a placeВҰ163316 to worship Kemosh, the Moabites detestable God, onВҰ163320 a hillВҰ163320 facing YerushalemВҰ163325, andВҰ163326 also for MolekВҰ163326, the Ammonites' detestable God.
\v 8 He did those things for his foreignВҰ163336 wivesВҰ163335 who were burning incense andВҰ163338 sacrificingВҰ163338 to theirВҰ163339 godsВҰ163339.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲAlthough Yisrael'sВҰ163351 godВҰ163350 Yahweh had appearedВҰ163352 twice to Shelomoh, he now turnedВҰ163346 his devotion away from Yahweh, who thenВҰ163341 became angryВҰ163341 withВҰ163343 him\add*.
\v 10 \add @Yahweh\add* had \add вүҲwarned\add* \add @Shelomoh\add* not to follow afterВҰ163365 otherВҰ163367 godsВҰ163366, butВҰ163356 he didn'tВҰ163362 \add вүҲobey\add* Yahweh'sВҰ163374 \add вүҲinstructionsВҰ163356\add*,
\v 11 and YahwehВҰ163378 told \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲYou have\add* this against you: you haven't kept my agreement and \add вүҲyou'veВҰ163387 disobeyed\add* my statutesВҰ163389 thatВҰ163390 I \add вүҲgave\add* you. \add So\add* I'llВҰ163394 definitely tear the kingdomВҰ163397 away from you and giveВҰ163399 it to your servantВҰ163400,
\v 12 except that for the sake of your father DavidВҰ163408 I won'tВҰ163405 do it inВҰ163404 your lifetimeВҰ163404, rather, I'llВҰ163409 tear the kingdom away from your son.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhat's more,\add* I won'tВҰ163420 tear the whole kingdomВҰ163419 awayвҖ”I'llВҰ163421 leave one tribeВҰ163422 for yourВҰ163425 son \add to rule\add* for my servantВҰ163428 David'sВҰ163427 sake, andВҰ163429 for the sake of my chosenВҰ163432 city YerushalemВҰ163430.вҖқ
\s1 Shelomoh's enemies
\rem /s1 Solomon's Enemies; Adversaries of Solomon; Solomon's Adversaries
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ163434 YahwehВҰ163435 \add вүҲcaused\add* HadadВҰ163439 the Edomite (andВҰ163434 a descendant of the Edomite kingВҰ163442) \add вүҲto stand\add* againstВҰ163437 Shelomoh.
\v 15 \add In the past\add* \add вүҲwhen\add* DavidВҰ163448 had been in Edom withВҰ163447 \add &his\add* army commanderВҰ163454 YoavВҰ163453 to buryВҰ163456 their deadВҰ163459, they had killed everyВҰ163461 maleВҰ163463 in Edom.
\v 16 (YoavВҰ163472 andВҰ163473 \add вүҲthe Israeli warriors\add* had had to stay thereВҰ163471 for sixВҰ163467 monthsВҰ163468 to kill the Edomite males.)
\v 17 \add вүҲHowever,\add* HadadВҰ163485 had been a small child at that time, andВҰ163484 \add *he'd\add* fled to EgyptВҰ163493 with some of his father'sВҰ163490 Edomite servantsВҰ163489.
\v 18 They'd \add вүҲpassed through Midyan and thenВҰ163498 ParanВҰ163501 where they'd gained some more menВҰ163503 before entering EgyptВҰ163507 where KingВҰ163511 Far-oh gave him a houseВҰ163517 and land, and provided him with food\add*.
\v 19 Far-oh \add вүҲtook a liking to\add* HadadВҰ163526 andВҰ163525 gave him his wife Queen Tahpenes' sister \add вүҲto marry\add*.
\v 20 Tahpenes' sisterВҰ163545 \add вүҲgave birthВҰ163543\add* to his son Genubath, his son, andВҰ163543 Tahpenes weanedВҰ163550 him in the midst of the house of Pharaoh. And Genubath was in the house of Pharaoh in the midst of the sons of Pharaoh.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ163563\add* Hadad inВҰ163565 EgyptВҰ163565 heardВҰ163564 that \add both\add* DavidВҰ163569 and \add &his\add* army commanderВҰ163577 YoavВҰ163576 had diedВҰ163575, Hadad saidВҰ163580 to PharaohВҰ163584, вҖң\add вүҲGive me permission to leave\add*, and I'll goВҰ163586 \add back\add* to my land.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲBut\add* Far-oh \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңBut \add вүҲwhat's wrong with staying here? You've stunned me by asking\add* to go to your land.вҖқ
\p вҖңNothing's \add lackingВҰ163598 here\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңbutВҰ163591 \add I have to go\add*вҖ”\add вүҲplease give me permission to leave\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 GodВҰ163614 \add also\add* \add вүҲcaused Elyada's son RezonВҰ163619 to stand against\add* \add @Shelomoh\add*. He'd run away from his masterВҰ163630, KingВҰ163627 HadadezerВҰ163626 in Tsovah,
\v 24 thenВҰ163632 he'd gatheredВҰ163632 menВҰ163634 for himself and had become a commander of a raiding band. WhenВҰ163632 DavidВҰ163640 \add вүҲattacked\add* them, theyВҰ163644 wentВҰ163642 to Dammesek \add (DamascusВҰ163643)\add*. They livedВҰ163644 there and \add вүҲgained control of\add* \add *the city\add*.
\v 25 ThenВҰ163649 during all of Shelomoh's reign, he'd been \add вүҲoutspoken\add* against IsraelВҰ163651вҖ”\add encouraged by\add* the evil thatВҰ163659 HadadВҰ163660 did. He reigned over \add SyriaВҰ163666\add* (AramВҰ163666) andВҰ163649 he \add вүҲloathedВҰ163661\add* YisraelВҰ163651.
\s1 God's promise to Yarave'am/Jeroboam
\rem /s1 Jeroboam's Rebellion; God's Promise to Jeroboam; Jeroboam Rebels against Solomon; Jeroboam Rebels Against Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 26 Nebat'sВҰ163672 son Yarave'amВҰ163669 \add (Jeroboam)\add*, an Efratite from TseredahВҰ163676 \add also\add* \add вүҲrebelled against the kingВҰ163686\add*. (His widowedВҰ163681 motherВҰ163678 TseruahВҰ163679 was one of Shelomoh's servantsВҰ163682.)
\v 27 \add вүҲThis is the background about how it started\add*: Shelomoh had builtВҰ163696 the raisedВҰ163692 terrace andВҰ163688 had \add вүҲrepaired a gap inВҰ163694 the wall\add* of the cityВҰ163704 of DavidВҰ163705 his fatherВҰ163706.
\v 28 Shelomoh \add вүҲhad noticedВҰ163712 Yarave'amВҰ163709 as a strong and hard-working\add* youngВҰ163716 man, \add вүҲso\add* he'd appointedВҰ163722 him \add вүҲas supervisor over all the forcedВҰ163726 labourВҰ163726 from Menashsheh and Efrayim's regions\add*.
\v 29 \add вүҲOne timeВҰ163732 when\add* Yarave'amВҰ163734 \add вүҲwas away\add* from YerushalemВҰ163736, the prophetВҰ163741 Ahiyyah the ShiloniteВҰ163740 met him onВҰ163732 the roadВҰ163742. He was \add вүҲwearing a brand-new\add* a new cloakВҰ163745, and \add вүҲthere was\add* \add just\add* the twoВҰ163747 by themselvesВҰ163748 inВҰ163732 the countrysideВҰ163749.
\v 30 AhiyyahВҰ163752 thenВҰ163751 pulled the new cloakВҰ163753 off \add his shoulders\add* andВҰ163751 tore it into twelve piecesВҰ163760,
\v 31 and told Yarave'am, вҖңTake ten piecesВҰ163768 for yourself, because this is what Yisrael'sВҰ163774 godВҰ163773 YahwehВҰ163772 saysВҰ163771, вҖҳListen, I'm aboutВҰ163776 to tear the kingdomВҰ163779 away from Shelomoh's \add вүҲcontrol\add*, and I'll giveВҰ163782 the\f + \fr 11:31 \ft Most English translations leave out this вҖҳtheвҖҷ (which is in the Hebrew). However, we suspect that both Ahiyyah and Yarave'am knew exactly which of the ten tribes it would be.\f* ten tribes to you.
\v 32 The one tribe\f + \fr 11:32 \ft It would have been obvious at the time that this was referring to Yehudah. (The unmentioned twelfth tribe is BenyaminвҖ”the youngest brother and the smallest tribe.)\f* will be for him, for the sake of my servantВҰ163795 DavidВҰ163796 and for the sake of YerushalemВҰ163798 cityВҰ163799 whichВҰ163800 I'veВҰ163801 chosenВҰ163801 from all the tribes of YisraelВҰ163805.
\v 33 \add This is\add* because they've abandonedВҰ163810 me. \add вүҲInstead\add* they've bowed down to the Tsidonians' God AshtoretВҰ163812, to the Moabite god Kemosh, and to the Ammonite God Milkom. They're \add no longer\add* \add вүҲfollowing my instructions or doingВҰ163827 what they know I've said is rightВҰ163828\add*вҖ”not \add obeying\add* my statutesВҰ163830 or my judgementsВҰ163831 like the king's fatherВҰ163833 DavidВҰ163832 did.
\v 34 ButВҰ163835 I won'tВҰ163835 takeВҰ163837 the \add вүҲentireВҰ163840\add* kingdomВҰ163842 \add вүҲoff him\add*, butВҰ163835 rather I'llВҰ163837 \add вүҲleave\add* him as a leader \add вүҲwhile he's still alive\add* for the sake of my chosenВҰ163855 servantВҰ163853 DavidВҰ163852, who \add вүҲobeyed\add* my commandsВҰ163859 andВҰ163835 my statutesВҰ163860.
\v 35 \add вүҲHowever,\add* I'll takeВҰ163862 the kingship \add вүҲaway from\add* his son andВҰ163862 I'll giveВҰ163866 the tenВҰ163869 tribesВҰ163870 to youВҰ163867 \add to rule\add*.
\v 36 I'llВҰ163873 giveВҰ163873 \add @Shelomoh\add*'s son one tribeВҰ163874 to rule so thatВҰ163891 \add вүҲone of David'sВҰ163881 descendants will always rule\add* inВҰ163889 my chosenВҰ163892 cityВҰ163890 YerushalemВҰ163889 \add вүҲbecause it's associated withВҰ163889 my nameВҰ163895\add*.
\v 37 \add вүҲButВҰ163898\add* I'llВҰ163899 \add вүҲuse\add* you, andВҰ163898 you'll be able to reignВҰ163900 over \add вүҲthe area where you want to rule\add*вҖ”you'll become kingВҰ163907 over YisraelВҰ163910.
\v 38 ThenВҰ163912 if you'll \add вүҲlistenВҰ163915 to everything\add* that I commandВҰ163921 you, and walkВҰ163922 \add вүҲonВҰ163923 the rightВҰ163925 path and do what pleases me and\add* keep my statutesВҰ163928 and my commandsВҰ163929, just like my servantВҰ163933 David did, thenВҰ163912 I'll be withВҰ163923 you. I'll \add вүҲestablish a dynasty\add* for you just \add вүҲlike I did\add* for David, and I'll giveВҰ163944 YisraelВҰ163948 to you.
\v 39 I'll make David'sВҰ163954 \add вүҲdescendants suffer because\add* of \add @Shelomoh's behaviour\add*, butВҰ163950 not forever.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 40 Shelomoh \add вүҲtried to killВҰ163966\add* Yarave'amВҰ163971, \add вүҲbutВҰ163964\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲleft the area\add* and fled to Egypt. \add вүҲHe remained inВҰ163981 Egypt under the protection\add* of KingВҰ163977 ShishakВҰ163976 untilВҰ163982 Shelomoh's deathВҰ163984.
\s1 Shelomoh's death
\rem /s1 The Death of Solomon; Solomon's Death
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 9:29-31)
\p
\v 41 A record of all the other things that Shelomoh did, andВҰ163987 all the wise things that he said, was writtenВҰ163998 in the вҖҳRecord of Shelomoh's AchievementsвҖҷ.
\v 42 ShelomohВҰ164008 reignedВҰ164007 over all YisraelВҰ164014 from YerushalemВҰ164009 for fortyВҰ164015 years,
\v 43 thenВҰ164018 he \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ164023 inВҰ164024 the City of DavidВҰ164025, and his son Rehavam (RehoboamВҰ164028) becameВҰ164027 kingВҰ164027.
\c 12
\s1 The north rejects Rehavam (Rehoboam)
\rem /s1 The kingdom divided; Israel Rebels Against Rehoboam; The Northern Tribes Revolt; The Northern Tribes Secede
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (2 Chr. 10:1-19)
\p
\v 1 \add Shelomoh's son\add* Rehavam wentВҰ164033 to ShekemВҰ164035, because all YisraelВҰ164041 had \add вүҲassembled there to make him kingВҰ164042\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Nebat'sВҰ164051 son Yarave'amВҰ164048 \add (Jeroboam)\add* inВҰ164054 EgyptВҰ164054 (whereВҰ164055 he'd fled from KingВҰ164058 Shelomoh) heardВҰ164046 the news andВҰ164045 returned to Yisrael.
\v 3 \add The leaders of the northern tribes\add* summoned him, andВҰ164064 theyВҰ164075 all wentВҰ164068 to \add вүҲpetition\add* \add King\add* Rehavam,
\v 4 вҖңYour father \add Shelomoh\add* \add вүҲrequired us to contribute too much labour\add*. If you'll lightenВҰ164088 the burden on us, then we'll serveВҰ164098 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲCome back in\add* threeВҰ164104 daysВҰ164105,вҖқ he replied, вҖңandВҰ164100 \add вүҲI'll give my response\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ164100 the peopleВҰ164109 left.
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ164111 KingВҰ164112 Rehavam consultedВҰ164111 withВҰ164126 the eldersВҰ164116 (who'd \add вүҲserved\add* his fatherВҰ164125 Shelomoh while he was aliveВҰ164127), asking them for advice onВҰ164126 how to respond.
\p
\v 7 вҖңIf you \add вүҲwant to serve these peopleВҰ164152 well\add*,вҖқ they repliedВҰ164140, вҖңanswerВҰ164155 them \add вүҲwith kindness now\add* thenВҰ164140 they'll \add вүҲserve you well in the future\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ164168 he decided to ignore that advice from\add* the eldersВҰ164171, and he consultedВҰ164174 with the young men who were standing \add вүҲin front of him\add* and that he'd grownВҰ164179 up with,
\v 9 \add вүҲso\add* he \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңWhatВҰ164207 \add вүҲwould you all recommend that we tell the peopleВҰ164194 who wanted me to lightenВҰ164200 the burden that my father placed on them\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңYou should tell \add *them\add* this,вҖқ \add вүҲhis young companions replied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲThey've asked that you should lightenВҰ164232 the load on them from what your father demanded, butВҰ164210 on the contrary, you should tell them that your littleВҰ164237 fingerВҰ164237 is thickerВҰ164238 than your father's thigh bone was\add*.
\v 11 \add Tell them that\add* your father placed a heavyВҰ164247 burden onВҰ164256 them, \add вүҲbut that\add* you'll add to \add *that\add*. \add *He\add* punished them with whipsВҰ164256, \add вүҲbut\add* you'll punish them with scorpionsВҰ164260.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ164262 when\add* Yarave'amВҰ164264 andВҰ164262 all the \add вүҲleaders\add* came \add back\add* to \add KingВҰ164275\add* RehavamВҰ164270 on the third day as \add *he'd\add* \add вүҲinstructed them\add*,
\v 13 he answeredВҰ164282 \add *them\add* harshlyвҖ”ignoring the advice of the eldersВҰ164292 \add at the beginning\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲInstead\add* he spokeВҰ164296 to them accordingВҰ164298 to the adviceВҰ164298 of the young men, saying, вҖңMy father \add вүҲplaced a heavyВҰ164302 burden onВҰ164314 you all, but\add* as for me, I'll add \add вүҲto those demands\add*. My father punished you all with whipsВҰ164314, but as for me, I'll punish you all with scorpionsВҰ164318.вҖқ
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ164320\add* the kingВҰ164323 didn'tВҰ164320 listenВҰ164322 to the peopleВҰ164326. This change came from YahwehВҰ164332 so thatВҰ164338 what he'd had Ahiyyah the ShiloniteВҰ164343 tell Nebat'sВҰ164349 son Yarave'amВҰ164346 would \add all indeed\add* \add вүҲhappen\add*.\x + \xo 12:15: \xt 1Ki 11:29-39.\x*
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲWhenВҰ164351\add* all YisraelВҰ164354 saw that the king hadn't listenedВҰ164358 to them, the peopleВҰ164362 \add вүҲresponded\add*,
\q1 вҖңWhat \add вүҲshare inВҰ164373\add* DavidВҰ164373 \add вүҲdo we have\add*?
\q1 вүҲ\add вүҲWe won'tВҰ164356 get any inheritanceВҰ164376 from\add* Yishay'sВҰ164379 \add (Jesse's)\add* son.
\q1 \add Go back\add* to your tents, Yisrael.
\q1 \add вүҲLook atВҰ164373 your dynasty\add* now, David.вҖқ\x + \xo 12:16: \xt 2Sam 20:1.\x*
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ164351\add* the \add northern\add* \add вүҲIsraeli leaders\add* went \add вүҲhome\add* \add again\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲHowever,\add* Rehavam continued to rule over the citiesВҰ164393 inВҰ164393 YehudahВҰ164394.
\p
\v 18 Then KingВҰ164401 Rehavam \add вүҲtook\add* Adoniram who was over the forcedВҰ164409 labourВҰ164409, \add вүҲto go\add* \add north\add* \add вүҲbutВҰ164400 the people killed him by throwing rocks atВҰ164421 him\add* and the king \add вүҲhad to hurriedly jump into\add* \add &his\add* chariotВҰ164421 to flee to YerushalemВҰ164423.
\v 19 \add вүҲEver since thenВҰ164425\add*, the \add northern tribes of\add* YisraelВҰ164426 have rebelledВҰ164425 against David'sВҰ164428 \add вүҲdynasty\add*.
\rem /s1 First Dynasty: Jeroboam Reigns over Israel
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSo\add* as soon as all Yisrael heardВҰ164435 that Yarave'amВҰ164442 had returnedВҰ164441 \add from Egypt\add*, they \add вүҲsummoned him to their assemblyВҰ164448 and appointed him as kingВҰ164449\add* over all \add northern\add* Yisrael. Only \add вүҲthe YehudahВҰ164465 region was left under the rule of David'sВҰ164461 grandson\add* \add Rehavam\add*.
\s1 Shemayah's prophecy
\rem /s1 Shemaiah's Prophecy
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 11:1-4)
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ164468 when\add* Shelomoh's son Rehavam \add (RehoboamВҰ164470)\add* \add вүҲreturned to\add* YerushalemВҰ164471, he assembledВҰ164472 all the \add вүҲtribes\add* of YehudahВҰ164478 and BenyaminВҰ164482, and 180,000 \add warriors\add* were chosenВҰ164486 to fightВҰ164489 against the \add вүҲnorthern tribes\add* to return the kingship to \add *him\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ164512\add* GodВҰ164506 \add вүҲtold the prophet\add* ShemayahВҰ164509,
\v 23 вҖң\add Go and\add* tell Shelomoh's son Rehavam, the kingВҰ164522 of Yehudah, and \add вүЎtell\add* all the \add вүҲdescendants of\add* Yehudah and BenyaminВҰ164530, and the remainder of the peopleВҰ164532, saying,
\v 24 вҖҳYahweh says this: Don't go and fightВҰ164544 againstВҰ164564 your \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ164548 relatives\add*. \add вүҲEveryone should just returnВҰ164551 home because everything that happened there was initiated\add* by me.вҖҷ вҖқ \add вүҲWhen\add* they heard Yahweh's messageВҰ164562, \add вүҲthey took note of it and everyoneВҰ164548 went back home\add*.
\s1 Yarave'am (Jeroboam) makes gold calves
\rem /s1 Jeroboam Turns Away from God; Golden Calves at Beyt-El and Dan; Jeroboam's Golden Calves; Jeroboam Makes Gold Calves
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 25 Then Yarave'amВҰ164571 built ShekemВҰ164574 inВҰ164575 the hill countryВҰ164575 of EfrayimВҰ164576 and he lived \add вүҲthere\add* \add for a while\add*. Then he \add вүҲleft\add* there and built PenuelВҰ164584.
\v 26 \add вүҲAfterВҰ164587 that,\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲworried that the entire country might want to go back under David'sВҰ164593 dynasty\add*.
\v 27 \add вүЎHe worried that\add* if the people went \add вүҲdown\add* to YerushalemВҰ164606 to offer sacrificesВҰ164602 in Yahweh's temple, they \add вүҲmight shift theirВҰ164613 allegiance\add* to KingВҰ164617 Rehavam in YehudahВҰ164626 and then \add вүҲhis life might be in danger\add*.
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ164628 after getting advice,\add* the kingВҰ164629 made twoВҰ164631 goldВҰ164633 calvesВҰ164632, andВҰ164628 he toldВҰ164634 \add @his people\add*, вҖңGoing \add all the way\add* \add вүҲdown\add* to YerushalemВҰ164640 is too \add вүҲfar\add* for you. Look, \add these can be\add* your godsВҰ164642, YisraelВҰ164643, who broughtВҰ164645 you out from EgyptВҰ164647.вҖқ\x + \xo 12:28: \xt Exo 32:4.\x*
\v 29 He set one up at Beyt-El \add (in the south)\add* andВҰ164656 the other one at DanВҰ164660 \add (in the north)\add*.
\v 30 This caused the people to sin, andВҰ164662 \add some\add* people went up as far as the one in DanВҰ164672.
\v 31 HeВҰ164675 built \add вүҲtemples on hills\add* andВҰ164679 appointed priestsВҰ164680 from \add вүҲvarious tribes\add*вҖ”not just from the \add вүҲtribe\add* of LeviВҰ164688.
\s1 The warning of worshipping there at Beyt-El
\rem /s1 Worship at Bethel Is Condemned
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 32 In the eighthВҰ164695 month on the 15th, Yarave'amВҰ164691 \add вүҲput on a celebration\add* like the one inВҰ164694 YehudahВҰ164705. \add He'd made\add* an altar atВҰ164694 Beyt-El and he got the priestsВҰ164725 from the \add вүҲhill temples\add* he'd made to come and stand there, thenВҰ164690 he offered a sacrificeВҰ164715 on that altar to the calvesВҰ164716 that he'd made.\x + \xo 12:32-33: \xt Lev 23:33-34.\x*
\v 33 \add вүҲThat date of\add* the 15th dayВҰ164743 of the eighthВҰ164745 month \add вүҲwas one thatВҰ164735 he'd just decided for himself\add*, and he \add вүҲinstituted\add* a \add new\add* \add вүҲcelebration\add* for the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ164755\add* and he \add вүҲburnt incenseВҰ164760\add* onВҰ164741 the altar \add as a sacrifice\add*.
\c 13
\rem /s1 The Man of God From Judah; A Man of God from Judah; A Prophet Denounces Jeroboam
\p
\v 1 Then a \add вүҲprophet from\add* of GodВҰ164766 cameВҰ164767 from YehudahВҰ164768, \add taking\add* Yahweh's messageВҰ164769 to Beyt-El. as Yarave'amВҰ164776 \add (Jeroboam)\add* was standingВҰ164777 by the altarВҰ164780 to burn incenseВҰ164781.
\v 2 \add @The prophet\add* calledВҰ164783 out against the altar withВҰ164787 Yahweh's messageВҰ164787: вҖңAltar! Altar! Yahweh saysВҰ164793 this: Listen, \add one of\add* \add вүҲDavid'sВҰ164801 descendants\add* will have a son \add вүҲwho'll be named\add* Yoshiyyah \add (Josiah)\add*, andВҰ164783 he'll sacrificeВҰ164804 the priestsВҰ164808 \add вүҲfrom the hill temples\add* on youвҖ”the ones who are burning incenseВҰ164810 on you. \add Yes,\add* humanВҰ164813 bonesВҰ164812 will be burnt on you.вҖқ\x + \xo 13:2: \xt 2Ki 23:15-16.\x*
\v 3 ThenВҰ164817 he \add вүҲoffered them evidence that what he said came from\add* YahwehВҰ164826, вҖңListen, that altarВҰ164828 will be \add вүҲbroken\add* into pieces, andВҰ164817 the ashesВҰ164831 in it will \add вүҲspill all over the ground\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲThe moment\add* the KingВҰ164838 Yarave'amВҰ164854 heardВҰ164837 the messageВҰ164841 that the man of GodВҰ164844 had called out against the altar at Beyt-El, \add вүҲhe called for the man to be arrested\add*. \add вүҲHowever,\add* the arm that he used to point to him over the altar \add вүҲsuddenly became paralysed\add* andВҰ164836 he wasn't able to \add вүҲpull it back\add*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ164873 the altar \add itself\add* \add вүҲbroke open\add* andВҰ164875 ashesВҰ164876 pouredВҰ164875 out \add onto the ground\add*, \add вүҲexactly as YahwehВҰ164886 had promised through thatВҰ164881\add* manВҰ164883 of GodВҰ164884.
\v 6 ThenВҰ164888 the king \add вүҲbegged the prophet\add*, вҖңPlease, \add вүҲpray to your godВҰ164903 Yahweh\add* for me, so my hand \add вүҲwill return to normal\add*.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ164888\add* the man of GodВҰ164903 \add вүҲinterceded withВҰ164923\add* Yahweh, andВҰ164888 the king \add вүҲwas able to use his hand again\add*.
\v 7 вҖңCome \add вүҲhomeВҰ164934 with me\add*,вҖқ the kingВҰ164926 \add вүҲtold the prophet\add*, вҖңandВҰ164925 \add вүҲhave something to eat\add*. ThenВҰ164925 \add вүҲI've got\add* a giftВҰ164938 to giveВҰ164936 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ164940\add* the manВҰ164941 of GodВҰ164943 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add Even\add* if you \add вүҲoffered\add* me half of your houseВҰ164955, I wouldn't goВҰ164957 withВҰ164967 you, andВҰ164940 I \add вүҲwouldn't eatВҰ164961 or drinkВҰ164964\add* inВҰ164967 this placeВҰ164967.
\v 9 YahwehВҰ164977 already told me not to eatВҰ164981 or drinkВҰ164984 \add here\add*, and not to returnВҰ164988 home \add вүҲby the same road IВҰ164975 came onВҰ164976\add*.вҖқ
\v 10 ThenВҰ164993 he \add left for home\add* \add вүҲtaking a different route from the one he'd used\add* to comeВҰ165001 to Beyt-ElВҰ165005.
\s1 The old prophet from Beyt-El
\rem /s1 The Old Prophet of Bethel
\s4 Both kingdoms
\p
\v 11 Now \add at that time there was\add* an old prophetВҰ165010 who lived in Beyt-El, and his sons\f + \fr 13:11 \ft This is singular in the Hebrew, but the rest of this segment suggests multiple sons.\f* had been and told him all the news about what that manВҰ165030 of GodВҰ165032 had done that dayВҰ165034 in Beyt-El and they told him the messageВҰ165040 that \add вүҲhad been passed on\add* to the kingВҰ165045.
\v 12 вҖң\add Oh,\add* \add вүҲwhat road did he take when he left\add*?вҖқ theirВҰ165051 fatherВҰ165051 \add вүҲasked\add*, andВҰ165049 \add indeed\add* his sonsВҰ165058 had \add вүҲnoticedВҰ165057 whichВҰ165062 road the manВҰ165064 of GodВҰ165065 from YehudahВҰ165069 had taken\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ165071\add* he told his sons to saddleВҰ165075 his donkey, andВҰ165071 he rode \add off\add*
\v 14 afterВҰ165087 the man of God, andВҰ165086 foundВҰ165090 him sittingВҰ165091 underВҰ165092 an oak tree. вҖңAre you the man of God,вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңwho came from YehudahВҰ165103?вҖқ
\p вҖңI am,вҖқ he said.
\p
\v 15 вҖң\add вүҲCome homeВҰ165111 with me andВҰ165112 have something to eatВҰ165112\add*.вҖқ he \add вүҲinvited\add* him.
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add Sorry,\add*вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңI \add вүҲcan't goВҰ165120 with you or visit your home\add*, andВҰ165115 I \add вүҲcan't eatВҰ165124 or drinkВҰ165128\add* with you inВҰ165131 this placeВҰ165131,
\v 17 because YahwehВҰ165139 \add вүҲinstructed\add* me \add вүҲnot to eatВҰ165142 or drinkВҰ165146 here, or to goВҰ165152 home by the same road thatВҰ165154 I came onВҰ165138\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ165159 \add @the old prophet\add* told himВҰ165172, вҖңI'm also a prophet like you, and YahwehВҰ165170 sent a messengerВҰ165169 to tell me \add вүҲthat I should take you home withВҰ165169 me so you can have something to eatВҰ165177 and drinkВҰ165179\add*.вҖқ (\add вүҲButВҰ165159 that was a lie\add*.)
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ165184\add* \add @the prophet\add* \add вүҲaccompanied him to his houseВҰ165188 andВҰ165184 had a meal there\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ165192 while theyВҰ165193 were \add вүҲstill\add* seated at the tableВҰ165197, YahwehВҰ165202 spoke through the \add вүҲold prophetВҰ165205\add*,
\v 21 and he calledВҰ165209 out to the manВҰ165212 of GodВҰ165235 who'd comeВҰ165216 from YehudahВҰ165217, вҖңYahweh saysВҰ165220 this: Because you have been rebelliousВҰ165224 againstВҰ165224 Yahweh and \add вүҲbecauseВҰ165222 you didn'tВҰ165227 obey what Yahweh instructedВҰ165233\add* you
\v 22 and you've returnedВҰ165237 and you've \add вүҲhad food and drink\add* in the placeВҰ165242 where he told you \add вүҲnot to eat or drink\add*, your \add вүҲbodyВҰ165257 won'tВҰ165246 be buried in your home town\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 After \add вүҲthe meal was finished\add*, \add @the old prophet\add* saddledВҰ165269 the donkeyВҰ165272 for the prophet that he'd broughtВҰ165275 back,
\v 24 and he left. \add вүҲButВҰ165277\add* on the road, a lion \add вүҲcame across him\add* and killedВҰ165281 him. His corpse \add вүҲended up\add* lying on the road withВҰ165280 the donkeyВҰ165286 standing beside it, and the lion also standing beside \add *it\add*.
\v 25 \add вүҲSome passers-by\add* sawВҰ165297 the corpse onВҰ165302 the roadВҰ165302 and \add the unusual sight of\add* the lionВҰ165305 standingВҰ165306 besideВҰ165307 \add *it\add*, and \add вүҲwhen they got to\add* the cityВҰ165311 where the old prophetВҰ165313 lived, they \add вүҲtold everyone the news\add*.
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲWhenВҰ165318\add* the prophetВҰ165319 who had broughtВҰ165321 him back from the road heard he said, вҖң\add вүҲThat will be\add* the manВҰ165326 of GodВҰ165327 who was rebelliousВҰ165330 againstВҰ165330 Yahweh. Yahweh \add вүҲmust have givenВҰ165335\add* him to the lionВҰ165337, and it tore him into pieces and put him to death accordingВҰ165340 what Yahweh \add вүҲhad said would happen\add*.вҖқ
\v 27 ThenВҰ165347 he told his sonsВҰ165350, вҖңSaddle the donkeyВҰ165357 for me.вҖқ They \add вүҲput the saddleВҰ165352 on\add*,
\v 28 and he went and foundВҰ165361 the body lying onВҰ165366 the road, and the donkey and the lion standingВҰ165369 by \add *it\add*. The lion hadn't eatenВҰ165374 any of the man of God's body, nor had it attacked the donkey.
\v 29 TheВҰ165387 prophet lifted the body and \add вүҲlaid it across\add* the donkeyВҰ165396 and broughtВҰ165397 it back to his cityВҰ165401 to be buried in his own tomb.
\v 30 They wailed over him, saying, вҖңOh dear, my brotherВҰ165415,вҖқ andВҰ165412 they laid his bodyВҰ165410 inВҰ165411 \add @the old prophet's\add* graveВҰ165411.
\v 31 \add вүҲWhen the period of mourning was over,\add* he told his sonsВҰ165424, вҖңWhen I die, bury me inВҰ165426 the graveВҰ165429 where the manВҰ165431 of GodВҰ165432 is buried. \add вүҲMy bones will end up\add* besideВҰ165435 his bones.
\v 32 The messageВҰ165445 from YahwehВҰ165449 thatВҰ165446 he shouted out against the altarВҰ165452 in Beyt-El will certainlyВҰ165443 happen, and against all the \add вүҲhilltop worship\add* placesВҰ165461 in ShomronВҰ165464 \add (Samaria)\add*.
\s1 Yarave'am's fatal sin
\rem /s1 Jeroboam's Fatal Sin
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 33 \add вүҲDespite\add* \add @the man of God's warning\add*, \add King\add* Yarave'amВҰ165473 didn'tВҰ165470 \add вүҲstop his evil ways\add*вҖ”\add in fact\add* he \add вүҲchose more peopleВҰ165479 from across the country to become\add* priests. \add вүҲAnyone who wantedВҰ165482 to be a priest would be appointed\add* and he would become one of the priests of the \add вүҲhilltop worship\add* places.
\v 34 \add вүҲThose were the sins of Yarave'amВҰ165496 that would eventually lead to the rejection andВҰ165491 destructionВҰ165498 of his entire family\add*.
\c 14
\s1 The death of Yarave'am's son
\rem /s1 Judgment on the House of Jeroboam; The Death of Jeroboam's Son; Ahijah's Prophecy Against Jeroboam; Ahijah's Prophecy against Jeroboam
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 At that timeВҰ165504, \add one of\add* Yarave'am's sons, Aviyyah, becameВҰ165506 very sickВҰ165506
\v 2 and Yarave'amВҰ165513 told his wife, вҖң\add вүҲGo and get changed so that no one will recognise you as\add* \add *my\add* wife. ThenВҰ165512 go to ShilohВҰ165527 where the prophet Ahiyyah isвҖ”he's \add вүҲthe one who prophesied that I'd becomeВҰ165537 kingВҰ165537\add*.
\v 3 Take tenВҰ165545 loaves of breadВҰ165546 and \add some\add* cakesВҰ165547 and a jar of honeyВҰ165549 to give to him. He'll tell youВҰ165544 what will happenВҰ165557 to the boyВҰ165558.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ165560\add* \add *his\add* wifeВҰ165562 \add вүҲgot ready\add* and wentВҰ165565 to Ahiyyah's houseВҰ165568 at ShilohВҰ165566. Ahiyyah was \add вүҲnow very elderly and\add* not able to seeВҰ165574,
\v 5 \add вүҲbutВҰ165581\add* Yahweh had told \add *him\add*, вҖңListen, Yarave'am's wifeВҰ165587 will be coming to \add вүҲask for your guidance\add* aboutВҰ165589 her son, because he's sickВҰ165598. \add вүҲI want you to tell her so-and-so. And when she comes, she won't be dressed like a queen\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ165609\add* as soon as Ahiyyah heardВҰ165610 herВҰ165615 \add вүҲwalk through the doorway\add*, he saidВҰ165618, вҖңCome inВҰ165617, wifeВҰ165620 of Yarave'amВҰ165621. Why \add вүҲdid you get changed like that\add*? Now I'veВҰ165626 been \add вүҲinstructed to pass bad newsВҰ165629 onto\add* youвҖ”
\v 7 go \add back\add* and \add вүҲgive Yarave'amВҰ165633 this message from\add* Yisrael'sВҰ165639 godВҰ165638 YahwehВҰ165637, вҖҳI \add вүҲchose you out from\add* the people and \add вүҲplaced\add* you as a leader over my people Yisrael,
\v 8 and I tore the kingdomВҰ165654 away from \add вүҲDavid'sВҰ165656 descendants\add* and gaveВҰ165657 it to you. \add вүҲButВҰ165651\add* you haven't been like my servantВҰ165662 David who \add вүҲobeyed my instructions and followed me withВҰ165677 integrityвҖ”only doingВҰ165674 what he knew thatВҰ165667 I approved of\add*.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add* you'veВҰ165695 done more evilВҰ165679 \add things\add* than any of thoseВҰ165682 who \add вүҲruled before you\add*. You've \add вүҲrejected me\add* and made cast imagesВҰ165692 of otherВҰ165691 godsВҰ165690, and have provokedВҰ165693 me into angerВҰ165693.
\v 10 \add вүҲBecause of that\add*, I'm aboutВҰ165702 to bringВҰ165702 calamityВҰ165703 to \add *your\add* \add вүҲfamily\add*: I'll \add вүҲcause all your male descendants to die, either before or after they've left home\add*. I'll \add вүҲeliminate your family\add* just like \add dried\add* dung burns untilВҰ165723 it's \add вүҲall gone\add*.\x + \xo 14:10: \xt 1Ki 15:29.\x*
\v 11 The \add family members\add* who die in the cityВҰ165729 will be eaten by dogs, andВҰ165732 those who die in the countrysideВҰ165733 will be eaten by birds. \add All this\add* \add вүҲcomes from\add* YahwehВҰ165738.вҖҷ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ165741 goВҰ165743 back home\add*, \add butВҰ165741\add* \add вүҲas soon as youВҰ165741 set foot inВҰ165745\add* the cityВҰ165747, your son will dieВҰ165748.
\v 13 All Yisrael will \add вүҲmournВҰ165751\add* for him andВҰ165757 they'll buryВҰ165757 him. \add вүҲHe'll be the only one of your children to be buried\add*, becauseВҰ165768 \add вүҲout of all of Yarave'am's descendants, he's the only one that\add* Yisrael'sВҰ165756 godВҰ165777 YahwehВҰ165776 foundВҰ165769 goodВҰ165773 in.
\v 14 \add вүҲIn the future,\add* YahwehВҰ165783 will \add вүҲappoint\add* for himself, a kingВҰ165785 over YisraelВҰ165788 who will \add вүҲget rid of Yarave'am's descendants\add*вҖ”\add in fact\add* \add вүҲit's beginning to come about\add* even now.
\v 15 And Yahweh will strikeВҰ165802 Yisrael just like the \add #reeds\add* \add вүҲbend over inВҰ165810 the swamps\add*, and he'll uprootВҰ165811 Yisrael from this goodВҰ165817 soil thatВҰ165819 he gaveВҰ165820 to their ancestorsВҰ165821 and he'll scatterВҰ165822 them beyondВҰ165823 the Euphrates, becauseВҰ165825 they made their Asherah \add statues\add* whichВҰ165819 provokedВҰ165831 Yahweh to angerВҰ165831.
\v 16 He will hand Yisrael over \add to their enemies\add* because of Yarave'am's sinsВҰ165841 andВҰ165836 \add how\add* he \add вүҲencouraged\add* Yisrael to sinВҰ165846.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ165851\add* Yarave'am's wifeВҰ165852 \add вүҲleft andВҰ165851 wentВҰ165855 home\add* to Tirtsah. \add вүҲAs sheВҰ165857 entered the doorway of their home, their son\add* diedВҰ165863.
\v 18 \add вүҲJustВҰ165866 as YahwehВҰ165874 had told them\add*, all YisraelВҰ165872 mournedВҰ165867 for the boy andВҰ165865 he was buriedВҰ165865.
\s1 Yarave'am's death
\rem /s1 Death of Jeroboam; The Death of Jeroboam
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲEverything else that Yarave'amВҰ165885 did, including the record of wars that his army fought andВҰ165883 how he ruled, is writtenВҰ165891 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ165897 of YisraelВҰ165898.
\v 20 Yarave'amВҰ165903 reignedВҰ165902 for twenty-two years, thenВҰ165900 he \add вүҲdied and was buried with his ancestorsВҰ165910\add*, and his son NadavВҰ165912 \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ165911\add*.
\s1 Rehavam (Rehoboam) rules in Yehudah
\rem /s1 Rehoboam Rules in Judah; Rehoboam King of Judah; Rehoboam Reigns over Judah; King Rehoboam of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 11:5вҖ“12:15)
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Shelomoh's son Rehavam reigned inВҰ165922 YehudahВҰ165922. He was forty-one when he \add started\add* reigning, and he reigned for seventeenВҰ165930 years from YerushalemВҰ165935вҖ”the cityВҰ165936 that YahwehВҰ165940 had chosenВҰ165939 \add вүҲto associate his name withВҰ165922\add* out of all the tribesВҰ165947 of YisraelВҰ165948. \add @Rehavam's\add* motherВҰ165950 was NaamahВҰ165951 the AmmoniteВҰ165952.
\p
\v 22 \add TheВҰ165960 people of\add* YehudahВҰ165955 did what YahwehВҰ165958 \add вүҲhad decided was\add* evilВҰ165956вҖ”\add inВҰ165965 fact\add* they made him more jealousВҰ165959 \add (by worshipping other gods)\add* than their ancestorsВҰ165964 \add вүҲever had\add*.
\v 23 They even builtВҰ165969 \add вүҲhilltop temples\add* and sacred pillarsВҰ165975 and polesВҰ165976 on every high hill and underВҰ165982 every \add вүҲlarge evergreen\add* treeВҰ165985.\x + \xo 14:23: \xt 2Ki 17:9-10.\x*
\v 24 There were also maleВҰ165990 prostitutesВҰ165990 \add вүҲassociated with them\add*, andВҰ165988 \add @the IsraelisВҰ166002\add* did the same abhorrent things as the nationsВҰ165996 thatВҰ165997 YahwehВҰ165999 had removed ahead of \add their entering the land\add*.\x + \xo 14:24: \xt Deu 23:17.\x*
\p
\v 25 In the fifthВҰ166007 yearВҰ166006 of King Rehavam's \add reign\add*, Egypt'sВҰ166015 King ShishakВҰ166011 \add вүҲattacked\add* YerushalemВҰ166018\x + \xo 14:25: \xt 2Ch 12:2-8.\x*
\v 26 and took away the valuables from Yahweh's temple, and the king's palace. He took everythingВҰ166034 \add of value\add*, including all the goldВҰ166042 shieldsВҰ166041 thatВҰ166043 Shelomoh had made.\x + \xo 14:26: \xt 1Ki 10:16-17; 2Ch 9:15-16.\x*
\v 27 \add вүҲTo replaceВҰ166050 them,\add* KingВҰ166048 Rehavam made \add some\add* bronzeВҰ166052 shieldsВҰ166051 andВҰ166047 \add вүҲassigned them to the officers who protect the entranceВҰ166060 to the palace\add*.
\v 28 \add вүҲWheneverВҰ166070\add* the kingВҰ166068 would enter the \add вүҲtemple, the guardsВҰ166072 would quickly take the shields there, andВҰ166064 when he left, they'd run them back to the palace\add*.
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲEverything else that Rehavam did is writtenВҰ166089 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ166095 of YehudahВҰ166096.
\v 30 RehavamВҰ166102 andВҰ166103 Yarave'amВҰ166104 \add вүҲwere in a continual state of war\add* \add during their reigns\add*.
\v 31 ThenВҰ166109 Rehavam (his motherВҰ166121 was NaamahВҰ166122 the AmmoniteВҰ166123) \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ166114 withВҰ166118 his ancestorsВҰ166113 inВҰ166118 the City of DavidВҰ166119, and his son Abiyyam \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ166124\add*.
\c 15
\s1 Abiyyam rules over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Abijam Reigns over Judah: Idolatry and War; King Abijah of Judah; Abijam Rules in Judah; Abijah King of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 13:1вҖ“14:1)
\p
\v 1 In the eighteenthВҰ166131 year of (Nabat's son) KingВҰ166133 Yarave'am's \add reign over Israel\add*, Abiyyam \add вүҲbecameВҰ166138 king of YehudahВҰ166142\add*.
\v 2 (His mother'sВҰ166149 nameВҰ166148 was Maakah, \add one of\add* Abishalom'sВҰ166153 daughtersВҰ166151.) He reignedВҰ166146 from YerushalemВҰ166147 for three yearsВҰ166145
\v 3 \add вүҲbutВҰ166155\add* he \add вүҲdisobeyed GodВҰ166172 in ways similar to\add* his fatherвҖ”\add вүҲhe wasn't interested in following his god YahwehВҰ166171 completelyВҰ166168 like his ancestor DavidВҰ166174 had done\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ166194\add* for David'sВҰ166179 sake, his godВҰ166182 YahwehВҰ166181 gaveВҰ166180 \add *Abiyyam\add* a son \add to rule\add* afterВҰ166190 himВҰ166190вҖ”to \add вүҲallow YerushalemВҰ166185 to continue onВҰ166185 withВҰ166185 a flicker of light\add*\x + \xo 15:4: \xt 1Ki 11:36.\x*
\v 5 because DavidВҰ166198 had done \add вүҲwhat Yahweh had said was correct, and throughout his lifeВҰ166213 he hadn't deviated from what Yahweh had instructedВҰ166210 him\add*, except inВҰ166215 the matterВҰ166215 concerning Uriyyah the HittiteВҰ166217.\x + \xo 15:5: \xt 2Sam 11:1-27.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲRehavam's andВҰ166224 Yarave'am's factions were in a continual state of war\add* \add during Abiyyam's reign\add*.\x + \xo 15:6: \xt 2Ch 13:3-21.\x*
\v 7 \add вүҲEverything else that Abiyyam did is writtenВҰ166241 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ166247 of YehudahВҰ166248, \add вүҲas the war between Abiyyam andВҰ166231 Yarave'amВҰ166254 continued\add*.
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ166256 Abiyyam \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ166261 withВҰ166263 his ancestorsВҰ166260 inВҰ166263 the City of DavidВҰ166264, and his son AsaВҰ166266 \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ166265\add*.
\s1 Asa's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Asa Reigns over Judah; Asa King of Judah; King Asa of Judah; Asa Rules in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 14:1-5; 15:16вҖ“16:6, 11-14)
\p
\v 9 In the twentiethВҰ166272 year of KingВҰ166274 Yarave'am's \add reign over\add* YisraelВҰ166275, AsaВҰ166277 \add вүҲbecameВҰ166276 king of YehudahВҰ166279\add*
\v 10 andВҰ166281 reignedВҰ166284 from YerushalemВҰ166285 for forty-one years. (His grandmother was Abishalom'sВҰ166291 daughterВҰ166289 Maakah.)
\v 11 AsaВҰ166294 did \add вүҲwhat was pleasing to\add* YahwehВҰ166297, like his ancestor DavidВҰ166298 \add had done\add*,
\v 12 and he \add вүҲexpelled the maleВҰ166302 prostitutesВҰ166302 from the country\add* and removedВҰ166306 all the idolsВҰ166311 \add вүҲmade by the previous generations\add*.\x + \xo 15:12: \xt 2Ch 15:8-15.\x*
\v 13 He also removedВҰ166322 his grandmother Maakah from being queen-mother because sheВҰ166326 had made a horrid Asherah \add вүҲgoddess\add*, thenВҰ166316 \add *he\add* cut down herВҰ166333 horrid \add вүҲidol\add* andВҰ166316 burnt it inВҰ166335 the KidronВҰ166336 \add вүҲvalley\add*.
\v 14 HeВҰ166345 didn'tВҰ166339 removeВҰ166341 the \add вүҲhilltop temples\add*, \add butВҰ166338 despite that\add* \add вүҲhe was fully devoted to\add* YahwehВҰ166350 all \add вүҲhis life\add*.
\v 15 He broughtВҰ166355 \add вүҲeverything that fatherВҰ166359 had dedicated, plus more of his own, into Yahweh's temple\add*, \add including\add* goldВҰ166365, silverВҰ166364, andВҰ166355 containers.
\rem /s1 Alliance with Aram against Israel
\p
\v 16 AsaВҰ166371 andВҰ166372 KingВҰ166374 BaashaВҰ166373 of YisraelВҰ166376 \add вүҲwere in a continual state of war during theirВҰ166379 reigns\add*.
\v 17 King BaashaВҰ166382 invaded Yehudah andВҰ166381 \add вүҲfortified\add* RamahВҰ166392 \add вүҲso that no one could pass in or out to help\add* King AsaВҰ166397 of Yehudah.
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ166401\add* AsaВҰ166402 tookВҰ166401 all the remaining goldВҰ166408 and silverВҰ166407 from the \add вүҲtemple and palace\add* storerooms, and \add вүҲsentВҰ166425 it withВҰ166411\add* his servantsВҰ166424 \add вүҲto take\add* to BenВҰ166430-HadadВҰ166432, son of TabrimmonВҰ166435, son of KingВҰ166426 HezionВҰ166438 of AramВҰ166440 who livedВҰ166441 inВҰ166411 DamascusВҰ166442, \add вүҲto tell him\add*,
\v 19 вҖң\add вүҲYou and me have an agreement between us that was made by our two fathersВҰ166449\add*, so look, I've sent a present of goldВҰ166457 and silverВҰ166456 to youВҰ166447. \add вүҲSo then,\add* breakВҰ166459 yourВҰ166462 agreement with KingВҰ166466 BaashaВҰ166465 of YisraelВҰ166468 \add вүҲso he'll give up on attacking\add* me.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 BenВҰ166473-HadadВҰ166475 \add вүҲdid what kingВҰ166478 AsaВҰ166479 requested\add*, and he sentВҰ166480 the commandersВҰ166483 of \add вүҲhis best warriors\add* to attack IsraeliВҰ166490 citiesВҰ166490 \add вүҲincluding\add* IyonВҰ166495, DanВҰ166498, Avel-Beyt-Maakah, and all Kinnerot along with all NaftaliВҰ166512 \add вүҲregionВҰ166511\add*.
\v 21 WhenВҰ166514 \add King\add* BaashaВҰ166516 heardВҰ166515 \add >about that\add*, he stoppedВҰ166517 \add вүҲfortifying\add* RamahВҰ166521 andВҰ166514 \add вүҲwithdrew\add* to Tirtsah.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ166525 KingВҰ166525 Asa \add вүҲinformed\add* all YehudahВҰ166532 \add вүҲthatВҰ166543 they were needed atВҰ166547\add* RamahВҰ166539. They removed the stonesВҰ166538 and timberВҰ166542 from Baasha'sВҰ166545 \add вүҲfortifications\add*, and king Asa used \add @the materials\add* to build GebaВҰ166552 (inВҰ166547 BenyaminВҰ166553) and Mitspah.
\v 23 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ166572 AsaВҰ166563 did\add*, and all his great works and all the citiesВҰ166571 he builtВҰ166573, \add вүҲare described\add* in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kingsВҰ166583 of YehudahВҰ166584. \add вүҲHowever\add* in his old age, he \add вүҲdeveloped problems\add* with his feetВҰ166591.
\v 24 ThenВҰ166593 he \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ166598 withВҰ166602 his ancestorsВҰ166601 inВҰ166602 the CityВҰ166594 of DavidВҰ166603 (also his ancestor) and his son YehoshafatВҰ166606 \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ166605\add*.
\s1 Nadav's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Nadab King of Israel; King Nadab of Israel; Nadab Rules in Israel; Nadab Reigns over Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 25 In the second year of Asa'sВҰ166621 \add вүҲreign over YehudahВҰ166623\add*, Yarave'am's son Nadav becameВҰ166615 king of YisraelВҰ166618 where he reigned for two yearsВҰ166628.
\v 26 HeВҰ166640 did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ166633 had said was\add* evil, \add вүҲfollowing his father'sВҰ166636 behaviour\add* andВҰ166630 his sin thatВҰ166638 \add inВҰ166635 turn\add*, causedВҰ166639 YisraelВҰ166642 to sin.
\p
\v 27 \add A man named\add* BaashaВҰ166646 (from the Yissakar tribe) plotted against \add @King Nadav\add* and \add вүҲkilled himВҰ166652 atВҰ166654 the Philistine city of GibbetonВҰ166654\add* when Nadav and all YisraelВҰ166660 were besieging \add *the city\add*.
\v 28 It was the third yearВҰ166668 of \add King\add* Asa'sВҰ166670 reignВҰ166673 in YehudahВҰ166672 when Baasha killedВҰ166666 \add @King Nadav\add*, thenВҰ166666 Baasha \add вүҲtook over as\add* kingВҰ166671 \add of Israel\add*.
\v 29 As soon as he \add вүҲtook over\add*, he \add вүҲhad Yarave'am's entireВҰ166681 family executedвҖ”not leaving a single one of them alive. This fulfilled what YahwehВҰ166696 had said through\add* his servantВҰ166701 Ahiyyah the ShiloniteВҰ166703,\x + \xo 15:29: \xt 1Ki 14:10.\x*
\v 30 because Yarave'am's \add own\add* sinsВҰ166707, as well as his causing YisraelВҰ166715 to sinВҰ166712, had provokedВҰ166718 YahwehВҰ166721 into getting angry.
\p
\v 31 \add вүҲEverything else that Nadav did is writtenВҰ166735 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ166741 of YisraelВҰ166742.
\rem /s1 Baasha Rules in Israel
\v 32 \add King\add* AsaВҰ166747 andВҰ166748 King BaashaВҰ166749 of YisraelВҰ166752 \add вүҲwere in a continual state of war during theirВҰ166755 reigns\add*.
\s1 Baasha's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Second Dynasty: Baasha Reigns over Israel; King Baasha of Israel; Baasha King of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 33 Ahiyyah's son BaashaВҰ166764 \add began\add* to reign over YisraelВҰ166772 inВҰ166773 the third yearВҰ166758 of KingВҰ166761 Asa'sВҰ166760 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ166762, and he ruled from Tirtsah for twenty-four years.
\v 34 He did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ166781 had said was\add* evil, \add вүҲsimilar to Nabat's son Yarave'am's behaviour\add* andВҰ166778 his sin thatВҰ166786 \add inВҰ166783 turn\add*, causedВҰ166787 YisraelВҰ166790 to sin.
\c 16
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ166796 \add вүҲtold Hanani'sВҰ166802 son YehuВҰ166799 to tell\add* BaashaВҰ166805,
\v 2 вҖңI \add вүҲtook a nobody and promoted you to\add* leader over my people Yisrael, \add вүҲyet\add* you \add вүҲfollowed Yarave'am's behaviour\add* and provokedВҰ166828 me to angerВҰ166828 by causing my people Yisrael to sin,
\v 3 \add вүҲso now I'll get rid of you and yourВҰ166840 familyвҖ”I'll do the same to you that I did to Yarave'amВҰ166842 and his family\add*.
\v 4 \add TheВҰ166848 bodies of\add* \add вүҲthose in your family who die in the cityВҰ166849 will be eaten by dogs, andВҰ166852 those who die in the countrysideВҰ166854 will be eaten by vultures\add*.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ166862 BaashaВҰ166861 did is writtenВҰ166868 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ166874 of YisraelВҰ166875.
\v 6 \add вүҲWhenВҰ166877 BaashaВҰ166878 died\add* he was buriedВҰ166882 inВҰ166883 TirtsahВҰ166883, andВҰ166877 his son ElahВҰ166885 \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ166884\add*.
\p
\v 7 Yahweh \add вүҲsent that messageВҰ166897 via HananiВҰ166895 the prophet'sВҰ166896 son YehuВҰ166892. It was for Baasha andВҰ166889 his familyвҖ”speaking againstВҰ166901 the evilВҰ166910 that they'd done that had provokedВҰ166918 Yahweh to get angry with their behaviour whichВҰ166912 was as bad as Yarave'am's family had been. Yahweh was also angry with Baasha because he had killed all of Yarave'am's family\add*.
\s1 Elah's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Elah Rules in Israel; Elah King of Israel; Elah Reigns over Israel; King Elah of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 8 Baasha'sВҰ166942 son ElahВҰ166939 \add began\add* to reign inВҰ166946 the twenty-sixth year of KingВҰ166936 Asa'sВҰ166935 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ166937, and he ruled from Tirtsah for two yearsВҰ166947.
\v 9 \add вүҲHowever,\add* his servantВҰ166951 ZimriВҰ166952 who was the commanderВҰ166953 of half of the chariotsВҰ166955 conspiredВҰ166949 against him. \add вүҲOnce when\add* \add @Elah\add* was in Tirtsah \add вүҲgetting\add* himself drunkВҰ166959 atВҰ166957 the houseВҰ166960 of ArzaВҰ166961 (who was \add вүҲin charge of the palaceВҰ166965\add*),
\v 10 ZimriВҰ166969 wentВҰ166968 in and \add вүҲattacked and killedВҰ166971\add* him, and \add вүҲtook over his placeВҰ166979 as king\add*. (That was in the twenty-seventh year of KingВҰ166976 Asa'sВҰ166975 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ166977.)
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲAs soon as Zimri took over andВҰ166981\add* sat onВҰ166982 his throneВҰ166986, he \add вүҲhad all of Baasha'sВҰ166993 family executedвҖ”he didn'tВҰ166994 leave a single male\add* or relative or friendВҰ167001.
\v 12 \add InВҰ167016 thatВҰ167012 way,\add* ZimriВҰ167004 \add вүҲeliminated all of Baasha'sВҰ167009 descendants just as YahwehВҰ167011 had said via\add* the prophetВҰ167019 YehuВҰ167018
\v 13 concerning all of Baasha'sВҰ167025 sins and the sins of his son ElahВҰ167027, and because they causedВҰ167032 Yisrael to sin by provokingВҰ167036 Yisrael'sВҰ167035 godВҰ167040 YahwehВҰ167039 to get angry withВҰ167042 theirВҰ167042 idolsВҰ167042.
\v 14 \add вүҲEverything else that ElahВҰ167046 did is writtenВҰ167054 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ167060 of YisraelВҰ167061.
\s1 Zimri's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 King Zimri of Israel; Zimri King of Israel; Third Dynasty: Zimri Reigns over Israel; Zimri Rules in Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 15 ZimriВҰ167072 reigned from Tirtsah for seven daysВҰ167074 inВҰ167075 the twenty-seventh year of KingВҰ167069 Asa'sВҰ167068 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ167070. \add At the time,\add* \add вүҲthe Israeli army were besieging the Philistine city of\add* GibbetonВҰ167080,
\v 16 and \add вүҲwhen the army\add* camped \add around the city\add* heard \add вүҲthat ZimriВҰ167089 had rebelled and assassinated\add* the king, that dayВҰ167108 all the people inВҰ167110 the camp \add вүҲinstalled\add* the army commanderВҰ167102 OmriВҰ167107 \add as king\add* to reign over YisraelВҰ167098.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ167112\add* OmriВҰ167113 \add вүҲtook all his warriors\add* from GibbetonВҰ167118 andВҰ167112 besiegedВҰ167119 Tirtsah.
\v 18 \add вүҲAsВҰ167140 soon as\add* ZimriВҰ167126 \add вүҲrealisedВҰ167125 that the cityВҰ167130 was surrounded\add*, he wentВҰ167131 into the \add вүҲsaferoom in the palace\add* and \add вүҲset fireВҰ167145 to the building and diedВҰ167146 in the flames\add*
\v 19 because \add вүҲhe'd done what YahwehВҰ167157 had said was evilвҖ”following Yarave'am'sВҰ167160 behaviour including\add* causing YisraelВҰ167167 to sin.
\v 20 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ167173 ZimriВҰ167171 did, including his rebellion, is writtenВҰ167178 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ167184 of YisraelВҰ167185.
\s1 Omri's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Fourth Dynasty: Omri Reigns over Israel; Omri King of Israel; Omri Rules in Israel; King Omri of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲAt that time,\add* the people of YisraelВҰ167191 were dividedВҰ167189 \add вүҲconcerning their leadership\add*вҖ”half of \add *them\add* \add вүҲsupported\add* Ginnat'sВҰ167200 son Tivni \add вүҲas kingВҰ167201\add*, and the other half \add вүҲsupported\add* OmriВҰ167204,
\v 22 \add вүҲbutВҰ167206\add* those \add вүҲsupporting Omri prevailed, so Tivni was executed\add* andВҰ167206 Omri \add remained\add* \add вүҲin power\add*.
\v 23 OmriВҰ167234 \add вүҲbecameВҰ167233 king\add* inВҰ167241 the thirty-first years of KingВҰ167231 Asa'sВҰ167230 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ167232, and reigned over YisraelВҰ167237 for twelve yearsвҖ”six of them from TirtsahВҰ167241.
\rem /s1 Samaria the New Capital
\v 24 He boughtВҰ167247 a hill from \add a man named\add* Shemer for seventy kilograms of silverВҰ167255, thenВҰ167247 built \add his capital\add* cityВҰ167264 onВҰ167254 it. He named it Shomron \add (SamariaВҰ167251)\add* \add вүҲinВҰ167254 honour of Shemer who'd owned\add* the hill.
\p
\v 25 OmriВҰ167276 did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ167279 had said was\add* evilвҖ”\add in fact\add* he did more evil things than all thoseВҰ167282 \add kings\add* who \add вүҲpreceded\add* him.
\v 26 He \add вүҲfollowed (Nabat's son) Yarave'am's behaviour including\add* causing Yisrael to sinВҰ167296 by provokingВҰ167300 Yisrael'sВҰ167299 godВҰ167304 YahwehВҰ167303 to get angry withВҰ167293 theirВҰ167306 idolsВҰ167306.
\v 27 \add вүҲEverything else thatВҰ167312 OmriВҰ167311 did, including his military victories, is writtenВҰ167320 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ167326 of YisraelВҰ167327.
\v 28 ThenВҰ167329 OmriВҰ167330 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buriedВҰ167334 inВҰ167335 ShomronВҰ167335, and his son Ahav \add (AhabВҰ167337)\add* \add вүҲreplaced him as kingВҰ167336\add*.
\s1 Ahav's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Ahab Becomes King of Israel; Ahab and Elijah; Ahab Rules in Israel; King Ahab of Israel; Ahab Reigns over Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 29 Omri'sВҰ167345 son Ahav \add вүҲbecameВҰ167346 king of IsraelВҰ167349\add* inВҰ167365 the thirty-eighth year of KingВҰ167346 Ahab'sВҰ167342 \add reign\add* over YehudahВҰ167356, and he reigned YisraelВҰ167349 from ShomronВҰ167365 for twenty-two years.
\v 30 Ahav did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ167377 had said was\add* evilвҖ”\add in fact\add* he did more evil things than all thoseВҰ167379 \add kings\add* who \add вүҲpreceded\add* him.
\rem /s1 Ahab Marries Jezebel and Worships Baal
\v 31 \add вүҲAs if following Yarave'am's behaviour wasn't bad enough, he married\add* Izevel \add (Jezebel)\add*, the daughterВҰ167395 of the Sidonian KingВҰ167398 EtbaalВҰ167397, thenВҰ167382 wentВҰ167400 and servedВҰ167401 BaalВҰ167404 and bowed down to him.
\v 32 HeВҰ167412 \add вүҲbuiltВҰ167414 a temple for BaalВҰ167410 in ShomronВҰ167415 andВҰ167408 placed an altarВҰ167409 in it\add*.
\v 33 Ahav \add also\add* made an Asherah pole andВҰ167422 went on to provokeВҰ167425 Yisrael'sВҰ167430 godВҰ167429 YahwehВҰ167428 to get angry, more than any of the \add вүҲprevious\add* kingsВҰ167432 of Yisrael \add had done\add*.
\v 34 \add вүҲDuring his reign\add*, HielВҰ167440 from Beyt-El \add вүҲrebuiltВҰ167439 Yeriko city. As they laid the foundationsВҰ167448, his eldest son Aviram died, and when they hung the city gatesВҰ167453\add*, his youngestВҰ167451 son Seguv died, just as YahwehВҰ167455 had told (Nun'sВҰ167462 son) Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add*.\x + \xo 16:34: \xt Josh 6:26.\x*
\c 17
\s1 Eliyah prophesies about a coming drought
\rem /s1 Elijah Fed by Ravens; Elijah and the Drought; Elijah Predicts a Drought
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add One day the prophet\add* Eliyah \add (ElijahВҰ167466)\add* from the TishbitesВҰ167467 in the GileadВҰ167469 region saidВҰ167465 to Ahav, вҖңAs Yisrael'sВҰ167477 godВҰ167476 YahwehВҰ167475 \add вүҲlives, the one who I serve\add*, there won't be any rain or \add even\add* dew theseВҰ167485 \add next\add* yearsВҰ167484 unless \add вүҲI give the command\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 17:1: \xt Jam 5:17.\x*
\v 2 Then YahwehВҰ167498 \add вүҲtold\add* \add @Eliyah\add*,
\v 3 вҖң\add вүҲGet away from here and travel\add* eastward \add вүҲtowards the KeritВҰ167509 stream thatВҰ167510 enters\add* the YordanВҰ167514 \add river\add* \add вүҲto hide\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲYou'll be able\add* to drinkВҰ167518 from the stream, andВҰ167516 I'veВҰ167522 commandedВҰ167522 the ravensВҰ167521 to \add вүҲbring food to\add* you thereВҰ167524.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ167526 he did what YahwehВҰ167529 told him, and went and lived by the KeritВҰ167533 stream near\add* the YordanВҰ167538.
\v 6 Ravens brought bread and meat to him \add every\add* morningВҰ167545 and \add вүҲagain\add* inВҰ167545 the eveningВҰ167548, and he was able to drink from the stream.
\rem /s1 The Widow at Zarephath
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever, the stream driedВҰ167557 up after a while because there was no rain anywhere in the country\add*.
\s1 Eliyah and the widow at Tserefat
\rem /s1 The Widow at Zarephath; Elijah and the Widow in Zarephath; The Widow of Zarephath
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ167570 \add вүҲtold\add* \add @Eliyah\add*,
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲLeave here\add* \add and\add* goВҰ167575 to Tserefat in the Tsidon \add region\add* and stayВҰ167579 there. Listen, I'veВҰ167582 commandedВҰ167582 a widowВҰ167585 lady there \add вүҲto keep youВҰ167586 fed\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 17:9: \xt Luk 4:25-26.\x*
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ167588 he got ready\add* and wentВҰ167590 to Tserefat. \add вүҲAs he entered the townВҰ167596, he saw a womanВҰ167600 picking up bits of firewood, and he asked her, вҖңCan you pleaseВҰ167609 get me a drinkВҰ167615 of waterВҰ167613\add*.вҖқ
\v 11 As she went to get it, he calledВҰ167619 out, вҖң\add вүҲWould you have a pieceВҰ167626 of breadВҰ167628 to go withВҰ167629 it?\add*.вҖқ
