\v 18 вҖң\add вүҲIt's not me who brings troubleВҰ168211 onto\add* YisraelВҰ168214,вҖқ Eliyah \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңButВҰ168209 rather \add вүҲit's youВҰ168218 and your father's families who decided to ignore Yahweh's commandsВҰ168224 and serve the BaalsВҰ168228 instead\add*.
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ168230\add* now, \add вүҲget all YisraelВҰ168238 to go to\add* MtВҰ168241. KarmelВҰ168242, along with the 450 prophets of BaalВҰ168246 andВҰ168230 the 400 prophets of Asherah who \add Queen\add* Izevel \add вүҲfeeds at her\add* tableВҰ168255.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Elijah's Triumph over the Priests of Baal
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ168258\add* AhavВҰ168259 \add вүҲsummoned all the IsraelisВҰ168263 andВҰ168264 the prophetsВҰ168267 to go to\add* MtВҰ168270. KarmelВҰ168271,
\v 21 andВҰ168273 EliyahВҰ168274 \add вүҲaddressed the people\add*, вҖң\add вүҲHow much longer are you all going to remain unsure who to follow\add*? If YahwehВҰ168292 is GodВҰ168293, \add вүҲfollow\add* him, butВҰ168273 if it's BaalВҰ168298, \add вүҲfollow\add* him.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ168273\add* the people \add вүҲjust stayed silent\add*.
\v 22 ThenВҰ168308 \add *he\add* saidВҰ168308, вҖң\add вүҲI'm Yahweh's only remaining prophet\add*, butВҰ168308 Baal \add вүҲhas 450 prophets\add*.
\v 23 Let them \add вүҲget us\add* two bullsВҰ168330 and they can chooseВҰ168331 one for themselves. ThenВҰ168326 they can cut it into pieces and lay them a pile of wood that they've set for a fire, but they \add вүҲcan'tВҰ168341 light the\add* fire. \add вүҲI'llВҰ168344 do the same with the other bull, but also won'tВҰ168341 light the\add* fire.
\v 24 ThenВҰ168358 \add вүҲthey must call to their god and I'llВҰ168362 call to\add* YahwehВҰ168365, and the god who answers \add вүҲby setting the wood onВҰ168363 fireВҰ168371 must be the true\add* GodВҰ168360.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲIt sounds good to us\add*,вҖқ the peopleВҰ168377 answered.
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ168382\add* EliyahВҰ168383 told Baal'sВҰ168385 prophetsВҰ168384, вҖң\add Okay,\add* \add вүҲthere's a lot more of you guys, so you chooseВҰ168386 your bullВҰ168388 and go firstВҰ168391 and call out to your godВҰ168397, butВҰ168382 don'tВҰ168399 set fireВҰ168398 to the pile\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲSoВҰ168402\add* they took the bullВҰ168405 he gave them and \add вүҲpreparedВҰ168410 it all\add*, and thenВҰ168402 they calledВҰ168411 out to Baal from morningВҰ168415 until midday, \add вүҲshouting\add*, вҖңBaal, answer us!вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ168402 they didn't hear any voiceВҰ168423 and got no answer\add*. ThenВҰ168402 they \add вүҲhopped\add* around the altarВҰ168429 \add #they'd\add* made.
\p
\v 27 \add вүҲFinally\add* atВҰ168434 noon, EliyahВҰ168437 \add began\add* mocking them, saying, вҖң\add вүҲCall out louder\add* because he's a godВҰ168445. \add вүҲMaybe he's thinking about something else, or busy withВҰ168434 something, or travelling somewhere\add*. Pehaps he's asleep andВҰ168433 \add вүҲneeds waking\add* up.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ168462 they shouted even louder and did their usual cutting of their bodies withВҰ168463 knives and swordsВҰ168467 untilВҰ168469 a lot of bloodВҰ168473 flowed\add*.
\v 29 Midday passedВҰ168477 and they continued raving \add вүҲall afternoon, butВҰ168476\add* they \add вүҲdidn't hear any\add* voiceВҰ168485, and \add вүҲthey got no answerВҰ168488 or even any suggestion that their god was listening\add*.
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ168492 EliyahВҰ168493 told the people, вҖң\add Okay, now\add* come \add вүҲover here by\add* me.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ168492\add* all the people came \add вүҲover by\add* him, andВҰ168492 he repairedВҰ168504 the altarВҰ168507 of YahwehВҰ168508 that had been torn down.
\v 31 \add *He\add* tookВҰ168511 twelve stonesВҰ168515 (the numberВҰ168516 of the sonsВҰ168518 of Yakob \add (Jacob)\add* who \add вүҲYahwehВҰ168525 told would be called YisraelВҰ168528\add*)\x + \xo 18:31: \xt Gen 32:28; 35:10.\x*
\v 32 andВҰ168532 \add вүҲused them to rebuild\add* Yahweh'sВҰ168538 altar. ThenВҰ168532 \add aroundВҰ168544\add* the altar he made a trench \add вүҲlarge enough to hold the water to water in twoВҰ168542 drums\add* of seed.\f + \fr 18:32 \ft A more Jewish interpretation that seems to agree with v34вҖ“35вҖ”see https://hermeneutics.stackexchange.com/questions/31555/water-in-elijahs-trench.\f*
\v 33 He arrangedВҰ168547 the firewood, and cut the bullВҰ168554 into pieces and placed them on \add вүҲtop\add*,
\v 34 and thenВҰ168560 \add вүҲordered\add*, вҖңFill four jars with waterВҰ168564 and pour it on the burntВҰ168568 offeringВҰ168568 and the firewood.вҖқ ThenВҰ168560 he said вҖң\add Now\add* do it a second time,вҖқ and they did it a second time, and \add againВҰ168574\add* he said, вҖңDo it a third time,вҖқ and they did it a third time.
\v 35 TheВҰ168585 waterВҰ168590 ranВҰ168580 aroundВҰ168582 the altarВҰ168583 andВҰ168584 even filledВҰ168588 the trenchВҰ168587.
\p
\v 36 \add вүҲWhenВҰ168592 it was time to offerВҰ168594 the evening sacrifices\add*, the prophetВҰ168598 EliyahВҰ168597 approached \add the altar\add* and \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ168600, God of AbrahamВҰ168602, Yitshak, and Yisrael, let it be knownВҰ168606 today that you are God inВҰ168594 Yisrael and I'm your servantВҰ168613, and I'veВҰ168616 done all theseВҰ168621 thingsВҰ168620 \add вүҲfollowing your instructions\add*.
\v 37 Answer me, Yahweh! Answer me, so that this \add вүҲcountry will understand\add* that you, Yahweh, are GodВҰ168633, and that you can turn theirВҰ168638 \add #hearts\add* \add вүҲback again\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 \add вүҲThenВҰ168641 YahwehВҰ168644 sent fireВҰ168642 down from the sky that consumed the pieces of meat\add*, the firewood, the stonesВҰ168654, andВҰ168641 the dirt \add around the altar\add*, \add вүҲincluding\add* \add all\add* the waterВҰ168660 that had been inВҰ168663 the trenchВҰ168663.
\v 39 \add вүҲWhenВҰ168666 all the peopleВҰ168669 sawВҰ168666 what had happened\add*, they fell onto their \add вүҲknees andВҰ168666 bowed their facesВҰ168673 to the ground, saying\add*, вҖңYahweh is God! Yahweh is God!вҖқ
\p
\v 40 ThenВҰ168682 Eliyah \add вүҲordered\add* them, вҖңGrab hold of Baal'sВҰ168690 prophetsВҰ168689. Don't let \add вүҲany of them\add* sneak away.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ168682\add* they seizedВҰ168685 them, and Eliyah broughtВҰ168697 them down to the KishonВҰ168702 valley and he slaughteredВҰ168703 them thereВҰ168704.
\s1 The drought ends
\rem /s1 The End of the Drought; Elijah Prays for Rain; The Drought Ends
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 41 ThenВҰ168706 EliyahВҰ168707 told \add King\add* Ahav, вҖңGet \add вүҲready and have something to\add* eatВҰ168710 and drinkВҰ168711, because \add вүҲI can hear the noiseВҰ168715 of heavy\add* rain \add coming\add*.вҖқ
\v 42 \add вүҲSoВҰ168718 Ahav got ready and had something\add* to eatВҰ168720 and drinkВҰ168721, \add вүҲbutВҰ168718\add* EliyahВҰ168722 went \add вүҲfurther up\add* Mt. KarmelВҰ168727 and \add squatted\add* with his face down betweenВҰ168732 his kneesВҰ168733\x + \xo 18:42-45: \xt Jam 5:18.\x*
\v 43 and told his servantВҰ168739, вҖңGo up now, \add and\add* lookВҰ168743 towards the ocean.вҖқ
\p He went up and lookedВҰ168748 and said, вҖңThere's nothing thereВҰ168750.вҖқ
\p This happened sevenВҰ168754 timesВҰ168755,
\v 44 \add вүҲbutВҰ168757 onВҰ168758\add* the seventhВҰ168758 timeВҰ168758 he came back and said, вҖң\add вүҲWow, there'sВҰ168760\add* a smallВҰ168763 cloudВҰ168762 \add вүҲout above the ocean about the size of\add* a man's palm.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ168757 Eliyah ordered him, вҖң\add вүҲRush\add* \add and\add* tell AhabВҰ168774 \add вүҲto get his chariot ready and head down so he won'tВҰ168777 be caught inВҰ168758 the rain\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 45 \add вүҲVery soon the skyВҰ168789 was full of dark\add* cloudsВҰ168791, thenВҰ168781 wind and heavy rain. Ahav \add kept\add* riding and \add вүҲmade it\add* to \add the city of\add* YezreelВҰ168799.
\v 46 \add вүҲYahwehВҰ168803 gave EliyahВҰ168807 extra strength and he tucked his robe into his belt, and ranВҰ168810 ahead of AhavВҰ168812 goingВҰ168815\add* into YezreelВҰ168816.
\c 19
\s1 Eliyah flees to Mt. Sinai
\rem /s1 Elijah on Mount Sinai; Elijah Flees to Sinai; Elijah Flees to Horeb; Elijah Flees from Jezebel
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ168818 \add King\add* Ahav told Izevel \add (Jezebel)\add* everything that EliyahВҰ168826 had done, \add вүҲincluding how\add* he'd killedВҰ168831 all of \add Baal's\add* prophetsВҰ168836,
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* \add *she\add* sent \add вүҲthis message\add* to EliyahВҰ168844, вҖңMay the godsВҰ168849 \add вүҲkill me or do worse\add* if I \add вүҲhaven't done with your life what you did to\add* \add @those prophets\add* by this time tomorrowВҰ168855.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲHearing thatВҰ168873, he packed up andВҰ168864 fled for his lifeВҰ168869 to Be'er-Sheva in YehudahВҰ168874, where he left\add* his servantВҰ168878.
\v 4 ThenВҰ168881 he wentВҰ168887 an extra day's travel further \add south\add* into the wildernessВҰ168884 where he sat down underВҰ168889 a broomВҰ168890 bush andВҰ168881 prayed that he \add вүҲmight be allowed\add* to die, saying, вҖңThis is now too much, YahwehВҰ168902. Take my life, because I'm no better than my ancestorsВҰ168911.вҖқ\x + \xo 19:4: \xt Yonah 4:3.\x*
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ168913 he laid down and slept underВҰ168915 the broomВҰ168916 bush, \add вүҲuntil he was suddenly woken by\add* a messengerВҰ168921 \add from Yahweh\add* \add вүҲtelling him to get up and eatВҰ168927\add*.
\v 6 \add @Eliyah\add* lookedВҰ168929 \add around\add* and wow, there was some breadВҰ168932 near his head that had been cooked on glowing coalsВҰ168933, and a jug of waterВҰ168935. He got up and ateВҰ168936 and drankВҰ168937, and thenВҰ168929 lay down againВҰ168938.
\v 7 ThenВҰ168941 Yahweh's messengerВҰ168942 returned a secondВҰ168945 time and prodded him and said, вҖңGet up \add and\add* eat, because \add otherwise\add* the \add вүҲjourneyВҰ168955\add* \add ahead\add* will be too much for you.вҖқ
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ168957\add* he got up and ateВҰ168958 and drankВҰ168959. \add вүҲThat food lasted his for forty days as he travelled to\add* God's mountainВҰ168970, HorevВҰ168972 \add (MtВҰ168970. Sinai)\add*.
\rem /s1 The Lord Speaks to Elijah; The Lord Appears to Elijah
\v 9 He entered a cave there andВҰ168974 overnighted \add @in the cave\add*, thenВҰ168974 \add вүҲsuddenly YahwehВҰ168985 spoke to him, asking\add*, вҖңWhat are youВҰ168991 doing here, EliyahВҰ168993?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңI'veВҰ168997 been very zealous for \add you\add*, armyВҰ169001 commanderВҰ169001 YahwehВҰ168998,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңButВҰ168995 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ169006 peopleВҰ169006\add* have abandonedВҰ169004 your agreement, and they've torn down your altarsВҰ169010 and killedВҰ169015 your prophetsВҰ169014 withВҰ169016 the swordВҰ169016. \add вүҲSoВҰ168995\add* \add here\add* I am, left by myselfВҰ169019 \add вүҲwhile meanwhile they're trying to kill me\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 19:10-14: \xt Rom 11:3.\x*
\rem /s1 Elijah Meets God at Horeb
\p
\v 11 Then \add @Yahweh\add* said, вҖңGo out and standВҰ169028 onВҰ169029 the mountain \add вүҲin front of me,\add* Yahweh. Then look, \add *I'm\add* about to \add вүҲgo past you\add*.вҖқ Then \add вүҲthere was an incredibly\add* strongВҰ169037 wind \add вүҲthat hit the mountain and broke off bits of rock that thenВҰ169026 shattered\add*. \add ButВҰ169026\add* Yahweh wasn't in the wind, and afterВҰ169047 the wind there was an earthquake \add butВҰ169026\add* Yahweh wasn't in the earthquake \add either\add*.
\v 12 After the earthquakeВҰ169056 there was a fire, \add butВҰ169055\add* YahwehВҰ169060 wasn't inВҰ169059 the fire.
\p ThenВҰ169055 after the fire, there was the soundВҰ169063 of a soft whisperВҰ169064.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ169067\add* Eliyah heard \add >that\add*, he wrappedВҰ169071 his cloak around his face and wentВҰ169074 out and stoodВҰ169075 atВҰ169073 the opening of the cave, and he heard a voiceВҰ169080 \add вүҲask\add* him, вҖң\add вүҲWhy are\add* you here, Eliyah?вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңI'veВҰ169090 been very zealous for \add you,\add* armyВҰ169094 commanderВҰ169094 YahwehВҰ169091,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ169088\add* the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ169099 peopleВҰ169099\add* have abandonedВҰ169097 your agreement, and they've torn down your altarsВҰ169103 and killedВҰ169108 your prophetsВҰ169107 withВҰ169109 the swordВҰ169109. \add вүҲSoВҰ169088\add* \add here\add* I am, left by myselfВҰ169112 \add вүҲwhile meanwhile they're trying to kill me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 Then YahwehВҰ169121 told him, вҖңGo \add вүҲback\add* towards the DamascusВҰ169127 wildernessВҰ169126, then you must go and anointВҰ169130 HazaelВҰ169133 as kingВҰ169134 over AramВҰ169137 \add (SyriaВҰ169137)\add*.\x + \xo 19:15: \xt 2Ki 8:7-13.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲAlso\add* you \add вүҲneed to\add* anoint Nimshi'sВҰ169143 son YehuВҰ169140 as kingВҰ169145 over YisraelВҰ169148, andВҰ169139 you must anoint Shafat'sВҰ169154 son ElishaВҰ169151 from Avel-Meholah \add вүҲto succeed you as prophetВҰ169158\add*.\x + \xo 19:16: \xt 2Ki 9:1-6.\x*
\v 17 \add вүҲInВҰ169169 the future\add*, \add вүҲanyone who escapes from being killed\add* by Hazael'sВҰ169164 \add army\add* will be \add вүҲkilled\add* by Yehu'sВҰ169166 \add army\add*, andВҰ169167 \add вүҲanyone who escapes from being killed\add* by Yehu'sВҰ169164 \add army\add* will be \add вүҲkilled\add* by ElishaВҰ169171.
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ169173\add* I've \add still\add* got sevenВҰ169175 thousandВҰ169176 people inВҰ169174 YisraelВҰ169174 \add вүҲwho've never bowedВҰ169183 to BaalВҰ169184 or kissedВҰ169191 his image\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 19:18: \xt Rom 11:4.\x*
\s1 Eliyah inspires Elisha
