\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ169567\add* \add @Ahav\add* gathered the provincialВҰ169572 commanders' youngВҰ169570 men and there were 232 of them. HeВҰ169587 \add also\add* assembled the \add вүҲfighting men\add* and there were \add merely\add* sevenВҰ169588 thousandВҰ169589 of them.
\p
\v 16 They \add вүҲexited the city\add* atВҰ169592 midday, \add вүҲwhile\add* Ben-Hadad andВҰ169591 the \add other\add* kingsВҰ169600 were \add still\add* getting drunkВҰ169597 inВҰ169592 their huts.
\v 17 The youngВҰ169609 men under the provincialВҰ169611 commanders \add вүҲled the way out\add*, andВҰ169608 \add the scouts\add* \add вүҲthat BenВҰ169614-HadadВҰ169616 had sent out informed\add* him that men were coming out of ShomronВҰ169622.
\v 18 He \add вүҲordered\add*, вҖңWhether they've come out for peaceВҰ169627 or for battleВҰ169632, capture them alive.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 The provincialВҰ169644 commanders' youngВҰ169642 menВҰ169642 exited the cityВҰ169641 followedВҰ169647 by the \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ169642\add*
\v 20 andВҰ169649 each of them killedВҰ169649 their opponent. ThenВҰ169649 the ArameansВҰ169653 \add вүҲtook off with the Israelis\add* chasing them, \add вүҲbutВҰ169649\add* KingВҰ169660 BenВҰ169657-HadadВҰ169659 escapedВҰ169656 on a horseВҰ169664 along with other riders.
\v 21 ThenВҰ169667 Yisrael'sВҰ169669 kingВҰ169668 \add led more men out\add* and they attackedВҰ169670 the horsesВҰ169673 and chariotsВҰ169676вҖ”\add вүҲthoroughly defeatingВҰ169677\add* AramВҰ169678.
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲAfterwards\add* \add thatВҰ169695 same\add* prophetВҰ169683 wentВҰ169682 \add back\add* to KingВҰ169686 Ahav and told him, вҖңGo \add back and\add* \add вүҲfortify your defenses and plan your strategy\add*, because Aram'sВҰ169702 king \add вүҲwill attack you againВҰ169704 at the same time next\add* year.вҖқ
\s1 Ben-Hadad's second attack
\rem /s1 Ben-Hadad's Second Attack; The Arameans Are Defeated; The Second Syrian Attack
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* the servantsВҰ169707 of Aram'sВҰ169710 king told him, вҖңTheir gods are the gods of the hills, so that's why they were stronger than us. \add вүҲButВҰ169707\add* let's fight them onВҰ169724 the plainВҰ169724 insteadВҰ169721 \add вүҲthen we'll be sure to defeat\add* them.
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ169731 this is what you should\add* do: relieve those kingsВҰ169737 of \add вүҲtheirВҰ169742 command andВҰ169740 replace them with military commanders\add*.
\v 25 Then \add вүҲgather an army like the one that was defeated, withВҰ169760 as many horses and chariots as you had.\add* Then we'll fightВҰ169758 them onВҰ169760 the plainВҰ169760 and \add вүҲwe'll be sure to defeat\add* them.вҖқ
\p \add @Ben-Hadad\add* \add вүҲtook theirВҰ169767 advice and put the plan into action\add*.
\v 26 \add вүҲThe following\add* yearВҰ169774, \add @he\add* \add вүҲassembled his army\add* and went to AfekВҰ169783 to battle \add вүҲthe Israelis\add*,
\v 27 and the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ169790 warriors assembled and received their supplies\add*. ThenВҰ169789 they wentВҰ169793 to confront them, \add вүҲbutВҰ169789\add* \add *they\add* \add вүҲseemed like ants in comparison to the massive Aramean army\add*.
\p
\v 28 A man of God approachedВҰ169809 Yisrael'sВҰ169816 king and told \add <him\add*, вҖңYahweh says \add вүҲthat the ArameansВҰ169825\add* have been saying that he's a god of the hills, butВҰ169809 not of the valleysВҰ169832. \add вүҲBecause of that, he's going to help you defeat this hugeВҰ169840 army\add*, and thenВҰ169809 you'll know that Yahweh \add вүҲis God\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \add @The two armies\add* \add вүҲremained campedВҰ169849 oppositeВҰ169851 each other for\add* sevenВҰ169853 daysВҰ169854, thenВҰ169849 the battleВҰ169860 \add вүҲbegan andВҰ169849 the IsraelisВҰ169864 killedВҰ169861 a hundredВҰ169868 thousandВҰ169870 ArameanВҰ169865 soldiersВҰ169871 that\add* day.
\v 30 The \add вүҲremainder\add* fled into AfekВҰ169878, \add вүҲbutВҰ169875\add* the \add city\add* wall fell onto the remaining twenty-seven thousandВҰ169888 men.
\p Ben-Hadad ran into the city andВҰ169875 \add вүҲhid inВҰ169900 an inner room\add*,
\v 31 \add вүҲbutВҰ169903\add* his servantsВҰ169905 told him, вҖңListen, we've heardВҰ169909 that the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ169912 kings show\add* mercy. Please let us wrap sackclothВҰ169921 around our waistsВҰ169922 and go out to Yisrael'sВҰ169913 king withВҰ169922 ropesВҰ169923 onВҰ169922 our headsВҰ169924вҖ”perhapsВҰ169930 he'll \add вүҲspare\add* your life.вҖқ
\v 32 \add вүҲSoВҰ169936\add* they wrapped their waistsВҰ169938 inВҰ169938 sacking and put ropesВҰ169939 onВҰ169938 their headsВҰ169940, and wentВҰ169941 to Yisrael'sВҰ169945 kingВҰ169944, saying, вҖңYour servantВҰ169947 BenВҰ169948-HadadВҰ169950 \add вүҲasks you to spare his\add* life.вҖқ
\p вҖңIs he stillВҰ169957 aliveВҰ169958?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add*. вҖңHe's \add вүҲlike a brotherВҰ169959 to me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 33 The menВҰ169962 \add вүҲwere looking for an indication\add* \add of mercy\add* and \add вүҲwhen they heard that they were encouraged\add*. вҖң\add Yes,\add*, BenВҰ169969-HadadВҰ169971 is \add like\add* your brotherВҰ169968,вҖқ they said.
\p вҖң\add вүҲYes,\add*, bringВҰ169974 him \add here\add*,вҖқ he \add вүҲrespondedВҰ169967\add*.
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ169962\add* Ben-Hadad \add вүҲrevealed himself\add* and was brought into \add Ahav's\add* chariotВҰ169983,
\v 34 and he told \add @Ahav\add*, вҖңI'll returnВҰ169995 the citiesВҰ169987 that my father took from withВҰ169999 \add вүҲyoursВҰ169998\add*, and \add вүҲyour traders can set up stalls\add* in DamascusВҰ169999, just as my father \add вүҲdid\add* in ShomronВҰ170004.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲOkay, I'll accept that agreement and release\add* you,вҖқ \add Ahav said,\add* and \add вүҲafter formalising the agreement\add*, he sent him away.
\s1 A prophet condemns Ahab
\rem /s1 A Prophet Condemns Ahab
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 35 \add One day,\add* a prophetВҰ170018 \add вүҲinВҰ170023 training withВҰ170023 a group\add* told his companion, вҖңBy Yahweh's command, pleaseВҰ170026 wound me.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ170015\add* the man refusedВҰ170027 to \add вүҲslash\add* him,
\v 36 \add вүҲso\add* the \add first\add* prophet told him, вҖңBecause you didn'tВҰ170035 \add вүҲobey Yahweh's command\add*, listenВҰ170037, \add вүҲas soon as you leave here you'll be attacked by a\add* lion.вҖқ ThenВҰ170031 after he \add вүҲleft\add*, a lion foundВҰ170047 him andВҰ170031 \add вүҲkilledВҰ170049\add* him.\x + \xo 20:36: \xt 1Ki 13:24.\x*
\p
\v 37 ThenВҰ170051 he foundВҰ170051 \add вүҲanotherВҰ170053 prophet\add* and said, вҖңStrike me, pleaseВҰ170056,вҖқ and the man struckВҰ170057 him \add with a sword\add*вҖ”woundingВҰ170060 \add >him\add*.
\v 38 ThenВҰ170062 the \add wounded\add* prophetВҰ170063 \add вүҲdisguisedВҰ170069 himself\add* withВҰ170070 a covering over his eyesВҰ170073 and wentВҰ170062 and stood onВҰ170070 the roadВҰ170068 \add to wait\add* for the kingВҰ170065.
\v 39 \add вүҲWhenВҰ170075 the king came past\add*, \add @the prophet\add* called out to \add *him\add*, saying, вҖңYour servantВҰ170084 went out in the middle of the battleВҰ170089, and suddenly, a man \add вүҲcame across withВҰ170087 a captive\add* and told \add >me\add*, вҖҳGuard this man. If he \add вүҲgoes\add* missing, your life will be \add forfeit\add* in placeВҰ170109 of his, or else you'll \add вүҲbe fined three thousand pieces\add* of silverВҰ170114.вҖҷ
\v 40 \add вүҲButВҰ170117 while I was busy with other things, the man escaped\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Well,\add* \add вүҲby your own testimony, you deserve your punishment\add*,вҖқ \add @King Ahav\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ170124\add*.
\p
\v 41 ThenВҰ170134 he quicklyВҰ170134 \add вүҲuncovered\add* his eyesВҰ170141 andВҰ170134 the kingВҰ170144 recognisedВҰ170142 that he was one of the prophetsВҰ170147,
\v 42 and \add @the prophet\add* told him, вҖңYahwehВҰ170154 says that becauseВҰ170155 you \add вүҲreleased\add* a man \add вүҲwho shouldВҰ170156 have been executed\add*, thenВҰ170150 your life \add will be required\add* in place of his, and your people in place of his people.вҖқ
\p
\v 43 ThenВҰ170171 the kingВҰ170172 wentВҰ170171 \add on\add* to his houseВҰ170177 in ShomronВҰ170181, \add butВҰ170171 he was\add* \add вүҲangryВҰ170179 andВҰ170171 depressed inside\add*.
\c 21
\s1 Navot's vineyard
\rem /s1 Naboth's Vineyard
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSometime afterВҰ170185 thatВҰ170192\add*, KingВҰ170197 Ahav from ShomronВҰ170198 \add was in his\add* palaceВҰ170195 in Yizreel city, andВҰ170184 \add вүҲhis neighbour was\add* the YezreeliteВҰ170191 Navot \add (NabothВҰ170190)\add* \add вүҲwithВҰ170193 his\add* vineyardВҰ170188.
\v 2 Ahav \add вүҲpressured\add* Navot, вҖңGive me yourВҰ170233 vineyard \add вүҲso I can make it into my vegetableВҰ170219 gardenВҰ170217\add* because it's right besideВҰ170223 my houseВҰ170224. \add вүҲI can replace it withВҰ170233\add* a better vineyard, \add вүҲor if you prefer, I can pay you inВҰ170233 silver for\add* this one.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ170241\add* Navot \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңFar be it for me \add вүҲto disobey\add* YahwehВҰ170248 by giving up the inheritanceВҰ170252 \add вүҲentrusted to\add* my ancestorsВҰ170253.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ170256\add* Ahav went \add back\add* to his palace bitter and angryВҰ170262 \add вүҲbecause of Navot's refusal to turn over the land\add*. He \add вүҲrefused to eat\add* and \add вүҲwent\add* to bed with his face towards the wall,
\v 5 \add вүҲbutВҰ170294\add* his wife Izevel wentВҰ170294 in and \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖңWhat's this \add вүҲabout eatingВҰ170306 nothing and going to bed in a sulk\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖң\add вүҲWell,\add* I talked withВҰ170326 Navot the YezreeliteВҰ170317,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲI offered to pay cash for his vineyard or to exchange it for another one if he preferred, butВҰ170309 he wouldn't let me have it\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖң\add What!\add* \add вүҲYou're the king of\add* YisraelВҰ170356!вҖқ his wife \add вүҲrespondedВҰ170346\add*. вҖңGet up \add and\add* \add вүҲhave something to eatВҰ170358 and cheerВҰ170361 up\add*! I'llВҰ170364 \add вүҲmake sure myself that you get\add* Navot's vineyardВҰ170368.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ170372\add* she wroteВҰ170372 lettersВҰ170373 inВҰ170377 Ahav's nameВҰ170374 and sealedВҰ170376 them withВҰ170377 his seal. ThenВҰ170372 she sentВҰ170378 them to the cityВҰ170389 eldersВҰ170383 and noblesВҰ170387 who livedВҰ170390 near Navot.
\v 9 \add вүҲThis is what\add* she wroteВҰ170395, вҖңAnnounce a fast, andВҰ170401 seatВҰ170401 Navot hear the head \add вүҲof the table\add*.
\v 10 Then seatВҰ170408 twoВҰ170409 \add вүҲtroublemakers oppositeВҰ170414\add* him, and get them to testifyВҰ170415 against him that he cursed GodВҰ170418 and the kingВҰ170419. Then takeВҰ170420 him outside and \add вүҲpelt him with rocks until he's dead\add*.
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ170424 the eldersВҰ170427 andВҰ170424 noblesВҰ170428 of the city did what IzevelВҰ170435 had instructed them via the lettersВҰ170438:
\v 12 They announced a fast andВҰ170445 seatedВҰ170445 Navot near the head \add вүҲof the table\add*,
\v 13 thenВҰ170452 two worthlessВҰ170457 men \add вүҲwere seated oppositeВҰ170459 him\add*, and they testified inВҰ170477 front of \add all\add* the peopleВҰ170467 that Navot had cursed GodВҰ170471 and the kingВҰ170472. \add вүҲSoВҰ170452\add* Navot was led out of the cityВҰ170475 and \add вүҲkilled by having rocksВҰ170477 thrown atВҰ170477 him\add*,
\v 14 andВҰ170487 they sentВҰ170480 \add a message\add* to Izevel \add вүҲto tell her that Navot had been stonedВҰ170485 to death\add*.
\p
\v 15 As soon as Izevel heardВҰ170490 that Navot had been \add вүҲexecuted\add*, \add *she\add* told Ahav, вҖң\add вүҲGo onВҰ170515 now\add* \add andВҰ170489\add* \add вүҲtakeВҰ170503 over\add* Navot's vineyardВҰ170506 that he refusedВҰ170511 to \add вүҲsell\add* you, because he's \add вүҲnot around any more\add*вҖ”he's dead.вҖқ
\v 16 As soon as Ahav heardВҰ170525 that Navot was dead, \add *he\add* went to the vineyardВҰ170535 to takeВҰ170538 possessionВҰ170538 of it.
\rem /s1 Elijah Pronounces God's Sentence
\p
\v 17 Then YahwehВҰ170544 told EliyahВҰ170547 (from TishbeВҰ170548),
\v 18 вҖң\add вүҲLeave here\add* \add and\add* goВҰ170552 to Yisrael'sВҰ170557 kingВҰ170555 Ahav in ShomronВҰ170559. Listen, he's there in Navot's vineyardВҰ170561, whereВҰ170563 he's gone to \add вүҲtakeВҰ170567 possessionВҰ170567 of\add* itВҰ170567.
\v 19 Tell him that Yahweh's asking if he's taking possessionВҰ170578 \add of the property\add* \add вүҲof a murderedВҰ170575 man\add*. ThenВҰ170569 tell him that Yahweh \add вүҲwants him to know that\add* the dogs will lick his blood inВҰ170585 the same placeВҰ170585 whereВҰ170586 Navot died and the dogs came and licked up his blood.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add WhenВҰ170602 EliyahВҰ170606 arrived\add*, Ahav \add вүҲasked\add* \add *him\add*, вҖң\add Ah,\add* my enemyВҰ170608. Have youВҰ170612 found me?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* I'veВҰ170610 found \add >you\add*,вҖқ \add @Eliyah\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲIt seems you've sold your soul by doingВҰ170613 what Yahweh's finds to be evilВҰ170614\add*.
\v 21 \add Yahweh says that\add* \add вүҲhe's aboutВҰ170619 to send disaster onВҰ170628 you to destroy\add* you and \add вүҲevery male inВҰ170628 your householdвҖ”whether they're slaves or free\add*.
\v 22 Your \add entire\add* \add вүҲfamily will be eliminated\add* like the families of Nebat'sВҰ170641 son Yarave'amВҰ170638 and Ahiyyah's son BaashaВҰ170643 becauseВҰ170647 you'veВҰ170651 provokedВҰ170651 \add Yahweh's\add* angerВҰ170651 and made YisraelВҰ170655 sinВҰ170652.
\v 23 Also concerningВҰ170659 Izevel, YahwehВҰ170661 says that the dogs will eat \add *her body\add* by Yezreel'sВҰ170669 \add city\add* \add вүҲwall\add*.\x + \xo 21:23: \xt 2Ki 9:36.\x*
\v 24 \add TheВҰ170672 bodies of\add* any of your family who die in the cityВҰ170673 will be eaten by dogs, andВҰ170676 any who die in the countrysideВҰ170677 will be eaten by birds.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 Surely there was never \add вүҲanyoneВҰ170685 else as evilВҰ170690 as Ahav who sold his soul by doingВҰ170689 what YahwehВҰ170692 was said was wrongвҖ”albeit often\add* incitedВҰ170695 by his wife Izevel.
\v 26 He \add also\add* behaved disgustingly by \add вүҲworshipping\add* idolsВҰ170704 like the AmoritesВҰ170708 had done \add before\add* YahwehВҰ170711 \add вүҲremoved them from the land as the IsraelisВҰ170714 entered\add*.
\p
\v 27 As soon as Ahav heardВҰ170718 that messageВҰ170722, he tore his clothesВҰ170725 and dressed in sacking and fastedВҰ170732. He \add even\add* slept in the sackcloth, and he walked around \add вүҲslowly\add* \add withВҰ170734 his head down\add*.
\p
\v 28 Then YahwehВҰ170742 \add вүҲasked\add* EliyahВҰ170745 (from TishbeВҰ170746),
\v 29 вҖңHave you \add вүҲnoticed\add* that Ahav has \add вүҲshown repentance towards me\add*? Because he's humbled himself, I won'tВҰ170760 bring \add вүҲthat disaster onВҰ170765 his family while he's still alive\add*, \add but rather\add* I'llВҰ170762 do \add *it\add* \add вүҲduring his son'sВҰ170767 reign\add*.вҖқ
\c 22
\s1 prophet Mikayehu and King Ahav
\rem /s1 Joint Campaign with Judah against Aram; Jehoshaphat and Ahab; Micaiah Prophesies Against Ahab; The Prophet Micaiah Warns Ahab
\s4 Both kingdoms
\r (2 Chr. 18:2-27)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ170774 \add almost\add* threeВҰ170775 yearsВҰ170776 went by without war between AramВҰ170780 \add (SyriaВҰ170780)\add* andВҰ170781 YisraelВҰ170782,
\v 2 \add вүҲbutВҰ170785\add* inВҰ170786 the thirdВҰ170787 year, Yehudah'sВҰ170792 KingВҰ170790 YehoshafatВҰ170789 went \add вүҲup north\add* to visit Yisrael'sВҰ170796 king.
\p
\v 3 \add While they were talking,\add* KingВҰ170799 Ahav said to his servantsВҰ170804, вҖңDo you know that RamotВҰ170809-GileadВҰ170810 \add вүҲshould be ours, butВҰ170798 we haven't reclaimed\add* it from Aram'sВҰ170817 king?вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ170819 he \add вүҲasked\add* YehoshafatВҰ170822, вҖңWill you go to war \add вүҲwith us to reclaim\add* RamotВҰ170826-GileadВҰ170827?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲYou and me are together\add*,вҖқ Yehoshafat told Yisrael'sВҰ170833 king. вҖң\add вүҲMy people are your people, and my horses are your horses\add*.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲThenВҰ170841 he added\add*, вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ170841 let's ask YahwehВҰ170854\add* \add about it first\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ170856\add* Yisrael'sВҰ170859 king gatheredВҰ170856 aboutВҰ170863 four hundredВҰ170864 prophetsВҰ170862 togetherВҰ170856 andВҰ170856 asked them, вҖңShould I \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ170871-GileadВҰ170872, or \add вүҲnot\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲahead\add*, because \add #our\add* masterВҰ170880\f + \fr 22:6 \ft Note that they don't mention вҖҳYahwehвҖҷ here.\f* will give \add вүҲyou victory\add*,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ170884\add* YehoshafatВҰ170885 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңIsВҰ170892 there no prophetВҰ170888 of YahwehВҰ170889 stillВҰ170890 \add around\add* here \add вүҲthat we can ask\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңThere's stillВҰ170902 one man \add вүҲwho speaksВҰ170931 for\add* YahwehВҰ170909,вҖқ \add @Ahav\add* \add вүҲreplied\add* to YehoshafatВҰ170928, вҖңYimla's son Mikayehu, butВҰ170894 I myself hate him because he \add вүҲnever prophesiesВҰ170916 anything\add* good aboutВҰ170917 meвҖ”\add вүҲonly negative things\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңThe king shouldn'tВҰ170914 \add вүҲtalk like that\add*,вҖқ said Yehoshafat.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ170935\add* Yisrael'sВҰ170937 kingВҰ170936 \add вүҲordered an official to fetch Yimla's son Mikayehu straight away\add*.
\rem /s1 Micaiah Prophesies against Ahab
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲNow\add* Yisrael'sВҰ170950 king \add Ahav\add* and Yehudah'sВҰ170954 king Yehoshafat were \add вүҲboth wearing theirВҰ170959 royal robes and sittingВҰ170955 onВҰ170962 thronesВҰ170959 atВҰ170962 a gateВҰ170964 inВҰ170962 Shomron'sВҰ170965 city wall, and many prophetsВҰ170968 were speaking messages to them\add*.
\v 11 Kenaanah'sВҰ170977 son TsidkiyyahВҰ170974 made \add вүҲsome hornsВҰ170978 for himself out of iron\add* andВҰ170980 saidВҰ170980, вҖңYahwehВҰ170984 saysВҰ170983 that you'll gore AramВҰ170989 withВҰ170985 theseВҰ170985 untilВҰ170990 they're destroyedВҰ170992.вҖқ
\v 12 All the \add other\add* prophets were prophesying \add вүҲsimilarly\add*, saying \add things like\add*, вҖң\add Yes,\add* \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ171001-GileadВҰ171002 and be successful, and YahwehВҰ171005 will \add вүҲrestore it back to you\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Micaiah Predicts Failure
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* the messengerВҰ171009 who had gone to call Mikayehu told him, вҖңListen, please, \add вүҲall the other prophets agree together as they prophesy victory for\add* the kingВҰ171030. Please let yourВҰ171034 messageВҰ171034 be \add вүҲsimilar to theirs\add* andВҰ171039 \add вүҲbe positive\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңAs surely as Yahweh lives,вҖқ Mikayehu \add вүҲrespondedВҰ171042\add*, вҖңI'llВҰ171055 only tell Ahav what Yahweh tells me to sayВҰ171051.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲWhenВҰ171057\add* he got to KingВҰ171060 \add Ahav\add*, the king asked him, вҖңMikayehu, should we \add вүҲattack\add* RamotВҰ171068-GileadВҰ171069, or \add вүҲnot\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲahead\add* and be successful,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңand YahwehВҰ171079 will give \add вүҲit back to\add* the king.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲButВҰ171083\add* \add looking at him,\add* the kingВҰ171085 saidВҰ171083 to him, вҖңHow many timesВҰ171089 do I have to make you promise that you'll \add вүҲonly tell the truthВҰ171099 about me when you pass on Yahweh's messages\add*?
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add Well,\add*вҖқ he said, вҖңI saw all YisraelВҰ171109 scatteredВҰ171110 into the hills like \add вүҲsheepВҰ171114\add* without a shepherdВҰ171119, andВҰ171103 YahwehВҰ171121 said \add вүҲthatВҰ171115 they have no leaders so they shouldВҰ171126 all returnВҰ171126 peacefullyВҰ171130 to their homes\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 22:17: \xt Num 27:17; Mat 9:36; Mrk 6:34.\x*
\p
\v 18 вҖң\add Ah,\add*вҖқ King \add вүҲAhav\add* told \add King\add* YehoshafatВҰ171138, вҖңDidn't I tell you that he wouldn't prophesyВҰ171144 \add anything\add* goodВҰ171146 aboutВҰ171145 meвҖ”\add вүҲonly bad news\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ171152\add* \add @Mikayehu\add* \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ171152\add*, вҖңListen to Yahweh's messageВҰ171155 thenВҰ171152: I sawВҰ171158 Yahweh sittingВҰ171162 on his throneВҰ171165, andВҰ171152 all the heavenlyВҰ171169 army were standingВҰ171170 at \add вүҲboth sides of him\add*.\x + \xo 22:19: \xt Yob 1:6; Isa 6:1.\x*
\v 20 ThenВҰ171175 YahwehВҰ171176 \add вүҲasked\add* who could deceiveВҰ171178 Ahav to \add вүҲattack\add* Ramot-Gilead so that he'd get killed there. \add вүҲSome suggested one thing andВҰ171175 others suggested something else\add*.
\v 21 ThenВҰ171193 a spiritВҰ171194 came out and stoodВҰ171195 \add вүҲinВҰ171205 frontВҰ171196 of\add* Yahweh and offered to deceive \add the king\add*, and Yahweh \add вүҲasked\add* him \add вүҲhow he intended to do it\add*.
\v 22 He \add вүҲreplied that he'd go and be a falseВҰ171211 spiritВҰ171210 so the kings prophetsВҰ171215 would tell lies\add*, and Yahweh \add вүҲsaid that that would work and told him to go ahead and do it\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ171226\add* now, listen, Yahweh has \add вүҲput a lying a spiritВҰ171230 into\add* all theseВҰ171236 prophetsВҰ171235 of yours, andВҰ171237 Yahweh has \add вүҲdeclared disaster onВҰ171232\add* youВҰ171239.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ171242 Tsidkiyyah (Kenaanah'sВҰ171246 son) \add вүҲwentВҰ171242 over and slappedВҰ171247 Mikayehu on the face\add*, and saidВҰ171254, вҖң\add вүҲSince when did Yahweh's spiritВҰ171259 leave me and start speakingВҰ171263 through\add* youВҰ171264?вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңListen \add here\add*,вҖқ Mikayehu replied, вҖңyou'll \add вүҲfind that out soon enough when you sneakВҰ171273 into an inner room to try andВҰ171266 hide\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 KingВҰ171279 \add вүҲAhav commanded\add*, вҖңTake Mikayehu to AmonВҰ171288, the cityВҰ171291 commander, andВҰ171278 to \add *my\add* son YoashВҰ171294.
\v 27 Tell \add вүҲthem that the kingВҰ171302 orders them to imprisonВҰ171308 this man and limit his breadВҰ171310 and waterВҰ171312 untilВҰ171314 I return safely\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖңIf you do return safely,вҖқ Mikayehu \add вүҲremarked\add*, вҖңthenВҰ171318 YahwehВҰ171328 hasn't spokenВҰ171327 through me.вҖқ And heВҰ171327 \add вүҲadded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲTake note all you peopleВҰ171332\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Ahav's death
\rem /s1 Ahab Killed at Ramoth Gilead; The Death of Ahab; Defeat and Death of Ahab
\s4 Northern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 18:28-34)
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ171335\add* so Yisrael'sВҰ171338 King \add Ahav\add* and Yehudah'sВҰ171343 King YehoshafatВҰ171339 \add вүҲleft to go and attack\add* RamotВҰ171344-GileadВҰ171345,
\v 30 andВҰ171347 \add @Ahav\add* told Yehoshafat, вҖңI'llВҰ171353 \add вүҲgo into the battle incognito, butВҰ171347\add* you can wear your \add вүҲroyal robesВҰ171358\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ171347\add* Yisrael'sВҰ171349 king \add вүҲchanged into ordinary clothes before heading\add* into the battle.
\p
\v 31 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Aram'sВҰ171366 king had orderedВҰ171367 his thirty-two chariotВҰ171371 commandersВҰ171367, вҖң\add вүҲDon't fight with the rank andВҰ171365 fileвҖ”only attack Yisrael'sВҰ171392 king\add*.вҖқ
\v 32 As soon as the chariotВҰ171398 commandersВҰ171397 sawВҰ171396 Yehudah's KingВҰ171405 Yehoshafat, they \add вүҲthought\add* to themselves, вҖңSurely that's Yisrael'sВҰ171407 kingВҰ171405.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ171395 thenВҰ171395 they came over to attack\add* him, butВҰ171395 Yehoshafat yelledВҰ171412 out,
\v 33 andВҰ171415 as soon as \add *they\add* realisedВҰ171416 that he wasn't the kingВҰ171423 of YisraelВҰ171424, they \add вүҲstopped chasingВҰ171427 him\add*.
\v 34 ButВҰ171429 one manВҰ171429 casually \add вүҲshot an arrow withВҰ171431 his\add* and \add вүҲit\add* struckВҰ171433 Yisrael'sВҰ171437 kingВҰ171436 between the \add вүҲplates of his\add* body armourВҰ171439, and he called to his \add вүҲchariotВҰ171443 driverВҰ171443\add*, вҖңTurn \add вүҲaroundВҰ171444 and get me out of the battleВҰ171449\add* because I'veВҰ171451 been woundedВҰ171451.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 The battleВҰ171454 \add вүҲcarried onВҰ171460 all\add* that day and KingВҰ171457 \add Ahav\add* was \add вүҲpropped\add* up inВҰ171460 \add &his\add* chariot oppositeВҰ171461 AramВҰ171462, \add вүҲhowever\add* he died that eveningВҰ171464 and the bloodВҰ171466 from his woundВҰ171468 \add вүҲpooled into the bottomВҰ171471 of his\add* the chariot.
\v 36 ThenВҰ171474 the \add вүҲcall went throughВҰ171474 the battle lines\add* just as the sunВҰ171478 \add вүҲwas going down\add*, вҖң\add Every\add* manВҰ171484 \add should abandon the battlefield andВҰ171474\add* \add вүҲreturn to his home\add*вҖқ
\p
\v 37 \add вүҲSoВҰ171489\add* KingВҰ171490 \add Ahav\add* diedВҰ171489 andВҰ171489 \add вүҲwas taken back\add* to Shomron \add вүҲwhere he was\add* buriedВҰ171493.
\v 38 They washedВҰ171499 out the chariotВҰ171502 beside the pool in ShomronВҰ171506 (where the prostitutesВҰ171512 bathedВҰ171513 themselves), andВҰ171499 dogs lickedВҰ171507 up the bloodВҰ171511, \add вүҲjust as YahwehВҰ171515 had said would happen\add*.
\p
\v 39 \add вүҲEverything else about Ahav and everything that he did, including the ivoryВҰ171527 palaceВҰ171526 and all the citiesВҰ171532 that he had built, is writtenВҰ171538 in the book of the events\add* of the kingsВҰ171544 of YisraelВҰ171545.
\v 40 \add вүҲNow that Ahav was dead, his son AhazyahВҰ171553 replaced him as kingВҰ171552\add*.
\s1 Yehoshafat's reign over Yehudah
\rem /s1 Jehoshaphat Rules in Judah; Jehoshaphat King of Judah; Jehoshaphat Reigns over Judah; King Jehoshaphat of Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Chr. 20:31вҖ“21:1)
\p
\v 41 Asa'sВҰ171561 son YehoshafatВҰ171558 \add started\add* \add вүҲhis reign\add* over YehudahВҰ171565 when KingВҰ171562 AhavВҰ171568 \add had ruled\add* YisraelВҰ171570 for fourВҰ171567 years.
\v 42 Yehoshafat was thirty-five when he \add вүҲbecameВҰ171578 kingВҰ171578\add* and he reignedВҰ171582 from YerushalemВҰ171583 for twenty-five years. (His motherВҰ171585 was Shilhi'sВҰ171589 daughterВҰ171587 Azuvah.)
\v 43 He \add вүҲfollowed\add* his fatherВҰ171596 AsaВҰ171595 in every wayВҰ171594 in doingВҰ171601 \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ171604 wanted\add*вҖ”he didn't \add вүҲveer\add* away from it, except that they didn't \add вүҲdemolish the hilltop temples so\add* the people were still sacrificing andВҰ171591 burning incense at \add *those\add* places.
\v 44 Yehoshafat did make \add вүҲa peace treaty\add* withВҰ171616 Yisrael's king.
\p
\v 45 \add вүҲEverything else\add* about YehoshafatВҰ171620, \add вүҲincluding his great achievements andВҰ171619 his battle record\add*, is written in the book of the \add вүҲevents\add* of the kings of Yehudah,
\v 46 and \add including how\add* he \add вүҲbanished\add* the male prostitutes from the land who had remained from the time of his father Asa.
\p
\v 47 \add At thatВҰ171651 time,\add* there was no king inВҰ171653 EdomвҖ”a governor \add appointed by Yehoshafat\add* ruled there.
\p
\v 48 Yehoshafat \add вүҲhad trading ships made\add* to go to Ophir for gold, butВҰ171662 \add #they\add* didn'tВҰ171663 go because the ships \add вүҲgot wrecked\add* atВҰ171664 Etsyon-Gaver.
\v 49 Ahav's son Ahazyah had said to Yehoshafat, вҖңLet my servants go withВҰ171684 your servants inВҰ171684 the ships.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ171677\add* Yehoshafat hadn't \add вүҲaccepted the offer\add*.
\p
\v 50 Then YehoshafatВҰ171696 \add вүҲdied\add* and was buried withВҰ171702 his ancestors inВҰ171702 the City of his ancestor David, and his son Yehoram \add вүҲreplaced him as king\add*.
\s1 Ahazyah's reign over Yisrael
\rem /s1 Ahaziah Reigns over Israel; Ahaziah King of Israel; Ahaziah Rules in Israel; King Ahaziah of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 51 Ahav's son Ahazyah \add began to\add* reign over Yisrael from Samaria inВҰ171717 the seventeenth year of KingВҰ171720 Yehoshafat's \add reign over\add* Yehudah, and he reigned over Yisrael for two years.
\v 52 He followed the \add вүҲbehaviour\add* of his father and mother and Nebat's son Yarave'am, and did \add вүҲwhat Yahweh had said was\add* evilвҖ”causing YisraelВҰ171734 to sin \add вүҲlike they had\add*.
\v 53 He served Baal and bowed down to him, and he provoked Yisrael'sВҰ171767 god YahwehВҰ171752 to \add вүҲget angry, similarly to everything\add* that his fatherВҰ171755 had done.
